pron/u/uka/ukadj/ukadjus030.mp3'),('adopt','收养；领养接受；采用；采纳选定；选用；采用养成某种习惯','uk :əˈdɒpt, us :əˈdɑːpt','[They\'ve adopted a baby girl. \n 他们领养了一个女婴。 \n, She had the child adopted (= she gave her baby to someone else to take care of). \n 她把自己的孩子送给别人抚养。 \n, They have no children of their own, but they\'re hoping to adopt. \n 他们没有亲生子女，但是希望能领养。 \n, I think it\'s time to adopt a different strategy in my dealings with him. \n 我觉得在和他的交往中该采用一种不同的策略了。 \n, The new tax would force companies to adopt energy-saving measures. \n 征收新税将迫使公司采取节能措施。 \n, He\'s adopted a remarkably light-hearted attitude towards the situation. \n 面对这种局面，他摆出了一种异乎寻常的轻描淡写的态度。 \n, Dr Kennedy has been adopted as the party\'s candidate for South Cambridge. \n 肯尼迪博士被选定为该党南剑桥地区的候选人。 \n, Roz has adopted one or two funny mannerisms since she\'s been away. \n 罗兹自她离开后养成了一两种可笑的怪癖。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukadm/ukadmon008.mp3'),('adultery','通奸（行为）','uk :əˈdʌl.tər.i, us :əˈdʌl.tɚ.i','[Many people in public life have committed adultery. \n 很多知名人物都有通奸行为。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukadu/ukadult002.mp3'),('aeronautical','航空','uk :ˌeə.rəˈnɔː.tɪ.kəl, us :ˌer.əˈnɑː.t̬ɪ.kəl','[eronautical engineering/science\n, Aeronautical charts are not available to view online but you can buy them.\n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaer/ukaerog003.mp3'),('aggro','（尤指青少年团伙之间的）斗殴，闹事，暴力行为烦恼；麻烦','uk :ˈæɡ.rəʊ, us :ˈæɡ.roʊ','[There was some aggro between rival fans at the station. \n 足球比赛对阵双方的球迷在车站寻衅闹事。 \n, Why are you being so uncooperative? I don t need this aggro. \n 你为什么这样不合作？我不想找这种麻烦。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukage/ukage__026.mp3'),('agility','敏捷','uk :əˈdʒɪl.ə.ti, us :əˈdʒɪl.ə.t̬i','[e has the agility of a mountain goat.\n, The acrobats