chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukann/ukannou008.mp3'),('anomalies','异常的人（或事物）；不规则；（同一种类中的）畸形','uk :əˈnɒm.ə.li, us :əˈnɑː.mə.li','[Statistical anomalies can make it difficult to compare economic data from one year to the next. \n 统计上的不规范会使年与年之间的经济数据难以互相比较。 \n, The anomaly of the social security system is that you sometimes have more money without a job. \n 社会保障制度下的反常现象是，失业有时反而拿钱更多。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukann/ukannou023.mp3'),('anticipate','预期，期望；预料采取行动来防止；先发制人','uk :ænˈtɪs.ɪ.peɪt, us :ænˈtɪs.ə.peɪt','[We don\'t anticipate any trouble. \n 我们不希望出现任何问题。 \n, We had one or two difficulties along the way that we didn\'t anticipate. \n 在进行的过程中，我们遇到一两个没有预料到的难题。 \n, Are you anticipating a lot of people at the party tonight? \n 你预计今晚的聚会会有很多人来吗？ \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n They anticipate having several applicants for the job. \n 他们预计会有几个人来应聘这份工作。 \n, [ + that ] \n They anticipate that they will have several applicants for the job \n 他们预计会有几个人来应聘这份工作。 \n, [ + question word ] \n At this stage we can\'t really anticipate what will happen. \n 在这个阶段我们真的无法预料会发生什么。 \n, The anticipated inflation figure is lower than last month\'s. \n 预计中的通货膨胀数字低于上月。 \n, It\'s always best to anticipate a problem before it arises. \n 防患于未然永远都是最明智之举。 \n, The army anticipated (= took action in preparation for) the explosion by evacuating the town. \n 这支军队预料会发生爆炸，已疏散了镇上居民。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukant/ukantep026.mp3'),('antisepsis','防腐劑；（尤指）殺菌劑，消毒劑, 不受感染的','ˈantiˌsepsis','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('antiseptic','防腐剂；（尤指）杀菌剂，消毒剂不受感染的；消过毒的；无菌的过分整洁而显得单调的，过于整洁而呆板的','uk :ˌæn.tiˈsep.tɪk, us :ˌæn.t̬iˈsep.tɪk','[Antiseptic is used to sterilize the skin before giving an injection. \n 消毒剂用于注射前给皮肤消毒。 \n, Many of the ingredients for antiseptics come from the rainforests. \n 很多杀菌剂的原料产自热带雨林。 \n, In the 1870s and 1880s, doctors began to follow the principles of antiseptic surgery. \n 在19世纪70和80年代，医生们开始遵循无菌外科手术原则。 \n, There s an antiseptic feeling to the new town centre, with its covered shopping mall. \n 新建的市中心购物广场上面架了棚顶，一切过于整洁而显得有些呆板。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukant/ukantic030.mp3'),('apes','猿；无尾猿；类人猿（拙劣地）模仿','uk :eɪp, us :eɪp','[Chimpanzees and gorillas are both apes. \n 黑猩猩和大猩猩都是类人猿。 \n, He called the new building unoriginal and said that it merely aped the classical traditions. \n 他称这座新楼的风格毫无新意，并说它只不过是对古典传统建筑的拙劣模仿。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukapa/ukapart005.mp3'),('apparently','据…所知；看来；据说；听说实际上好像；似乎；看起来','uk :əˈpær.ənt.li, us :əˈper.ənt.li','[Apparently it s going to rain today. \n 看样子今天有雨。 \n, Apparently he s had enough of England and is going back to Australia. \n 据说他在英国呆够了，要回澳大利亚。 \n, You know I told you Alice s party was on the 13th? Well I saw her last night and apparently it s on the 14th. \n 你还记得我告诉过你爱丽丝的聚会在13号举行，可是我昨晚见到她后得知实际上是14号。 \n, She looks about ten, but apparently she s 14. \n 她看上去差不多10岁，可实际上都14岁了。 \n, I thought they were married but apparently not (= they are not married). \n 我以为他们结婚了，但实际上并不是这样。 \n, An 80-year-old woman was badly hurt in what the police describe as an apparently motiveless attack (= an attack for no apparent reason). \n 一位80岁的老太太遇袭受重伤，警察称这似乎是一起无动机袭击。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukapo/ukapolo021.mp3'),('applause','掌声','uk :əˈplɔːz, us :əˈplɑːz','[His speech met with (= received) loud applause. \n 他的讲话赢得热烈的掌声。 \n, So let s have a round of applause, please, for (= please applaud) a very talented young lady who is going to sing for us. \n 好，让我们热烈鼓掌，欢迎一位才华横溢的年轻女士为我们演唱。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukapp/ukappen013.mp3'),('appreciation','欣赏；理解；感谢（价格，价值等的）上涨，增值','uk :əˌpriː.ʃiˈeɪ.ʃən, us :əˌpriː.ʃiˈeɪ.ʃən','[Max has no appreciation of the finer things in life. \n 马克斯对生活中高雅点的事物都不懂欣赏。 \n, The crowd cheered in appreciation. \n 观众喝彩叫好。 \n, Children rarely show any appreciation of/for what their parents do for them. \n 孩子们对父母为自己所做的一切鲜少表现出感激之情。 \n, These flowers are a token of my appreciation of/for all your help. \n 你们给予我那么多帮助，这些鲜花聊表谢意。 \n, There has been little appreciation in the value of property recently. \n 最近房地产价格几乎没有上涨。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukapp/ukappra008.mp3'),('arachnia','八脚怪大蜘蛛','null','null\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'null'),('arc','弧；弧状；弧线；弧形电弧，弧光循弧线行进；做弧形运动形成电弧','uk :ɑːk, us :ɑːrk','[The ball rose in a high arc and fell behind the boundary line. \n 球在空中高高地划了一条弧线落在边线外。 \n, The rocket arced gracefully into the sky. \n 火箭升空，在空中划出一条优美的弧线。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaqu/ukaquat024.mp3'),('ascendant','飞黄腾达；步步高升；日益受欢迎；占有优势','uk :əˈsen.dənt, us :əˈsen.dənt','[He s very much in the ascendant in Hollywood. \n 他在好莱坞的事业蒸蒸日上。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukasb/ukasbes005.mp3'),('assault','殴打；袭击，攻击攻关，攻坚；硬仗暴力殴打殴打；袭击，攻击','uk :əˈsɒlt, us :əˈsɑːlt','[He was charged with sexual assault. \n 他被指控性侵犯。 \n, K \n The number of indecent assaults has increased alarmingly over the past year. \n 在过去的一年中，强暴猥亵案件数量的增长令人震惊。 \n, an assault on a police officer \n 袭击警察 \n, They launched an assault on the capital yesterday. \n 昨天他们对首都发起了进攻。 \n, Women s groups have demanded a nationwide assault on sexism in the workplace. \n 妇女团体已经要求在全国范围内发动一场反对工作场所性别歧视的攻坚战。 \n, She died heroically during an assault on the world s second-highest mountain. \n 她在尝试攀登世界第二高峰时英勇牺牲。 \n, A woman and a man have been convicted of assaulting a police officer. \n 一名女子和一名男子被判袭警罪名成立。 \n, He had attempted to sexually assault the woman. \n 他试图对该妇女进行性侵犯。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukass/ukassau001.mp3'),('associate','将…（与…）联系起来，把…联系在一起朋友；同事；（生意）伙伴副学士，准学士副的；准的；非正式的','uk :əˈsəʊ.si.eɪt, us :əˈsoʊ.ʃi.eɪt',NULL,'2020-01-07',0,3,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukass/ukassiz004.mp3'),('astronomer','天文学家','uk :əˈstrɒn.ə.mər, us :əˈstrɑː.nə.mɚ','[]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukast/ukaston019.mp3'),('astrophysicist','天体物理学天体物理学家','uk :ˌæs.trəʊˈfɪz.ɪks, us :ˌæs.troʊˈfɪz.ɪks',NULL,'2020-02-14',2,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukast/ukaston026.mp3'),('asylum','（尤指政治）避难，庇护精神病院','uk :əˈsaɪ.ləm, us :əˈsaɪ.ləm','[to seek/apply for political asylum \n 寻求／申请政治避难 \n, a lunatic asylum \n 精神病院 \n]\n','2019-12-18',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukasu/ukasund002.mp3'),('at-the-drop-of-a-hat','一时冲动','','null\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'null'),('atmosphere','（包围地球的）大气，大气层，大气圈（包围天体的）气体（特定场所的）空气气氛；环境氛围；情调，情趣','uk :ˈæt.mə.sfɪər, us :ˈæt.mə.sfɪr','[These factories are releasing toxic gases into the atmosphere. \n 这些工厂向大气中排放有毒气体。 \n, the search for planets with a breathable atmosphere \n 寻找有可呼吸气体的星球 \n, The atmosphere in the room was so stuffy I could hardly breathe. \n 房间里空气污浊，我都快喘不过气来了。 \n, A few plants in an office will improve the atmosphere. \n 在办公室里摆些植物可以改善空气。 \n, There s a very relaxed atmosphere in our office. \n 我们办公室的气氛非常轻松。 \n, There has been an atmosphere of gloom in the factory since it was announced that it would be closing. \n 自从宣布工厂要关闭的消息后，厂子就笼罩在一片沮丧的气氛中。 \n, You want a restaurant that serves good food but has a little atmosphere too. \n 谁都想去家饭菜可口又有点情调的饭店吃饭。 \n, He put on some soft music and turned the lights down in order to give the room a little more atmosphere. \n 为了使房间更富情调，他放起了轻柔的音乐，调暗了灯光。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukasu/ukasund024.mp3'),('attorney','律师','uk :əˈtɜː.ni, us :əˈtɝː.ni','[a defense attorney \n 辩护律师 \n, an attorney for the plaintiff \n 原告律师 \n, a civil/criminal attorney \n 民事／刑事律师 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukatt/ukatten010.mp3'),('atypical','非典型的；异常的；不同寻常的','uk :ˌeɪˈtɪp.ɪ.kəl, us :ˌeɪˈtɪp.ɪ.kəl','[The sociable behaviour of lions is considered atypical of the cat family. \n 狮子的群居习性被认为是猫科动物中的特例。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukatt/ukatten024.mp3'),('auntie','姑母；姨母；婶婶；伯母；舅母（同 aunt）阿姨（对女性长辈的通称）','uk :ˈɑːn.ti, us :ˈæn.t̬i','[My auntie and uncle are coming to visit. \n 我舅舅舅妈将来看我。 \n, [ as form of address ] \n Thank you for the present, Auntie Louise. \n 路易丝阿姨，谢谢您的礼物。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaud/ukaudac024.mp3'),('aura','气氛，氛围；气息（一些人声称在人或动物身体周围看到的）光环，光轮','uk :ˈɔː.rə, us :ˈɔːr.ə','[The woods have an aura of mystery. \n 这片树林透着神秘的气息。 \n, There s an aura of sadness about him. \n 他看上去一副悲伤的样子。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaud/ukaudac027.mp3'),('autistic','自闭症','uk :ɔːˈtɪs.tɪk, us :ɑːˈtɪs.tɪk','[ne child in 5,000 is autistic.\n, The story is told from the viewpoint of an autistic child.\n, She was diagnosed as autistic at 18 months.\n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukautis002.mp3'),('automate','使自动化','uk :ˈɔː.tə.meɪt, us :ˈɑː.t̬ə-','[Massive investment is needed to automate the production process. \n 要实现生产过程的自动化需要大量的投资。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukautis021.mp3'),('autonomy','自治，自治权自主，自主权','uk :ɔːˈtɒn.ə.mi, us :ɑːˈtɑː.nə.mi','[Demonstrators demanded immediate autonomy for their region. \n 游行示威者要求立即实现该地区的自治。 \n, The universities want to preserve their autonomy from central government. \n 大学都希望维护其自主办学权，不受中央政府的控制。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukauton002.mp3'),('averse','反对的；嫌恶的；不愿意的','uk :əˈvɜːs, us :əˈvɝːs','[Few people are averse to the idea of a free holiday. \n 几乎没有人会反对免费假期这个主意。 \n, I\'m not averse to (= I like) the occasional glass of champagne myself. \n 我乐得偶尔自己来杯香槟酒。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukauton027.mp3'),('avert','防止，避免转移（目光、想法等）；把…转（向别处）','uk :əˈvɜːt, us :əˈvɝːt',NULL,'2020-02-13',5,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukauton029.mp3'),('avocado','鳄梨','uk :ˌæv.əˈkɑː.dəʊ, us :ˌæv.əˈkɑː.doʊ','[]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld00050.mp3'),('awareness','意识','uk :əˈweə.nəs, us :əˈwer.nəs','[Public awareness of the problem will make politicians take it seriously. \n 一旦公众意识到这个问题，政客们就会严肃对待它了。 \n, Environmental awareness has increased dramatically over the past decade. \n 在过去的10年中，环保意识明显增强。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukavi/ukaviat026.mp3'),('awkward','难用的；棘手的；难处理的，难对付的令人尴尬的；使人难堪的尴尬的；局促不安的；为难的难相处的；不合作的；故意为难的笨拙的；别扭的；不灵活的；难看的','uk :ˈɔː.kwəd, us :ˈɑː.kwɚd','[It s an awkward corner, so take it slowly. \n 这个转弯不好过，开慢点儿。 \n, Some of the questions were rather awkward. \n 有些问题很难回答。 \n, It was an awkward ascent, but we reached the top eventually. \n 那段上坡路很难走，但最后我们还是爬到了山顶。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n My car s quite awkward to drive. \n 我的车很难开。 \n, He s an awkward customer (= a difficult person to deal with). \n 他是个很难应付的顾客。 \n, an awkward position/situation \n 令人尴尬的位置／局面 \n, There followed an awkward silence while we all tried to think of something to say. \n 然后是一段令人尴尬的沉默，我们都绞尽脑汁地想说点儿什么。 \n, They d chosen an awkward time to call as I d just got into the bath. \n 他们偏偏在我刚开始洗澡的时候来电话，真不是时候。 \n, The police asked some awkward questions about where the money had come from. \n 警方围绕钱的来源问了一些让人很难作答的问题。 \n, I always feel awkward when I m with Chris - he s so difficult to talk to. \n 我跟克里斯在一起总感到别扭——与他这人交谈太费劲儿。 \n, He seemed a little awkward when I first met him. \n 我第一次见他的时候，他有点儿放不开。 \n, Just stop being so awkward and help me push the car, will you! \n 别再跟我闹别扭了，快帮我推推车，好不好！ \n, His movements were slow and awkward. \n 他的动作迟缓笨拙。 \n]\n','2020-01-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukawe/ukawein010.mp3'),('backstab','背刺','null','null\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'null'),('backstop','（英国圆场棒球运动中的）接手（棒球）接手（catcher的非正式说法）（棒球场上的）挡球网','uk :ˈbæk.stɒp, us :ˈbæk.stɑːp',NULL,'2020-01-20',3,5,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbac/ukbackc030.mp3'),('bandit','土匪；盗贼；暴徒','uk :ˈbæn.dɪt, us :ˈbæn.dɪt','[]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbal/ukballs027.mp3'),('banter','开玩笑，逗乐（善意地）取笑，逗弄','uk :ˈbæn.tər, us :ˈbæn.t̬ɚ','[He considered himself a master of witty banter. \n 他认为自己是风趣幽默的玩笑大王。 \n, He stood around bantering with his colleagues. \n 他转来转去，与同事们打趣逗乐。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukban/ukbanqu005.mp3'),('barrage','掩护炮火，阻击火网连珠炮一样的（投诉、批评或质问），接二连三的…堰；拦河坝；拦潮坝','uk :ˈbær.ɑːʒ, us :bəˈrɑːʒ','[an artillery barrage \n 炮火掩护 \n, The TV station has received a barrage of complaints about the amount of violence in the series. \n 电视台接到了一连串的投诉，批评电视剧中的暴力镜头太多。 \n, He faced a barrage of questions over his handling of the problem. \n 就该问题的处理方式，他受到了接二连三的质问。 \n, The proposed tidal barrage would generate enough electricity to supply 80,000 homes. \n 提议修筑的拦潮坝发电量将足够8万户家庭使用。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbaroq007.mp3'),('barrel','桶桶（一桶石油相当于159升）枪管飞驰','uk :ˈbær.əl, us :ˈber.əl','[They drank a whole barrel of beer (= the contents of a barrel) at the party. \n 聚会上他们喝了整整一桶啤酒。 \n, We were barrelling along the autobahn at 180 kph. \n 我们以每小时180公里的速度在高速路上飞驰。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbaroq009.mp3'),('bash','猛撞；猛击严厉批评，猛烈抨击聚会猛击；痛打试试看','uk :bæʃ, us :bæʃ','[He bashed his arm against a shelf. \n 他的胳膊猛地撞在了架子上。 \n, K \n I could hear her bashing away on the computer (= hitting the keys loudly). \n 我能听见她重重地敲击计算机键盘的声音。 \n, He kept bashing local government officials. \n 他不停地抨击当地政府官员。 \n, He had a big bash for his 18th birthday. \n 他举办了盛大的聚会庆祝自己的18岁生日。 \n, a bash on the head \n 猛击头部 \n, I ve never been skiing before, but I m prepared to have a bash (at it). \n 我以前从来没有滑过雪，但是我准备试试。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbaroq029.mp3'),('bastion','堡垒棱堡（城堡和堡垒的突出部分）','uk :ˈbæs.ti.ən, us :ˈbæs.ti.ən','[British public schools are regarded as one of the last bastions of upper-class privilege. \n 英国公学被视为上流阶级特权的最后堡垒之一。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbas/ukbashf029.mp3'),('batter','连续猛打（尤指妇女、儿童）（用面粉、鸡蛋和牛奶调成的）面糊（棒球等的）击球员','uk :ˈbæt.ər, us :ˈbæt̬.ɚ',NULL,'2020-02-13',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbat/ukbatch021.mp3'),('beam','光线；光束；光柱（定向发出的）射束，粒子流（尤指支撑建筑物或其他结构的）梁，桁架，栋梁（女子体操运动中的）平衡木高兴的微笑，眉开眼笑辐射；发光；闪光；发射电波；播送','uk :biːm, us :biːm','[We could just pick out the trail in the weak beam of the flashlight. \n 我们借着手电筒微弱的光仅能勉强认清路。 \n, The rabbit stopped, mesmerized by the beam of the car s headlights. \n 兔子被汽车前灯射出的光束迷住了眼，停了下来。 \n, a laser beam \n 激光束 \n, an electron beam \n 电子波 \n, The sitting room had exposed wooden beams. \n 客厅顶上有裸露的木梁。 \n, She beamed with delight/pleasure at his remarks. \n 听完他的话她高兴得眉开眼笑。 \n, The child beamed at his teacher as he received the award. \n 那个孩子在领奖时对他的老师报以微笑。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  I m so pleased to see you,  he beamed (= said as he smiled). \n “见到你很高兴，”他微笑着说。 \n, The sun beamed (= shone brightly) down on the boat as it drifted along. \n 阳光照在缓缓漂动的船上。 \n, The concert was beamed (= broadcast) by satellite all over the world. \n 音乐会经卫星播送到世界各地。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbat/ukbattl030.mp3'),('beckon',':ˈbek.ən,','uk','[The customs official beckoned the woman to his counter. \n 海关官员示意那个妇女到他桌前来。 \n, \"Hey you!\" she called, beckoning me over with her finger. \n “嘿，叫你呢！”她喊道，并用手指示意我过去。 \n, He beckoned to me, as if he wanted to speak to me. \n 他给我打手势，好像是要跟我说什么。 \n, For many young people, the bright lights of the city beckon, though a lot of them end up sleeping on the streets. \n 城市璀璨的灯火吸引了许多年轻人，然而其中许多人却最终落得露宿街头。 \n, She\'s an excellent student, for whom a wonderful future beckons. \n 她是个优秀的学生，美妙的前程向她召唤。 \n]','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'null'),('belie','给人以假象；掩饰（感情等）','uk :bɪˈlaɪ, us :bɪˈlaɪ','[Her calm face belied the terror she was feeling. \n 她平静的表情掩盖了内心的恐惧。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbel/ukbelda006.mp3'),('bent','（bent 的过去式及过去分词）弯曲的；不直的；不平的（尤指当权者）不诚实的（尤指男性）同性恋的天赋','uk :bent, us :bent',NULL,'2020-02-14',3,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukben/ukbenev012.mp3'),('bestow','赠予；给予','uk :bɪˈstəʊ, us :bɪˈstoʊ','[The George Cross is a decoration that is bestowed upon/on British civilians for acts of great bravery. \n 乔治十字勋章是为了表彰英国平民的英勇行为而颁发的。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbes/ukbesid017.mp3'),('beyond','更远；远于（范围）超出…；超过…太…而难以置信（无法修复，难以辨认等）（案件或罪行）证据确凿的，确实的令…无法理解；非…所能及','uk :biˈjɒnd, us :biˈjɑːnd','[In the distance, beyond the river, was a small town. \n 在河对岸的远处有一座小镇。 \n, From the top of the hill we could see our house and the woods beyond. \n 站在这个小山顶，能看到我们的房子和远处的森林。 \n, Few people live beyond the age of a hundred. \n 很少有人活过100岁。 \n, We cannot allow the work to continue beyond the end of the year. \n 我们不能允许这项工作延续到下一年。 \n, I ve got nothing to tell you beyond (= in addition to) what I told you earlier. \n 除了先前告诉你的以外，我没有别的可说了。 \n, The repercussions will be felt throughout the industry and beyond (= in other areas). \n 影响将波及整个产业及其他领域。 \n, Tonight s performance has been cancelled due to circumstances beyond our control (= events that we are unable to deal with). \n 由于出现了一些我们无法控制的情况，今晚的演出取消了。 \n, She has always lived beyond her means (= spent more than she has earned). \n 她生活总是入不敷出。 \n, His thoughtlessness is beyond belief. \n 他的轻率令人不可思议。 \n, He survived the accident, but his car was damaged beyond repair. \n 在车祸中他幸存了下来，但他的车却彻底报废了。 \n, Her guilt was established beyond reasonable doubt. \n 她的罪行确凿无疑。 \n, Physics is completely beyond me. \n 恐怕我根本就学不会物理。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbet/ukbetid029.mp3'),('bilateral','双边的，双方的','uk :ˌbaɪˈlæt.ər.əl, us :ˌbaɪˈlæt̬.ɚ.əl','[France and Germany have signed a bilateral agreement to help prevent drug smuggling. \n 法国和德国已经签署了一项双边协定以防止毒品走私。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbif/ukbiff_025.mp3'),('bluff','虚张声势；吓唬蒙混过关虚张声势；吓唬悬崖，峭壁；陡岸过分直率的；过于直接的','uk :blʌf, us :blʌf','[Is he going to jump or is he only bluffing? \n 他是真要跳还是只是吓唬人？ \n, Tony seems to know a lot about music, but sometimes I think he s only bluffing. \n 托尼似乎对音乐很了解，但有时我觉得他只是在装样子。 \n, She bluffed the doorman into thinking that she was a reporter. \n 她装模作样让门卫以为她是记者。 \n, How did Mina manage to bluff her way into that job? \n 米娜究竟是怎样蒙混过关得到那份工作的？ \n, He s one of those people who is very good at bluffing their way out of trouble. \n 他属于那种善于蒙混过关摆脱麻烦的人。 \n, When she said she was leaving him, he thought it was only a bluff. \n 当她说要离开他时，他以为那只是吓唬他。 \n, Despite her bluff manner, she s actually a very kind woman. \n 尽管有点过于直率，但她实际上是个很善良的女人。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukblo/ukblowg025.mp3'),('blurb','简介；推荐语','uk :blɜːb, us :blɝːb','[The blurb on the back of the book says that it  will touch your heart . \n 封底上的简介称此书“将触动你的内心”。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukblu/ukblunt004.mp3'),('boar','种猪；野猪','uk :bɔːr, us :bɔːr','[]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukblu/ukblunt020.mp3'),('boast','自吹自擂，吹嘘，夸耀拥有（值得自豪的东西）夸耀','uk :bəʊst, us :boʊst','[He didn t talk about his exam results in case people thought he was boasting. \n 他没有谈论自己的考试成绩，以免让别人以为他在自我吹嘘。 \n, Parents enjoy boasting about their children s achievements. \n 父母喜欢夸耀子女所取得的成绩。 \n, [ + that ] \n They boasted that they had never lost a single game. \n 他们夸口说从来没有输过一场比赛。 \n, Ireland boasts beautiful beaches, great restaurants, and friendly locals. \n 爱尔兰拥有美丽的海滩、很棒的餐馆和友好的当地人。 \n, [ + that ] \n It is her proud boast that she has never missed a single episode of the show. \n 她骄傲地夸口说这个肥皂剧她从未漏看过一集。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukblu/ukblunt027.mp3'),('boll-weevil','象鼻象鼻虫','Xiàng bí xiàng bí chóng','\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=boll-weevil&tl=ja&tk=378164.258368&client=webapp&prev=input'),('bony','瘦削的；皮包骨头的骨头的；骨制的','uk :ˈbəʊ.ni, us :ˈboʊ.ni','[long bony fingers \n 细长瘦削的手指 \n, bony prominences \n 骨头突出处 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbon/ukbonfi014.mp3'),('bookcase','书架；书橱','uk :ˈbʊk.keɪs, us :ˈbʊk.keɪs','[]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukboo/ukbookb005.mp3'),('bootlegging','非法制造（或贩卖）的；盗版的（裤子）靴形裁剪的，膝下稍加宽的靴形裁剪的裤子非法制造（或复制、贩卖）','uk :ˈbuːt.leɡ, us :ˈbuːt.leɡ','[bootleg CDs/liquor \n 盗版光盘／私酒 \n, bootleg jeans \n 靴形裁剪的牛仔裤 \n, a pair of bootlegs \n 一条靴形裁剪的裤子 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukboo/ukboomi013.mp3'),('booze','酒喝酒','uk :buːz, us :buːz','[The party s at Kate s on Friday night - bring some booze. \n 聚会周五晚上在凯特家举行——带些酒来。 \n, Have you been out boozing again? \n 你是不是又出去喝酒了？ \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukboo/ukboomi016.mp3'),('bosom','（女人的）乳房前胸；（尤指）胸怀，内心（女人）乳房丰满的','uk :ˈbʊz.əm, us :ˈbʊz.əm','[a large/ample bosom \n 大／丰满的乳房 \n, She held him tightly to her bosom. \n 她把他紧紧地拥在胸前。 \n, A dark jealousy stirred in his bosom. \n 他内心生出一阵恶毒的嫉妒。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbor/ukborin014.mp3'),('botanical','植物（学）的；和植物（学）有关的','uk :bəˈtæn.ɪ.kəl, us :bəˈtæn.ɪ.kəl','[a botanical print \n 植物图片 \n, botanical/botanic gardens \n 植物园 \n, Several new botanical species have been discovered in the last year. \n 过去的一年里发现了几种新的植物。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbor/ukborin022.mp3'),('bourgeois','中产阶级的；追求物质享受的；平庸粗俗的','uk :ˈbɔːʒ.wɑː, us :ˈbʊrʒ.wɑː',NULL,'2019-12-27',1,3,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbou/ukbount005.mp3'),('bovine','牛的；牛类动物的迟钝的；蠢笨的','uk :ˈbəʊ.vaɪn, us :ˈboʊ.vaɪn','[a bovine virus \n 牛（痘）病毒 \n, He had a gentle, slightly bovine expression. \n 他表情温和，略显木讷。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbou/ukbount009.mp3'),('bowl','碗；钵（物体的）碗状部分圆形运动场；圆形露天剧场草地滚木球戏（草地滚木球戏中所用的）木球；（保龄球运动中所用的）圆球（美国）美式橄榄球季后赛（在游戏中）滚动球把（球）投给击球员，投（球）','uk :bəʊl, us :boʊl','[a soup/cereal/salad/sugar bowl \n 汤碗／麦片粥碗／色拉钵／糖钵 \n, a bowl of soup/rice/porridge \n 一碗汤／米饭／粥 \n, She eats a bowl (= the contents of a bowl) of cereal every morning. \n 她每天早上吃一碗麦片粥。 \n, Sift the flour and baking powder into a mixing bowl. \n 将面粉和发酵粉筛进搅拌钵里。 \n, K \n Just put the dirty dishes in the washing-up bowl, and I ll do them later. \n 将脏碟子放进洗碗盆好了，我一会儿再洗。 \n, The toilet bowl was cracked and stained, and the walls were covered in mould. \n 抽水马桶破裂了，污迹斑斑，四周墙上到处都是霉点。 \n, the Hollywood Bowl \n 好莱坞露天剧场 \n, Bowls is one of the most popular sports in the UK . \n 草地滚球是英国最流行的运动之一。 \n, Pringle was tired after bowling for an hour. \n 投了一小时球后普林格尔累了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukboe/ukboer_020.mp3'),('brawl','（乱哄哄的）斗殴，闹事斗殴，大打出手','uk :brɔːl, us :brɑːl','[a drunken brawl \n 醉酒斗殴 \n, The young men had nothing better to do than brawl in the streets. \n 这些年轻人除了在大街上打架斗殴做不出什么好事。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbra/ukbraw_002.mp3'),('breach','破坏，违犯；违反，不履行扰乱治安（行为）违反（法律或规章）（攻击墙或防御工事时打出的）缺口破坏，违犯；违反，不履行（尤指为从背后突袭）在…上打开缺口','uk :briːtʃ, us :briːtʃ','[They felt that our discussions with other companies constituted a breach of/in our agreement. \n 他们认为我们与别的公司谈判违反了我们之间的协定。 \n, He was sued for breach of contract. \n 他因为违反合同而被起诉。 \n, There have been serious security breaches (= breaks in our security system). \n 安全体系出了大问题。 \n, The theatre was in breach of the safety laws for having no fire doors. \n 由于没有消防门，这家剧院违反了安全法规。 \n, A cannon ball had made a breach in their castle walls. \n 一颗炮弹在他们城堡的墙上打出了一个缺口。 \n, They breached the agreement they had made with their employer. \n 他们违反了曾与雇主达成的协议。 \n, Their defences were easily breached. \n 他们的防线轻而易举就被突破了。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbra/ukbraw_013.mp3'),('brew','酿（啤酒）泡（茶）；煮（咖啡）；（茶）冲泡；（咖啡）煮（坏事或暴风雨）即将来临，酝酿（尤指某地或某个时间酿造的）啤酒一杯茶；一份啤酒混合物','uk :bruː, us :bruː','[[ + two objects ] \n He brewed us some coffee./He brewed some coffee for us. \n 他给我们煮了些咖啡。 \n, It was too quiet - I felt that trouble was brewing. \n 太安静了——我觉得要出事了。 \n, A storm was brewing in the distance. \n 远处一场暴风雨即将来临。 \n, Make us a brew, Bren. \n 布伦，给我们泡杯茶吧。 \n, They gave her a strange brew to drink. \n 他们让她喝一种奇怪的混合饮料。 \n, War, with its fear, its deprivation, its excitement and violence makes for a very heady brew (= powerful combination). \n 战争是恐惧、剥夺、刺激和暴力诸因素的混合体，给人以强烈震撼。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbre/ukbrew_001.mp3'),('briefly','短暂地；简短地简言之，一言以蔽之','uk :ˈbriːf.li, us :ˈbriːf.li','[We chatted briefly about the weather. \n 我们聊了几句天气。 \n, Briefly, the company needs to cut its expenditure. \n 简言之，公司需要缩减开支。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbre/ukbrew_028.mp3'),('bronchiolitis','毛细支气管炎','bräŋ-kē-ō-ˈlī-təs','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('bronchitis','支气管炎','uk :brɒŋˈkaɪ.tɪs, us :brɑːŋˈkaɪ.t̬əs','[]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukad5/ukad5080.mp3'),('bronze','青铜古铜色，青铜色青铜塑像铜牌古铜色的，青铜色的','uk :brɒnz, us :brɑːnz','[The church bells are made of bronze. \n 教堂大钟是青铜制成的。 \n, He got a bronze in the high jump. \n 他跳高得了铜牌。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbro/ukbroke014.mp3'),('brute','残忍的人（尤指大个的）野兽；牲畜强力，极大的力量','uk :bruːt, us :bruːt','[[ as form of address ] \n Take your hands off me, you brute! \n 把手松开，你这畜牲！ \n, Your dog s an ugly brute, isn t it? \n 你那条狗是个丑陋的家伙，对吧？ \n, The oldest elephant was lame, poor brute. \n 那头最老的大象腿跛了，可怜的家伙。 \n, In the end she used brute force to push him out. \n 最后她使出吃奶的力气将他推了出去。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbro/ukbroug017.mp3'),('bucket','（有提梁的）桶','uk :ˈbʌk.ɪt, us :ˈbʌk.ɪt','[Armed with a bucket and a mop, I started washing the floor. \n 提着桶和拖把，我开始拖地板。 \n, K \n I took my two-year-old nephew down to the beach with his bucket and spade. \n 我带两岁的小外甥去海滩，拿着他的小桶和铲子。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbru/ukbrusq022.mp3'),('burglarize','入室盗窃','uk :ˈbɜː.ɡəl, us :ˈbɝː.ɡəl','[When they got back from their holiday they found that their home had been burgled. \n 他们度假回来时发现家中被盗了。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbun/ukbunny025.mp3'),('bust','（女子的）胸部，胸围半身像逮捕；搜捕击碎；打破；弄坏逮捕；突击搜查（建筑物等）并逮捕疑犯坏的，损坏的破产','uk :bʌst, us :bʌst','[I couldn t find any blouses in my bust size. \n 我找不到适合我胸围的衬衫。 \n, There was a bust of Mahler on his desk. \n 他书桌上有一尊马勒的半身像。 \n, In their latest drugs bust police entered a warehouse where cocaine dealers were meeting. \n 在最近的毒品搜捕行动中，警方突袭了一个可卡因毒贩正在进行交易的仓库。 \n, Oh no! I bust his MP3 player. \n 噢，不好！我弄坏了他的MP3播放机。 \n, The police busted him because they think he s involved with a terrorist group. \n 警方认为他与恐怖团伙有牵连而逮捕了他。 \n, I think my watch is bust. \n 我想我的表坏了。 \n, More than 20 companies in the district went bust during the last three months. \n 过去的3个月里这一地区有超过20家公司破产。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbus/ukbushr012.mp3'),('cabbie','出租车司机，计程车司机','uk :ˈkæb.i, us :ˈkæb.i','[]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbys/ukbysta013.mp3'),('cabinet','内阁贮藏柜；陈列柜；橱柜','uk :ˈkæb.ɪ.nət, us :ˈkæb.ən.ət','[The Cabinet meet/meets every Thursday. \n 内阁成员每周四开会。 \n, The President is completing the selection of his new Cabinet. \n 首相已宣布新内阁名单。 \n, a cabinet post \n 内阁大臣 \n, K \n a cabinet reshuffle (= changes in the Cabinet). \n 内阁改组 \n, K \n a cabinet minister \n 内阁部长 \n, Valuable pieces of china were on display in a glass-fronted cabinet. \n 贵重瓷器陈列在正面是玻璃的柜子里。 \n, a bathroom/filing cabinet \n 浴室／文件柜 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbys/ukbysta017.mp3'),('cache','隐藏物；隐藏所（计算机的）高速缓冲存储器','uk :kæʃ, us :kæʃ','[an arms cache \n 武器隐藏地 \n, a cache of explosives/weapons/drugs \n 一批隐藏的炸药／武器／毒品 \n, 256 Kb secondary cache \n 256千字节二级高速缓冲存储器 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbys/ukbysta022.mp3'),('campus','（大学）校园，校区','uk :ˈkæm.pəs, us :ˈkæm.pəs','[There s accommodation for about five hundred students on campus. \n 校区内可供约500名学生住宿。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcam/ukcambo029.mp3'),('capacity','容积，容量；生产能力；（尤指某人或某组织的）办事能力职位；工作；角色','uk :kəˈpæs.ə.ti, us :kəˈpæs.ə.t̬i','[The stadium has a seating capacity of 50,000. \n 这个体育场能容纳5万人。 \n, The game was watched by a capacity crowd/audience of 50,000 (= the place was completely full). \n 比赛场座无虚席，5万观众观看了比赛。 \n, She has a great capacity for hard work. \n 她特别能吃苦耐劳。 \n, The purchase of 500 tanks is part of a strategy to increase military capacity by 25 percent over the next five years. \n 购买500辆坦克是在今后5年里将军事力量增加25%的战略计划的一部分。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n It seems to be beyond his capacity to (= he seems to be unable to) follow simple instructions. \n 他好像连简单的指令也听不懂。 \n, Do you think it s within his capacity to (= do you think he ll be able to) do the job without making a mess of it? \n 你认为他有能力完成这项工作而不把它搞砸吗？ \n, The generators each have a capacity of (= can produce) 1,000 kilowatts. \n 每台发电机都有1000千瓦的发电能力。 \n, The larger cars have bigger capacity engines (= the engines are bigger and more powerful). \n 大轿车引擎功率也比较大。 \n, All our factories are working at (full) capacity (= are producing goods as fast as possible). \n 我们所有的工厂都在满负荷运行。 \n, We are running below capacity (= not producing as many goods as we are able to) because of cancelled orders. \n 因为订单取消，我们的工厂开工不足。 \n, He suffered a stroke in 2008, which left him unable to speak, but his mental capacity (= his ability to think and remember) wasn t affected. \n 2008年他得了中风，不能说话了，但是思维能力没有受影响。 \n, She guides tourists at the Martin Luther King Jr. Birth Home in her capacity as a National Park Service ranger. \n 作为国家公园管理局的管理员，她陪同游客参观马丁·路德·金的出生地。 \n, She was speaking in her capacity as a novelist, rather than as a television presenter. \n 她是作为小说家而不是电视节目主持人在发言。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcan/ukcant_021.mp3'),('capital market','资本市场','Zīběn shìchǎng','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=capital market&tl=ja&tk=508598.128706&client=webapp&prev=input'),('capricious','反复无常的','uk :kəˈprɪʃ.əs, us :kəˈprɪʃ.əs','[a capricious child \n 任性的小孩 \n, He was a cruel and capricious tyrant. \n 他是个残忍而又反复无常的暴君。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcap/ukcapit010.mp3'),('caption','（图书、杂志或报纸图片的）说明文字图片说明','uk :ˈkæp.ʃən, us :ˈkæp.ʃən','[The picture was captioned  Catherine Deneuve in Belle du Jour . \n 照片说明写道“凯瑟琳·德纳芙在《白日美人》中”。 \n, a captioned photograph \n 一幅带有文字说明的照片 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcap/ukcapit020.mp3'),('cardinal','（罗马天主教会的）红衣主教，枢机主教基数红衣凤头鸟（见于北美，雄鸟有鲜红色的羽毛）极重要的；基本的；主要的','uk :ˈkɑː.dɪ.nəl, us :ˈkɑːr.dɪ.nəl','[Cardinals elect and advise the Pope. \n 红衣主教们推选教皇并担当教皇的顾问。 \n, a cardinal rule/error/sin \n 基本规则／根本错误／严重错误 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcar/ukcarap027.mp3'),('carnage','屠杀','Túshā','\n','2019-10-28',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=carnage &tl=ja&tk=460853.80961&client=webapp&prev=input'),('carve','（尤指在石头或木头上）雕刻把（熟肉）切成小片','uk :kɑːv, us :kɑːrv','[This totem pole is carved from/out of a single tree trunk. \n 这根图腾柱是由一整根树干雕刻而成的。 \n, He carved her name on a tree. \n 他将她的名字刻在了树上。 \n, Some of the tunnels in the cliff are natural, some were carved out (= cut into the rock) by soldiers for defensive purposes. \n 峭壁中的一些隧道是天然形成的，一些是士兵们在石头上开凿出来用于防御的。 \n, Would you like me to carve (the chicken)? \n 您要我（把鸡肉）切成小块吗？ \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcal/ukcalip022.mp3'),('catastrophic','严重的破坏','uk :ˌkæt.əˈstrɒf.ɪk, us :ˌkæt̬.əˈstrɑː.fɪk','[n unchecked increase in the use of fossil fuels could have catastrophic results for the planet.\n, A catastrophic storm made landfall on US soil.\n, he had to put her catastrophic Olympic performance out of her mind.\n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcas/ukcaste026.mp3'),('cathartic','解气','uk :kəˈθɑː.tɪk, us :kəˈθɑːr.tɪk','[ cathartic experience\n, I find it very cathartic to dance. \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcat/ukcatch021.mp3'),('cattle','牛','uk :ˈkæt.əl, us :ˈkæt̬.əl','[beef/dairy cattle \n 肉／奶牛 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcat/ukcatsu005.mp3'),('channel','电视台；电视频道（水或其他液体流通的）管道，渠道；航道英吉利海峡（交流的）途径，渠道（提供产品、信息等的）渠道，方法（机场或港口检查旅客行李的）通道引导；把…导入，将…引入模仿（某人的举止等）','uk :ˈtʃæn.əl, us :ˈtʃæn.əl','[a cable/terrestrial/satellite channel \n 有线／地面／卫星频道 \n, a music/movie/news/shopping/sports channel \n 音乐／电影／新闻／购物／体育频道 \n, the news on Channel 4 \n 四频道的新闻 \n, She switched/turned to another channel to watch football. \n 她换到另一个频道看足球赛。 \n, There are drainage/irrigation channels all over this flat agricultural land. \n 在这片平坦的农田上遍布着排水／灌溉渠。 \n, The boats all have to pass through this narrow channel. \n 所有船只都必须通过这条狭窄的航道。 \n, We re going to have a day-trip across the Channel. \n 我们将进行一次横渡英吉利海峡的一日游。 \n, We took the car to France overnight on a (cross-)channel ferry. \n 我们用横渡英吉利海峡的渡船把汽车运到了法国。 \n, We must open the channels of communication between the two countries. \n 我们必须打开两国之间的交流渠道。 \n, The government pursued every diplomatic/official channel to free the hostages. \n 政府寻求一切外交／官方渠道以使人质获释。 \n, Complaints should be made through the proper/usual channels. \n 应当通过适当的／正常的渠道进行投诉。 \n, The insurer sells its products through a variety of distribution channels, including banks. \n 保险公司通过包括银行在内的各种渠道销售其产品。 \n, If you have nothing to declare, go through the green channel. \n 如果你没有东西要申报，就走绿色通道。 \n, Goods to declare - use the red channel. \n 有商品要报税——走红色通道。 \n, Ditches were constructed to channel water away from the buildings. \n 修造了沟渠把水引离建筑物。 \n, If she could only channel all that energy into something useful. \n 要是她能把那些精力都倾注到有用的事情上就好了。 \n, A lot of money has been channelled into research in that particular field. \n 大笔经费投入到了那个领域的研究中。 \n, The band were dressed in 1960s outfits and seemed to be channelling the Beatles. \n 这支乐队身着60年代的服装，似乎是在模仿甲壳虫乐队。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukchamo023.mp3'),('characteristic','特色，特点，特征特有的，典型的','uk :ˌkær.ək.təˈrɪs.tɪk, us :ˌker.ək.təˈrɪs.tɪk','[Unfortunately a big nose is a family characteristic. \n 不幸的是，大鼻子是家族特征。 \n, Sentimentality seems a characteristic of all the writers of that period. \n 多愁善感似乎是那个时期所有作家的特征。 \n, The male bird displays (= has) several characteristics which distinguish him from the female. \n 雄鸟有几个有别于雌鸟的特征。 \n, With the hospitality so characteristic of these people, they opened their house to over 50 guests. \n 这些人生性好客，他们敞开家门接待了五十多位客人。 \n, She behaved with characteristic dignity. \n 她表现出自己特有的尊严。 \n, The creamy richness is characteristic of the cheese from this region. \n 奶味浓郁是该地区出产的奶酪的特色。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukchaot022.mp3'),('charity','慈善事业；慈善组织，慈善机构仁慈，宽容，友善','uk :ˈtʃær.ə.ti, us :ˈtʃer.ə.t̬i','[She does a lot of work for charity. \n 她做了很多慈善工作。 \n, People tend to give to (= give money to) charity at Christmas time. \n 人们往往在圣诞节向慈善组织捐钱。 \n, Proceeds from the sale of these cards will go to (= be given to) local charities. \n 卖这些贺卡所得的收益将捐献给地方慈善组织。 \n, UNICEF is an international charity. \n 联合国儿童基金会是国际性慈善组织。 \n, They did a charity performance on the first night, to raise money for AIDS research. \n 他们的首晚演出是慈善义演，为艾滋病研究募集资金。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukcharg012.mp3'),('chewing','咀嚼；嚼碎（尤指为品尝味道而）嚼，咬嚼，咀嚼咀嚼物（越嚼越软的）硬糖；口香糖','uk :tʃuː, us :tʃuː','[This meat is difficult to chew. \n 这肉很难嚼。 \n, You don t chew your food enough - that s why you get indigestion. \n 你没把食物嚼烂——这就是你消化不良的原因。 \n, Would you like some gum to chew? \n 你想吃口香糖吗？ \n, She gave the children some sweets to chew (on) during the long car journey. \n 在漫长的汽车旅行途中，她给了孩子们些糖果嚼着吃。 \n, She sat in the dentist s waiting room, nervously chewing (at) (= biting) her nails. \n 她坐在牙医的候诊室里，紧张地咬着指甲。 \n, dog chews \n 狗咬胶 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukche/ukchess007.mp3'),('chick','雏鸟，幼鸟；（尤指）小鸡（冒犯性用语）女孩；少女；小妞儿','uk :tʃɪk, us :tʃɪk','[]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukche/ukchess017.mp3'),('chlorine','氯，氯气','uk :ˈklɔː.riːn, us :ˈklɔːr.iːn','[The chlorine in the pool makes my eyes sore. \n 游泳池里的氯气刺得我眼睛发疼。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukchi/ukchirp021.mp3'),('chore','日常琐事；杂务；乏味的例行工作','uk :tʃɔːr, us :tʃɔːr','[I\'ll go shopping when I\'ve done my chores (= done the jobs in or around the house). \n 我把家务琐事干完后要去购物。 \n, I find writing reports a real chore (= very boring). \n 我觉得写报告真是件烦人的事。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcho/ukchora003.mp3'),('circumstance','条件，情况；情形，形势无法控制的因素；客观环境；命运经济状况','uk :ˈsɜː.kəm.stɑːns, us :ˈsɝː.kəm.stæns','[I think she coped very well under the circumstances. \n 我觉得在那种情况下她处理得很不错。 \n, Obviously we can\'t deal with the problem until we know all the circumstances. \n 显然，我们只有了解全部情况后才能处理这问题。 \n, She died in suspicious circumstances. \n 她死得很蹊跷。 \n, We oppose capital punishment in/under any circumstances. \n 无论在什么情况下，我们都不赞成死刑。 \n, Under no circumstances should you (= you should not) approach the man. \n 你无论如何都不应该联系那个男人。 \n, The meeting has been cancelled due to circumstances beyond our control. \n 会议因不可控情况的出现而被取消了。 \n, They were victims of circumstance. \n 他们是客观环境的牺牲品。 \n, We were obliged to go by force of circumstance. \n 形势所迫，我们不得不走。 \n, Grants are available depending on your circumstances. \n 视经济状况，符合条件可获得助学金。 \n, By now she was alone and living in reduced circumstances (= with little money). \n 现在她孤单一人，生活拮据。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcin/ukcinna026.mp3'),('cite','举例，引证引用，引述援引；传唤，传讯（军队中公开）嘉奖，表彰，表扬','uk :saɪt, us :saɪt','[She cited three reasons why people get into debt. \n 她举出了人们为何负债的3个原因。 \n, The company cited a 13 percent decline in new orders as evidence that overall demand for its products was falling. \n 公司举出新订单减少13%这一事实，以此来证明对其产品的总需求在下降。 \n, She cites both T.S. Eliot and Virginia Woolf in her article. \n 她在文章中引用了T.S.艾略特和弗吉尼娅•吴尔夫的作品。 \n, The lawyer cited two similar cases. \n 律师援引了两个类似的案例。 \n, He has been cited as the co-respondent in the divorce case. \n 他作为这起离婚案的共同被告被传讯。 \n, He was cited for bravery. \n 他因为勇敢而受到嘉奖。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcir/ukcirrh008.mp3'),('civil','文职的；民用的；平民的，国民的民事的有礼貌的；文明的；客气的','uk :ˈsɪv.əl, us :ˈsɪv.əl','[Helicopters are mainly used for military rather than civil use. \n 直升机主要用于军事而非民用。 \n, After ten years of military dictatorship, the country now has a civil government. \n 经历了10年军事专制统治后，该国现在有了一个文官政府。 \n, We weren t married in church, but we had a civil ceremony in a registry office. \n 我们没在教堂结婚，不过在婚姻登记处举行了个世俗仪式。 \n, The matter would be better dealt with in the civil court rather than by an expensive criminal proceeding. \n 这事最好在民事法庭处理，而不要进行昂贵的刑事诉讼。 \n, His manner was civil, though not particularly friendly. \n 他的态度很客气，尽管不是特别友好。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcir/ukcirrh021.mp3'),('classier','流行的；时髦的；豪华的','uk :ˈklɑː.si, us :ˈklæs.i','[That s one classy vehicle you ve got there. \n 你那辆车真是太气派了。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcla/ukclass004.mp3'),('clatter','（使）发出响亮的撞击声；（使）哐啷作响','uk :ˈklæt.ər, us :ˈklæt̬.ɚ','[Don t clatter the dishes - you ll wake the baby up. \n 别把碗碟碰得叮当响——会把宝宝吵醒的。 \n, He was clattering away at his keyboard. \n 他在键盘上咔嗒咔嗒打东西。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcla/ukclass005.mp3'),('clinical','门诊的，临床的冷漠的；无动于衷的；无感情的无特色的；冷冰冰的；朴素的','uk :ˈklɪn.ɪ.kəl, us :ˈklɪn.ɪ.kəl','[clinical tests/training \n 临床试验／实习 \n, the Department of Clinical Medicine \n 临床医学部 \n, Clinical trials of the new drug may take five years. \n 这种新药的临床试验可能需要5年时间。 \n, She seems to have a very clinical attitude towards her children. \n 她好像对子女们态度很冷漠。 \n, We were going to paint our kitchen white, but we decided that would look too clinical. \n 我们打算把厨房漆成白色，可是又觉得那样会看起来太冷冰冰了。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcli/ukclima018.mp3'),('clink','（使）发出叮当声，（使）叮当作响叮当声监狱，大牢','uk :klɪŋk, us :klɪŋk','[The ice clinked as she dropped it into the glass. \n 她把冰块丢入玻璃杯，冰块叮当作响。 \n, We all clinked our glasses together and drank to a happy new year. \n 我们大家一起碰杯，祝贺新年快乐。 \n, I could hear the clink of coins in his pocket. \n 我能听到他口袋里的硬币叮当作响。 \n, Everyone always said Joe would end up in (the) clink. \n 大家都说乔总有一天要坐牢。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcli/ukclima021.mp3'),('clown','丑角，小丑（常指故意）出洋相的人；愚蠢可笑的人扮小丑；出洋相；逗笑','uk :klaʊn, us :klaʊn','[Left alone, the class threw books, pulled faces, and generally clowned around. \n 由于没有人管，班上的学生扔书本，扮鬼脸，简直胡闹成一片。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukclo/ukclosu015.mp3'),('coffin','棺材；灵柩','uk :ˈkɒf.ɪn, us :ˈkɑː.fɪn','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcoe/ukcoedu014.mp3'),('coinage','货币系统，货币制度新造的词（语）；新词语的创造','uk :ˈkɔɪ.nɪdʒ, us :ˈkɔɪ.nɪdʒ','[decimal coinage \n 十进位币制 \n, The expression  boy band  is a 1990s coinage. \n boy band（男孩乐队）是20世纪90年代的新词语。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcoh/ukcohab016.mp3'),('colonist','殖民地居民；殖民地移民；殖民地开拓者','uk :ˈkɒl.ə.nist, us :ˈkɑː.lə.nist','[]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01677.mp3'),('colossal','巨大的，庞大的','uk :kəˈlɒs.əl, us :kəˈlɑː.səl','[In the centre of the hall stood a colossal wooden statue, decorated in ivory and gold. \n 大厅中央矗立着一尊用象牙和金子装饰的木质巨型雕像。 \n, They were asking a colossal amount of money for the house. \n 他们对这房子漫天要价。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcol/ukcolor003.mp3'),('commanding height','制高点','Zhǐlìng gāodù','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q= commanding height&tl=ja&tk=509866.127966&client=webapp&prev=input'),('commercial','商业的；商务的；贸易的（唱片、电影、书等）商业化的，以营利为目的的（产品）商品化的（广播或电视）商业性的，靠广告收入维持的（电视或广播里的）商业广告','uk :kəˈmɜː.ʃəl, us :kəˈmɝː.ʃəl','[a commercial organization/venture/success \n 商业组织／企业／成功 \n, commercial law \n 商法 \n, The commercial future of the company looks very promising. \n 这家公司的商业前景看起来非常光明。 \n, a commercial break \n 插播广告 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcomma024.mp3'),('commission','（正式地）安排…做，委托…做委任（或任命）…为军官（负责调查问题真相或原因的）委员会佣金；提成；回扣委托；请求犯罪军官的职务（或职权）','uk :kəˈmɪʃ.ən, us :kəˈmɪʃ.ən','[The newspaper commissioned a series of articles on the worst excesses of the fashion industry. \n 报社请人撰写了一系列针砭时装业极端倾向的文章。 \n, She\'s commissioned an artist to paint her portrait. \n 她请了一位艺术家为她画肖像。 \n, Grandfather was commissioned as Group Captain in the RAF just before the war. \n 就在战争爆发前夕祖父被任命为皇家空军上校。 \n, a commission on alcohol abuse/racial tension \n 酗酒问题／种族间紧张关系调查委员会 \n, The government has set up/established a commission to investigate the problem of inner city violence. \n 政府设立了专门委员会来调查市中心区的暴力问题。 \n, Is she paid a regular wage or is it on/by commission only? \n 她拿正式工资还是只拿提成？ \n, She gets a 15 percent commission on every machine she sells. \n 她每卖出一台机器就拿15%的提成。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n She\'s just got a commission to paint Sir Ellis Pike\'s wife. \n 她刚刚受托为埃利斯‧帕克爵士的夫人画像。 \n, Do you do/take commissions? \n 你接受委托吗？ \n, the commission of the crime/offence/murder \n 犯罪／犯法／犯杀人罪 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcommi006.mp3'),('commitment','忠诚；投入；奉献；承诺，保证，诺言必须做（或处理）的事情','uk :kəˈmɪt.mənt, us :kəˈmɪt.mənt','[Players must make a commitment to play for a full season. \n 队员必须保证参加整个赛季的比赛 \n, her commitment to left-wing politics/the cause of feminism/the company \n 她对左翼政治／女权主义事业／公司的奉献 \n, She is known chiefly for her commitment to nuclear disarmament. \n 她主要以全力支持核裁军运动而出名。 \n, I d like to thank the staff for having shown such commitment. \n 我要对全体员工作出的巨大奉献表示感谢。 \n, Try the product out in the comfort of your own home with absolutely no commitment to buy! \n 可在家随意试用本产品且根本无须承诺购买！ \n, family/work commitments \n 家庭义务／工作任务 \n, I ve got too many commitments at the moment to do an evening class. \n 我眼下要做的事情太多，没时间晚上上课。 \n, Children are such a commitment. \n 照管孩子真费精力。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcommi010.mp3'),('companion','同伴；伙伴；伴侣陪护（旧时受雇陪伴老太太或女性病人旅行的年轻女子）（成对物件中的）一件（用于书名）指南，手册','uk :kəmˈpæn.jən, us :kəmˈpæn.jən','[The dog has been her constant companion these past ten years. \n 在过去的这10年里，这条狗一直与她形影不离。 \n, a travelling companion \n 旅伴 \n, I ve still got one of the candlesticks but I ve lost its companion. \n 我还拥有一个烛台，却把配对的另一个给弄丢了。 \n, the Music Lover s Companion \n 《音乐爱好者指南》 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcommu022.mp3'),('comparison','比较，对照，对比相提并论，认为…和…相似','uk :kəmˈpær.ɪ.sən, us :kəmˈper.ɪ.sən','[They made a comparison of different countries  eating habits. \n 他们对不同国家的饮食习惯作了一番比较。 \n, By/In comparison with the French, the British eat far less fish. \n 与法国人相比，英国人吃鱼要少得多。 \n, She drew a comparison between life in the army and life in prison. \n 她把军队生活比作坐牢。 \n, To my mind there s no comparison between the two restaurants (= one is much better than the other). \n 在我心目中，这两家饭店根本不能相比。 \n, He s a good writer but he doesn t bear/stand comparison with Shakespeare (= he is not nearly as good as Shakespeare). \n 他是位好作家，但无法与莎士比亚相提并论。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompa001.mp3'),('compartment','（车辆的）分隔厢，舱；（尤指火车的）隔间，包厢（家具、设备或容器的）隔间，格（身体内的）隔间，隔室','uk :kəmˈpɑːt.mənt, us :kəmˈpɑːrt.mənt','[a first-class compartment \n 头等包厢 \n, a fridge with a small freezer compartment \n 带有小冷冻室的冰箱 \n, the sleeping/inner compartment in a tent \n 帐篷里的睡间／内间 \n, The knee joint is composed of three compartments and ligaments that stabilize the joint. \n 膝关节由三个隔间和起稳定作用的韧带组成。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompa002.mp3'),('compensate','赔偿；补偿弥补，补偿','uk :ˈkɒm.pən.seɪt, us :ˈkɑːm.pən.seɪt','[Victims of the crash will be compensated for their injuries. \n 车祸的受害者会得到伤害赔偿。 \n, Nothing will ever compensate for his lost childhood. \n 什么也不能弥补他失去的童年。 \n, His enthusiasm more than compensates for his lack of experience. \n 他的热情大大弥补了经验的不足。 \n, I took her swimming to compensate for having missed out on the cinema. \n 为弥补她错过了电影，我带她去游泳。 \n, We were late and I was driving fast to compensate. \n 我们迟到了，所以我开快车来赶时间。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompa019.mp3'),('competitive edge','竞争优势','Jìngzhēng yōushì','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=competitive edge&tl=ja&tk=177902.295578&client=webapp&prev=input'),('compound','化合物复合物；混合物（语法中的）复合词（围起来的）场地，楼群，院落使加重，使加剧，使恶化使混合；使复合复合的（利息）以复利计算的','uk :ˈkɒm.paʊnd, us :ˈkɑːm-','[Salt is a compound of sodium and chlorine. \n 盐是钠和氯的化合物。 \n, Many fertilizers contain nitrogen compounds. \n 许多化学肥料都含有氮化合物。 \n, Then there was his manner, a curious compound of humour and severity. \n 还有他的态度，那是一种幽默与严厉的奇异混合。 \n,  Bodyguard  and  floppy disk  are two examples of compounds. \n bodyguard 和 floppy disk 是两个复合词。 \n, The gates opened and the troops marched into their compound. \n 大门开了，部队进入他们的大院。 \n, The embassy compound has been closed to the public because of a bomb threat. \n 因受到炸弹威胁，使馆区停止对公众开放。 \n, Her terror was compounded by the feeling that she was being watched. \n 她有种被人监视的感觉，这加剧了她的恐惧感。 \n, His financial problems were compounded when he unexpectedly lost his job. \n 他意外地失去了工作，这使他手头更紧了。 \n, Severe drought has compounded food shortages in the region. \n 严重的干旱加剧了该地区的食品短缺问题。 \n, Most tyres are made of rubber compounded with other chemicals and materials. \n 大多数轮胎都是用橡胶和其他化学制品、材料混合制成的。 \n, compound interest \n 复利 \n, The investment fund has achieved annual compound returns of 18.2 percent. \n 投资得到了18.2%的复利年回报率。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompl019.mp3'),('concept','原则；概念；观念；想法对…一无所知','uk :ˈkɒn.sept, us :ˈkɑːn.sept','[The concept of free speech is unknown to them. \n 他们没有言论自由的概念。 \n, It is very difficult to define the concept of beauty. \n 很难给美这个概念下一个定义。 \n, I failed to grasp the film s central concept. \n 我没理解这部电影的中心思想。 \n, Kleenbrite is a whole new concept in toothpaste! \n Kleenbrite 是牙膏生产领域的一个全新概念！ \n, I don t think you have any concept of the pain you have caused her. \n 我觉得你对自己给她造成的痛苦根本就一无所知。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconce011.mp3'),('conduct','组织；实施；进行；处理（尤指在公共或正式场合中）举止，表现；为人引导；带领；指引；给…带路为…导游，带（游客）游览指挥（合唱团、乐队等）传导（电或热）行为，举止；表现；为人组织方式；实施方式','uk :kənˈdʌkt, us :kənˈdʌkt','[We are conducting a survey to find out what our customers think of their local bus service. \n 我们正在进行一项调查，了解顾客对当地公交服务系统的看法。 \n, The experiments were conducted by scientists in New York. \n 这些实验是科学家在纽约做的。 \n, How you choose to conduct your private life is your own business! \n 你选择怎么过你的私生活是你自己的事！ \n, How should I conduct myself at these dinners? I know nothing about etiquette. \n 我在这类晚宴上该怎样做到举止得体呢？对于礼仪我可是一窍不通。 \n, May I conduct you to your table, sir, or would you prefer to have a drink at the bar first? \n 先生，我带您去餐桌呢，还是您先在吧台喝上一杯？ \n, The protesters were conducted from the courtroom by two police officers. \n 抗议者被两名警察带出了法庭。 \n, A guide conducts tours of the cathedral every afternoon at 2.00. \n 每天下午2点一位导游会带游客参观大教堂。 \n, a conducted tour of the palace \n 有导游陪同的宫殿游 \n, The orchestra was conducted by Mira Shapur. \n 管弦乐队由米拉‧沙普尔指挥。 \n, Who\'s conducting at tonight\'s concert? \n 今晚的音乐会谁担任指挥？ \n, Copper conducts electricity, but plastic does not. \n 铜导电，但塑料不导电。 \n, bad/excellent/disgraceful conduct \n 糟糕的／得体的／丢脸的举止 \n, The club has a strict code (= set of rules) of conduct. \n 该俱乐部有严格的行为准则。 \n, He was criticized for his conduct of the inquiry. \n 他组织这次调查的方式受到了批评。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconde029.mp3'),('confirmatory','确切的','uk :kənˈfɜː.mə.tər.i, us :kənˈfɜ˞ː.mə.tɔːr.i','[nyone who tests positive with a rapid test must get a confirmatory blood test.\n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0318ukconf0346.mp3'),('confrontation','对抗；冲突；对峙；争论','uk :ˌkɒn.frʌnˈteɪ.ʃən, us :ˌkɑːn.frənˈteɪ.ʃən','[Some couples seem to like confrontation, but Josh and I hardly ever argue. \n 有的夫妻似乎很喜欢争吵，我跟乔希却几乎没有吵过嘴。 \n, There were violent confrontations between police and demonstrators. \n 警察和示威者之间发生了激烈的冲突。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfi026.mp3'),('confrontational','對抗性的','uk :ˌkɒn.frʌnˈteɪ.ʃən.əl, us :ˌkɑːn.frənˈteɪ.ʃən.əl','[e has a very aggressive, confrontational way of talking to people.\n, The opposition has adopted a more confrontational approach in recent months.\n, nion leaders said they were disappointed by the rhetoric used by the management, and dismayed by their confrontational approach.\n, You should try to be less confrontational if you want to work well in a team.\n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfi027.mp3'),('congregate','聚集，集合','uk :ˈkɒŋ.ɡrɪ.ɡeɪt, us :ˈkɑːŋ.ɡrə.ɡeɪt','[A crowd congregated around the entrance to the theatre, hoping to catch a glimpse of the stars of the show. \n 一群人聚集在戏院门口，希望能看一眼演出的明星。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfu019.mp3'),('conjure','变戏法；用魔法变出；像变魔术般变出','uk :ˈkʌn.dʒər, us :ˈkʌn.dʒɚ','[In an instant, the magician had conjured (up) a dove from his hat. \n 魔术师眨眼间便从他的帽子里变出了一只鸽子。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconje009.mp3'),('consecrate','使圣化；把…奉为神圣；给…祝圣宣布…任主教','uk :ˈkɒn.sɪ.kreɪt, us :ˈkɑːn.sə.kreɪt','[The new cathedral was completed and consecrated in 2002. \n 新的大教堂于2002年竣工并祝圣。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsc011.mp3'),('consequent','作为结果的；随之而来的；由此引起的','uk :ˈkɒn.sɪ.kwənt, us :ˈkɑːn.sə.kwənt','[Our use of harmful chemicals and the consequent damage to the environment is a very serious matter. \n 我们使用有害化学物品且因此对环境造成了破坏，这是件非常严重的事情。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsc020.mp3'),('consist','在于，存在于','uk :kənˈsɪst, us :kənˈsɪst','[The beauty of air travel consists in its speed and ease. \n 乘飞机旅行的好处在于快捷、舒适。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n For her, happiness consists in watching television and reading magazines. \n 对她来说，幸福就是看电视和读杂志。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld00265.mp3'),('constitution','宪法；章程体质，体格组成；构成；结构；构造','uk :ˌkɒn.stɪˈtʃuː.ʃən, us :ˌkɑːn.stəˈtuː.ʃən',NULL,'2020-02-14',3,4,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsp021.mp3'),('constitutional','宪法（或章程）允许的，符合宪法（或章程）的体质的，体格的健身散步','uk :ˌkɒn.stɪˈtʃuː.ʃən.əl, us :ˌkɑːn.stəˈtuː.ʃən.əl',NULL,'2020-02-13',4,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsp022.mp3'),('contaminate','污染；弄脏；毒害','uk :kənˈtæm.ɪ.neɪt, us :kənˈtæm.ə.neɪt','[Much of the coast has been contaminated by nuclear waste. \n 大部分海岸已受到核废料污染。 \n, The food which had been contaminated was destroyed. \n 受污染的食物已被销毁了。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconta006.mp3'),('contemplate','盘算；沉思，冥想','uk :ˈkɒn.təm.pleɪt, us :ˈkɑːn.t̬əm.pleɪt','[[ + -ing verb ] \n I m contemplating going abroad for a year. \n 我打算出国一年。 \n, They were contemplating a move to California. \n 他们打算搬到加利福尼亚去。 \n, It s too awful/horrific/dangerous to contemplate. \n 这件事太糟糕／可怕／危险，简直不敢想。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconta010.mp3'),('content','满意的；满足的；知足的（杂志或书的）目录（文章、演讲、电影等的）内容所含之物；容纳的东西；内容含量使满意，使满足','uk :kənˈtent, us :kənˈtent','[He seems fairly content with (his) life. \n 他好像对生活相当满足。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n They re content to socialize with a very small circle of people. \n 他们满足于只和一小群人交往。 \n, the table of (= list of) contents \n 目录 \n, the contents page \n 目录页 \n, It s a very stylish and beautiful film, but it lacks content. \n 这部电影很新潮而且画面美丽，但内容空洞。 \n, We ve discussed the unusual form of the book - now, what about the content? \n 我们已经讨论了这本书与众不同的形式——现在，谈谈它的内容怎么样？ \n, The contents of his bag spilled all over the floor. \n 他包里的东西掉了一地。 \n, He didn t need to open the letter because he already knew the contents. \n 他不用拆那封信，因为他已经知道内容了。 \n, Chocolate has a high fat content. \n 巧克力脂肪含量很高。 \n, You re quite easily contented, aren t you? \n 你很容易满足，是不是？ \n, My explanation seemed to content him. \n 我的解释似乎让他很满意。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconta026.mp3'),('contingency','可能发生的事；意外事件，不测事件','uk :kənˈtɪn.dʒən.si, us :kənˈtɪn.dʒən.si','[You must be able to deal with all possible contingencies. \n 你必须能应付一切可能发生的意外事件。 \n, Have you made any contingency plans? \n 你们制订应急方案了吗？ \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconte020.mp3'),('controversial','有争议的；引起争议的','uk :ˌkɒn.trəˈvɜː.ʃəl, us :ˌkɑːn.trəˈvɝː.ʃəl','[a controversial issue/decision/speech/figure \n 有争议的问题／决议／讲话／数字 \n, The book was very controversial. \n 这本书很有争议。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukcontr023.mp3'),('convey','表达，传达（思想、感情或想法）运送，运输','uk :kənˈveɪ, us :kənˈveɪ','[His poetry conveys a great sense of religious devotion. \n 他的诗歌表达了献身宗教的强烈感情。 \n, Please convey our condolences to the family. \n 请向家人转达我们的哀思。 \n, [ + question word ] \n I tried to convey in my speech how grateful we all were for his help. \n 在发言中，我竭力地表达我们大家对他所给予帮助的感激之情。 \n, You don t want to convey the impression that we re not interested. \n 你不想给人留下我们不感兴趣的印象吧。 \n, The goods are usually conveyed by rail. \n 这种货物通常通过铁路运输。 \n, Could you convey a message to Mr Merrick for me, please? \n 你能替我给梅里克先生传个口信吗？ \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve003.mp3'),('convicted','（在法庭上）宣判…有罪，证明…有罪已决犯，既决犯；（服刑中的）囚犯','uk :kənˈvɪkt, us :kənˈvɪkt','[He has twice been convicted of robbery/arson. \n 他两次被判犯有抢劫罪／纵火罪。 \n, an escaped convict \n 逃犯 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve009.mp3'),('convince','说服；使相信；使信服','uk :kənˈvɪns, us :kənˈvɪns','[He managed to convince the jury of his innocence. \n 他使陪审团相信他是无辜的。 \n, [ + (that) ] \n It s useless trying to convince her (that) she doesn t need to lose any weight. \n 要让她相信她无需减肥是徒劳的。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n I hope this will convince you to change your mind. \n 我希望这会说服你改变主意。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve011.mp3'),('convincing','令人信服的；有说服力的令人心悦诚服的胜利，大比分获胜','uk :kənˈvɪn.sɪŋ, us :kənˈvɪn.sɪŋ','[a convincing argument/explanation \n 令人信服的论据／解释 \n, convincing evidence \n 确凿的证据 \n, The end of the book wasn\'t very convincing. \n 这本书的结局难以令人信服。 \n, They won a convincing victory. \n 他们大比分获胜。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve013.mp3'),('coronavirus','冠状病毒','uk :kəˈrəʊ.nəˌvaɪə.rəs, us :kəˈroʊ.nəˌvaɪ.rəs','[]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0317corouk0920.mp3'),('corpse','（通常指人的）尸体','uk :kɔːps, us :kɔːrps','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcor/ukcorps001.mp3'),('corrode','（使）腐蚀；侵蚀','uk :kəˈrəʊd, us :kəˈroʊd','[Steel tends to corrode faster in a salty atmosphere. \n 在盐分高的环境里，钢往往腐蚀得更快。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcor/ukcorps027.mp3'),('cotton','棉，棉花棉线；棉布（通常用于清洁皮肤的）药棉，脱脂棉','uk :ˈkɒt.ən, us :ˈkɑː.t̬ən','[a bale of cotton \n 一大包棉花 \n, a shirt made of pure cotton \n 纯棉衬衫 \n, She looked pretty in a simple cotton dress. \n 她穿着朴素的棉布连衣裙，看上去很漂亮。 \n, K \n a reel of cotton (= thread) \n 一卷棉线 \n, cotton pads \n 化妆棉 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcos/ukcossa021.mp3'),('counterpart','（与不同地方或组织的人或物）作用相同者，相对应者','uk :ˈkaʊn.tə.pɑːt, us :ˈkaʊn.t̬ɚ.pɑːrt','[The prime minister is to meet his European counterparts to discuss the war against drugs. \n 首相将会见欧洲各国首脑就打击毒品犯罪进行商讨。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcou/ukcounc029.mp3'),('courier','（递送重要书信或文件的）信使，递送员旅游团领队，导游通过递送员递送','uk :ˈkʊr.i.ər, us :ˈkʊr.i.ɚ','[I want to have this package delivered by motorcycle courier. \n 我想找摩托递送员送这个包裹。 \n, I ll courier the relevant documents to you this afternoon. \n 我今天下午请递送员把相关文件送给你。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcou/ukcouri001.mp3'),('coward','胆小鬼，懦夫','uk :ˈkaʊ.əd, us :ˈkaʊ.ɚd','[They branded her a coward for informing on her colleagues during the interrogation. \n 她在审讯中告发了同事，因此被视为懦夫。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcov/ukcover012.mp3'),('creep','（通常指为避免注意而）缓慢行进，悄悄移动，潜行谄媚者，奴颜婢膝者，阿谀奉承者讨厌鬼，令人恶心的人（尤指男人）使…毛骨悚然；使…紧张害怕','uk :kriːp, us :kriːp','[She turned off the light and crept through the door. \n 她关上灯，悄悄溜出门。 \n, Someone was creeping around outside my window. \n 有人在我的窗户外蹑手蹑脚地走动。 \n, The spider crept up the wall. \n 蜘蛛缓缓地爬上墙。 \n, The traffic was creeping along at a snail s pace. \n 车辆如蜗牛般缓慢移动。 \n, Making coffee for the boss again? You creep! \n 又在给老板冲咖啡？你这个马屁精！ \n, He was such a creep - he was always staring at me in the canteen. \n 他真是个讨厌鬼——在饭厅里他老盯着我看。 \n, [ as form of address ] \n Leave me alone, creep! \n 让我一个人呆一会儿，你这个讨厌鬼！ \n, Living next to a graveyard would give me the creeps. \n 住在墓地旁边会令我毛骨悚然。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcre/ukcreed002.mp3'),('crippling','手臂残废者；瘸子，跛子感情残废者，感情有缺陷的人使受伤致残；使跛严重损坏；严重削弱残疾的，伤残的严重的；造成严重后果的','uk :ˈkrɪp.əl, us :ˈkrɪp.əl','[a country crippled by war \n 因战争而元气大伤的国家 \n, Will she be crippled for life? \n 她会终生残疾吗？ \n, A crippling attack of malaria kept him in bed for months. \n 一场严重的疟疾让他好几个月卧床不起。 \n, crippling debts \n 使人破产的债务 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcre/ukcrew_028.mp3'),('crisis','危机，极其困难的时期紧要关头，危急时刻（疾病的）危险期，关键期信任危机','uk :ˈkraɪ.sɪs, us :ˈkraɪ.sɪs',NULL,'2020-02-14',7,6,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcri/ukcripp003.mp3'),('crisp','脆的；易碎的（糕点、饼干等食物）酥脆的（蔬果）新鲜爽脆的，脆生生的（纸或布）挺括的，平展的（声音或形象）清晰明了的（说话、写作或行为）干脆利落的，利索的，明快的（天气）干冷的，晴冷的（空气）清爽的，凉爽的油炸薯片酥皮水果甜点心','uk :krɪsp, us :krɪsp','[a crisp apple \n 脆生生的苹果 \n, a crisp new £5 note/a crisp white tablecloth \n 平展簇新的5英镑钞票／平展的白色桌布 \n, The sound from the new speakers is very crisp. \n 新扬声器的声音非常清晰。 \n, a crisp reply \n 干脆利落的回答 \n, a crisp, efficient manner \n 举止利落干练 \n, a wonderful crisp spring morning \n 一个晴爽的春日清晨 \n, I breathed in deeply the crisp mountain air. \n 我深深地吸了口山间清爽的空气。 \n, a packet of salt and vinegar crisps \n 一袋盐醋薯片 \n, apple crisp \n 酥皮苹果甜点 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcri/ukcripp004.mp3'),('crop','庄稼，作物；收成，收获量（同时涌现的）一批，一帮（人或事物）平头发型（鸟的）嗉囊短马鞭修剪；剪短（羊、马等）啃食（草或其他植物）的顶部剪裁（照片）（植物）结果，开花，收成，收获种植（庄稼）','uk :krɒp, us :krɑːp','[The main crops grown for export are coffee and rice. \n 主要的出口作物是咖啡和大米。 \n, a bumper (= very good) potato crop \n 土豆大丰收 \n, The judges will select the best from this year s crop of first novels. \n 评委们将从今年的一批处女作小说中选出最出色的一部。 \n, Her hair was cut in a short crop. \n 她留着很短的平头。 \n, He had his hair cropped when he went into the army. \n 他参军时把头发剪短了。 \n, He cropped the photo so that only the face remained. \n 他把照片剪到只剩下脸。 \n, The carrots have cropped (= grown) well this year. \n 今年的胡萝卜收成很好。 \n, The land is intensively cropped. \n 这片地庄稼种得很密。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrocu014.mp3'),('crop-up','提及','','null\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'null'),('crossword','纵横填字游戏','uk :ˈkrɒs.wɜːd, us :ˈkrɑːs.wɝːd','[I do the Times crossword every morning. \n 我每天早上都要做《泰晤士报》上的填字游戏。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcross018.mp3'),('crowd','>人群；群众>（有共同爱好的）一帮朋友，一伙人，一群人>挤；靠近；盯着','uk :>kraʊd, us :>kraʊd',NULL,'2020-02-14',0,6,1,NULL),('crucial','至关重要的；关键的；决定性的','uk :ˈkruː.ʃəl, us :ˈkruː.ʃəl','[a crucial decision/question \n 至关重要的决定／问题 \n, Her work has been crucial to the project\'s success. \n 她的工作对于这个项目的成功至关重要。 \n, [ + that ] \n It is crucial that the problem is tackled immediately. \n 关键是要马上着手处理这一问题。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrowe004.mp3'),('crude','粗糙的；简陋的；粗制的；未加修饰的粗俗的；粗野的；无礼的原油','uk :kruːd, us :kruːd','[a crude device/weapon \n 简陋的装置／粗制的武器 \n, a crude remark/comment \n 粗俗的话／评论 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrowe013.mp3'),('cruel','残忍的；残酷的；刻毒伤人的令人痛苦的残酷地；残忍地','uk :ˈkruː.əl, us :ˈkruː.əl','[Don t tease him about his weight - it s cruel. \n 别拿他的体重开玩笑——这样太刻薄了。 \n, Children can be very cruel to each other. \n 小孩相互之间会很残忍。 \n, His death was a cruel blow. \n 他的死是个无情的打击。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrowe018.mp3'),('cunning','狡猾的，狡诈的吸引人的，迷人的狡诈；狡猾；机灵','uk :ˈkʌn.ɪŋ, us :ˈkʌn.ɪŋ','[a cunning plan/ploy \n 诡诈的计划／花招 \n, He s a very cunning man. \n 他为人十分狡猾。 \n, a cunning little child/puppy/kitten \n 逗人喜爱的小孩／小狗／小猫 \n, We need to show some cunning if we want to defeat the enemy. \n 要想骗过敌人，我们得想点计策。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcul/ukcull_029.mp3'),('curator','（博物馆、图书馆等的）馆长','uk :kjʊˈreɪ.tər, us :kjɝːˈeɪ.t̬ɚ',NULL,'2020-02-13',7,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcun/ukcunt_019.mp3'),('customs-union','关税同盟','null','null\n','2020-01-07',0,3,0,'null'),('cynical','愤世嫉俗的；怀疑人之真诚的；认为人皆自私的利用他人感情的；损人利己的','uk :ˈsɪn.ɪ.kəl, us :ˈsɪn.ɪ.kəl','[She has a pretty cynical view of men. \n 她对男人的态度太过偏激。 \n, I ve always been deeply cynical about politicians. \n 我对政客们总是嗤之以鼻。 \n, She works in that most cynical of industries - advertising. \n 她供职于最具煽惑性的行业——广告行业。 \n, He praises my cooking but it s just a cynical ploy to get me to make him dinner. \n 他夸我烧一手好菜只不过是在耍花招，哄我给他做饭。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcyb/ukcyber023.mp3'),('dame','女人（童话剧中通常由男人扮演的）老年女丑角，滑稽老太婆（英国授予有贡献的女性的荣誉称号）女爵士；有女爵士头衔的女性','uk :deɪm, us :deɪm','[Dame Judy Dench \n 朱迪‧登奇女爵士 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdag/ukdagoe026.mp3'),('dapper','（男子）穿着考究的，衣冠楚楚的','uk :ˈdæp.ər, us :ˈdæp.ɚ','[Hercule Poirot is the dapper detective of the Agatha Christie novels. \n 赫尔克里‧波洛就是阿加莎‧克里斯蒂小说中那位衣冠楚楚的侦探。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdam/ukdamne030.mp3'),('debate','谈论，讨论；争论，辩论讨论；争论斟酌；考虑','uk :dɪˈbeɪt, us :dɪˈbeɪt','[Education is the current focus of public debate. \n 教育是目前大众谈论的焦点。 \n, How we proceed from here is a matter for debate. \n 我们下一步怎样做还需要讨论。 \n, Over the year we have had several debates about future policy. \n 一年来，我们就未来的政策进行了几次讨论。 \n, In Parliament today, MPs debated the Finance Bill. \n 今天在议会上议员们讨论了财政法案。 \n, They had been debating for several hours without reaching a conclusion. \n 他们已经争论了好几个小时，仍然没有得出一个结论。 \n, [ + question word ] \n The authorities debated whether to build a new car park. \n 政府有关部门就是否要修建一座新停车场进行了讨论。 \n, [ + question word ] \n We debated whether to take the earlier train. \n 我们考虑到底要不要乘早一点的那次列车。 \n, I m still debating what colour to paint the walls. \n 我还在考虑要把墙刷成什么颜色。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdea/ukdeath012.mp3'),('debt','借款，欠款；债务','uk :det, us :det','[He managed to pay off his debts in two years. \n 他设法在两年内还清了债务。 \n, The company ran up huge debts. \n 公司很快就负债累累。 \n, They are in debt to (= owe money to) the bank. \n 他们欠银行的钱。 \n, He got into debt (= borrowed money) after he lost his job. \n 他失业后开始举债。 \n, The company is deep in debt (= owes a lot of money). \n 公司已经债台高筑。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdea/ukdeath023.mp3'),('decade','十年；年代','uk :ˈdek.eɪd, us :ˈdek.eɪd','[]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdea/ukdeath030.mp3'),('decay','腐蚀；（使）衰败，（使）衰弱腐蚀；衰败，衰弱','uk :dɪˈkeɪ, us :dɪˈkeɪ','[Sugar makes your teeth decay. \n 糖能引起蛀牙。 \n, The role of the extended family has been decaying for some time. \n 大家庭的作用开始减弱已经有一段时间了。 \n, Pollution has decayed the surface of the stonework on the front of the cathedral. \n 大教堂前部的石刻表面已经因为污染受到了侵蚀。 \n, the smell of decaying meat \n 腐肉气味 \n, environmental/industrial/moral/urban decay \n 环境恶化／工业衰退／道德沦丧／城市衰落 \n, dental/tooth decay \n 蛀牙 \n, The buildings had started to fall into decay. \n 那些建筑已经开始破败了。 \n, This industry has been in decay for some time. \n 这个行业早就开始衰退了。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdec/ukdecad014.mp3'),('decorate','装饰，装点，打扮粉刷；（给…）贴壁纸（尤指授予奖章以）嘉奖，表彰','uk :ˈdek.ə.reɪt, us :ˈdek.ər.eɪt','[They decorated the wedding car with ribbons and flowers. \n 他们用彩带和鲜花装点婚车。 \n, We re going to decorate the kitchen next week. \n 我们下周要粉刷厨房。 \n, I hate the smell of paint when I m decorating. \n 我刷墙时很讨厌油漆味儿。 \n, They were decorated for their part in the rescue. \n 他们因在此次救援行动中的表现而受到嘉奖。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdec/ukdecod014.mp3'),('defect','缺点；缺陷；瑕疵生理缺陷；生理障碍（尤指为加入敌对国家、政党等）脱离，退出，叛逃','uk :ˈdiː.fekt, us :ˈdiː.fekt',NULL,'2020-02-13',4,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdef/ukdefec001.mp3'),('delicate','脆弱的；娇嫩的需要小心处理的微妙的形势（问题，时刻等）精细的，精密的柔和的；轻柔的；清淡的纤细的，细长的','uk :ˈdel.ɪ.kət, us :ˈdel.ə.kət','[Peaches have delicate skins which are easily bruised. \n 桃子的表皮很娇嫩，容易碰伤。 \n, Delicate plants need to be kept in a greenhouse during the winter. \n 娇贵的植物需要在温室里过冬。 \n, delicate china \n 易碎的瓷器 \n, Molly s health has always been delicate (= she gets sick easily). \n 莫莉的身体一直都很娇弱。 \n, Repairing damaged nerves is a very delicate operation/process. \n 修复受损神经的手术／过程需要非常小心谨慎。 \n, I need to speak to you about a delicate matter. \n 我要跟你谈一件很棘手的事情。 \n, The pay negotiations have reached a delicate point/stage. \n 工资谈判已经到了微妙的关头／阶段。 \n, Teachers need to strike a delicate (= carefully achieved) balance between instructing their students and letting them discover things for themselves. \n 教师需要在向学生传授知识和引导学生自己去探索之间找到一个微妙的平衡点。 \n, Weather-forecasters have extremely delicate equipment which helps them predict what the weather is going to be like. \n 气象预报人员使用非常精密的设备来帮助他们预测天气变化。 \n, a rose with a delicate scent \n 散发清香的玫瑰 \n, a delicate shade of pink \n 柔和的粉色 \n, We chose a delicate floral pattern for our bedroom curtains. \n 我们为卧室选了一种花色图案非常淡雅的窗帘。 \n, She folded her delicate hands on the table. \n 她纤纤十指交叉着放在桌上。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdej/ukdejur023.mp3'),('delta','三角洲（希腊语字母表的第四个字母）','uk :ˈdel.tə, us :ˈdel.t̬ə','[the Mississippi delta \n 密西西比河三角洲 \n, the delta of the Nile \n 尼罗河三角洲 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdel/ukdelig020.mp3'),('demerit','缺陷；劣势（尤指学校给学生的）记过，过失分','uk :ˌdiːˈmer.ɪt, us :ˌdiːˈmer.ɪt','[We need to consider the merits and demerits of the plan. \n 我们需要考虑该计划的优缺点。 \n, She got three demerits for lateness on this term s report. \n 她因迟到在本学期总评中被记过3次。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdem/ukdemag017.mp3'),('demonstrator','展示者，演示者，示范者示威者，游行者','uk :ˈdem.ən.streɪ.tər, us :ˈdem.ən.streɪ.t̬ɚ','[A demonstrator was showing customers how the food processor worked. \n 一个人在向顾客演示如何使用食品加工器。 \n, Police arrested several of the demonstrators. \n 警察逮捕了数名示威者。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdem/ukdemoc026.mp3'),('derivative','缺乏独创性的；模仿的衍生物，派生物；派生词金融衍生产品','uk :dɪˈrɪv.ə.tɪv, us :dɪˈrɪv.ə.t̬ɪv','[His painting/style is very derivative. \n 他的油画／风格有很重的模仿痕迹。 \n,  Detestable  is a derivative of  detest . \n detestable 这个词是从 detest 派生而来的。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukder/ukdereg011.mp3'),('derive','从…中得到，从…中获得','uk :dɪˈraɪv, us :dɪˈraɪv','[The institute derives all its money from foreign investments. \n 该机构的资金均来自于国外投资。 \n, She derives great pleasure/satisfaction from playing the violin. \n 拉小提琴能让她获得极大的乐趣／满足。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukder/ukdereg013.mp3'),('deserve','值得；应得','uk :dɪˈzɜːv, us :dɪˈzɝːv','[After all that hard work, you deserve a holiday. \n 干了那么多活儿，你该休假了。 \n, Chris deserves our special thanks for all his efforts. \n 我们应该特别感谢克里斯所付出的心血。 \n, I hope they get the punishment they deserve. \n 我希望他们受到应有的惩罚。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n They certainly deserved to win that game. \n 他们当然应该赢得那场比赛。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdes/ukdescr017.mp3'),('desperation','破釜沉舟，拼死一搏急需；渴求','uk :ˌdes.pəˈreɪ.ʃən, us :ˌdes.pəˈreɪ.ʃən','[There was a note of desperation in his voice. \n 他的声音里透出破釜沉舟的决心。 \n, In desperation, they jumped out of the window to escape the fire. \n 情急之下，他们跳出窗户躲避大火。 \n, an act of desperation \n 破釜沉舟之举 \n, his desperation to survive \n 他强烈的求生欲望 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdes/ukdesir023.mp3'),('detective','侦探警探（用于某些级别的警察头衔）','uk :dɪˈtek.tɪv, us :dɪˈtek.tɪv','[a private detective \n 私家侦探 \n, detective stories \n 侦探故事 \n, Detective Sergeant Lewis \n 刘易斯探长 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetai008.mp3'),('detest','憎恨；厌恶，讨厌','uk :dɪˈtest, us :dɪˈtest','[I detest any kind of cruelty. \n 我厌恶任何形式的残暴。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n I detest having to get up when it\'s dark outside. \n 我讨厌天不亮就得起床。 \n, her detested older brother \n 她那令人讨厌的哥哥 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetai023.mp3'),('devastate','摧毁；毁灭使极为震惊；使极为烦乱','uk :ˈdev.ə.steɪt, us :ˈdev.ə.steɪt',NULL,'2020-02-13',5,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetou015.mp3'),('devotee','（狂热的）崇拜者，爱好者','uk :ˌdev.əˈtiː, us :ˌdev.əˈtiː','[He is a great devotee of the prime minister. \n 他是首相的狂热崇拜者。 \n, devotees of golf \n 高尔夫球爱好者 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdev/ukdevil015.mp3'),('diagnose','诊断（病症）；查出（问题）','uk :ˈdaɪ.əɡ.nəʊz, us :ˌdaɪ.əɡˈnoʊz','[The specialist diagnosed cancer. \n 那位专家作出的诊断是癌症。 \n, His condition was diagnosed as some type of blood disorder. \n 他的病被诊断为某种血液病。 \n, She was diagnosed with/as having diabetes. \n 她被查出患有糖尿病。 \n, The electrician has diagnosed a fault in the wiring. \n 电工查出了一处线路故障。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdex/ukdextr010.mp3'),('dial','拨号，按号码表盘，仪表盘旋钮，调节器（老式电话机的）拨号盘','uk :ˈdaɪ.əl, us :ˈdaɪ.əl','[Can I dial this number direct, or do I have to go through the operator? \n 我可以直接拨这个号码还是需要通过话务员接转？ \n, Dial 0 for the switchboard. \n 总机拨0。 \n, Can you read what it says on the dial? \n 你能读出仪表盘上的读数吗？ \n, The dial of/on his watch had a picture of Mickey Mouse on it. \n 他手表的表盘上有一个米老鼠的图案。 \n, You turn this dial to find a different radio station. \n 转动这个旋钮可选择不同的广播电台。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdex/ukdextr019.mp3'),('diarrhea','腹泻','uk :ˌdaɪ.əˈriː.ə, us :ˌdaɪ.əˈriː.ə','[diarrhoea and sickness \n 腹泻恶心 \n, an attack of diarrhoea \n 腹泻发作 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdia/ukdiaph004.mp3'),('digestive','消化的（全麦）消化饼干','uk :daɪˈdʒes.tɪv, us :daɪˈdʒes.tɪv','[the digestive process \n 消化过程 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdif/ukdiffi016.mp3'),('dimly','昏暗的','uk :ˈdɪm.li, us :ˈdɪm.li','[he room was dimly lit.\n, The February sun shone dimly.\n,  dimly remembered reading the book a few years before.\n, They were only dimly aware of the telephone ringing.\n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdig/ukdigs_029.mp3'),('dimmer','亮度调节器','uk :ˈdɪm.ər, us :ˈdɪm.ɚ','[]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/uka32/uka32549.mp3'),('disarming','缴…的械,解除…的武装；交出武器,裁军（尤指出乎意料地）使产生好感','uk :dɪˈsɑːm, us :dɪˈsɑːrm','[With one movement, she disarmed the man and pinned him against the wall. \n 她一下子就缴了那男子的械，并把他按到墙上。 \n, Many politicians argued that this was no time to disarm (= give up the country s weapons and army). \n 很多政治家争辩说现在不是交出国家的武器和军队的时候。 \n, Experts successfully managed to disarm the bomb (= stop it from exploding). \n 专家们成功地拆除了炸弹的引信。 \n, His frankness completely disarmed her. \n 他的坦率彻底征服了她。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisap003.mp3'),('discrepancy','不一致，出入，差异','uk :dɪˈskrep.ən.si, us :dɪˈskrep.ən.si','[There is some discrepancy between the two accounts. \n 这两份账单之间有一些出入。 \n, The committee is reportedly unhappy about the discrepancy in numbers. \n 据说委员会对数字不一致很不满。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisco024.mp3'),('discrimination','歧视；区别对待区分能力，辨别能力','uk :dɪˌskrɪm.ɪˈneɪ.ʃən, us :dɪˌskrɪm.əˈneɪ.ʃən','[racial/sex/age discrimination \n 种族／性别／年龄歧视 \n, Until 1986 most companies would not even allow women to take the exams, but such blatant discrimination is now disappearing. \n 直至1986年大多数公司甚至还不允许女性参加这种考试，但目前这种明目张胆的歧视做法正在消失。 \n]\n','2020-02-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisco030.mp3'),('disguise','给…化装，给…乔装打扮；将…伪装起来掩饰，隐藏（观点、感受等）化装用具（服饰）；用于伪装的东西伪装，化装','uk :dɪsˈɡaɪz, us :dɪsˈɡaɪz','[He disguised himself by wearing a false beard. \n 他粘上假胡须伪装自己。 \n, Minor skin imperfections can usually be disguised with a spot of make-up. \n 微小的皮肤瑕疵通常可以用化妆品来掩盖。 \n, We tried to 