3'),('easter','复活节（基督教纪念耶稣复活的节日）','uk :ˈiː.stər, us :ˈiː.stɚ','[I get two weeks off school at Easter. \n 复活节我们学校放假两周。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeas/ukeasil006.mp3'),('elaborate','精心计划（或制作）的；详尽的；复杂的详尽说明；阐述','uk :iˈlæb.ər.ət, us :iˈlæb.ɚ.ət','[You want a plain blouse to go with that skirt - nothing too elaborate. \n 你应该用一件样式简单的衬衫来配那条裙子，不要样式太复杂的。 \n, They re making the most elaborate preparations for the wedding. \n 他们正为婚礼做极为精心周到的准备。 \n, He came out with such an elaborate excuse that I didn t quite believe him. \n 他突然说了那么一大套理由，我不太相信他。 \n, The congresswoman said she was resigning, but refused to elaborate on her reasons for doing so. \n 这位国会女议员说她要辞职，但拒绝说明辞职的原因。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeig/ukeight014.mp3'),('elbow','肘；（衣服的）肘部用肘推；用肘挤开（为让某人注意或提醒某事而）用肘碰','uk :ˈel.bəʊ, us :ˈel.boʊ','[Her arm was bandaged from the elbow to the fingers. \n 她的胳膊从肘部一直到手指全缠上了绷带。 \n, The sleeve of his shirt was torn at the elbow. \n 他的衬衫的肘部被撕了个口子。 \n, He elbowed his way to the front of the crowd. \n 他挤到了人群的前边。 \n, They elbowed the onlookers aside. \n 他们把旁观者推到一边。 \n, She elbowed me in the ribs before I could say anything. \n 我还没开口呢，她就用胳膊肘在我肋部碰了一下。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeig/ukeight030.mp3'),('elevation','立面图；立视图海拔；高度丘；高地，高处提拔；晋升；提升','uk :ˌel.ɪˈveɪ.ʃən, us :ˌel.əˈveɪ.ʃən','[This plan shows the front, side, and back elevations of the new supermarket. \n 该示意图展示的是新超市的正、侧、后三面的立视图。 \n, Atmospheric pressure varies with elevation and temperature. \n 气压随海拔和气温的变化而变化。 \n, The crop is not grown at high elevations/above an elevation of 1,000 metres. \n 这种作物不宜在海拔高的／海拔高于1000米的地区种植。 \n, The flagpole stands on a small elevation in front of the building. \n 旗杆矗立在楼前的一小块高地上。 \n, His elevation to the presidency of the new republic was generally popular. \n 总的来说，他被推举为新共和国的总统是众望所归。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukele/ukelect020.mp3'),('elite','（社会）上层集团；掌权人物；出类拔萃的人，精英（社会）上层集团的；掌权人物的；精英的','uk :iˈliːt, us :iˈliːt','[the country\'s educated elite \n 这个国家受过良好教育的精英 \n, a member of the elite \n 上层集团的一员 \n, isapproving \n A powerful and corrupt elite has bled this country dry. \n 该国专权腐败的权贵阶层榨干了人民的血汗。 \n, Elite troops were airlifted to the trouble zone. \n 精锐部队被空运到骚乱地区。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeli/ukelimi005.mp3'),('elysium','极其美好；天堂','uk :iˈlɪz.i.əm, us :iˈlɪz.i.əm','[Everything was perfect. She was in Elysium. \n 对她来说一切都是那么完美，就好像在天堂一样。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukelu/ukeluci008.mp3'),('emaciated','（通常由于疾病或极度饥饿）消瘦的，憔悴的，虚弱的','uk :iˈmeɪ.si.eɪ.tɪd, us :iˈmeɪ.si.eɪ.t̬ɪd','[There were pictures of emaciated children on the cover of the magazine. \n 杂志封面上是几幅骨瘦如柴的儿童的照片。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukelu/ukeluci010.mp3'),('emblem','象征；标志；符号；徽章','uk :ˈem.bləm, us :ˈem.bləm','[A rose is the national emblem of England. \n 玫瑰是英格兰的标志。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukemb/ukembar015.mp3'),('eminent','显赫的；卓越的；著名的','uk :ˈem.ɪ.nənt, us :ˈem.ə.nənt',NULL,'2020-01-20',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukemb/ukembry021.mp3'),('emission','（气体、热量、光线等的）排放，散发，射出排放物；散发物','uk :iˈmɪʃ.ən, us :iˈmɪʃ.ən','[Environmental groups want a substantial reduction in the emission of greenhouse gases. \n 环保组织要求切实减少温室气体的排放量。 \n, carbon dioxide emissions \n 二氧化碳的排放 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukemb/ukembry027.mp3'),('enchant','使陶醉；使入迷对…施魔法','uk :ɪnˈtʃɑːnt, us :ɪnˈtʃænt','[The audience was clearly enchanted by her performance. \n 观众显然陶醉于她的演出中。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukenc/ukencas002.mp3'),('encrust','cover or decorate (something) with a hard surface layer','/ɪnˈkrʌst,ɛnˈkrʌst/','null\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'null'),('endurance','忍耐力，耐受力','uk :ɪnˈdʒʊə.rəns, us :ɪnˈdʊr.əns','[Running a marathon is a test of human endurance. \n 马拉松长跑是对人耐力的考验。 \n, The pain was bad beyond endurance. \n 疼痛剧烈，令人难以忍受。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukenc/ukencum028.mp3'),('entail','使必要；牵涉','uk :ɪnˈteɪl, us :ɪnˈteɪl','[Such a large investment inevitably entails some risk. \n 这样的巨额投资必然会有一定的风险。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n Repairing the roof will entail spending a lot of money. \n 修房顶免不了要花好多钱。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukens/ukensla007.mp3'),('enterocolitis','小肠结肠炎','ˌentərōkəˈlītis','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('enveloped','覆盖；包住；围绕；笼罩','uk :ɪnˈvel.əp, us :ɪnˈvel.əp','[The graveyard looked ghostly, enveloped in mist. \n 墓地笼罩在薄雾中，显得阴森森的。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukent/ukentre012.mp3'),('enzyme','酶','uk :ˈen.zaɪm, us :ˈen.zaɪm','[An enzyme in the saliva of the mouth starts the process of breaking down the food. \n 由于唾液中酶的作用，食物进入口腔时就开始了分解过程。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukent/ukentre029.mp3'),('epidemic','（疾病的）流行，传染泛滥；蔓延流行的；盛行的；肆虐的','uk :ˌep.ɪˈdem.ɪk, us :ˌep.əˈdem.ɪk','[a flu epidemic \n 流感的传播 \n, a crime/unemployment epidemic \n 犯罪频发／大范围失业 \n, Poverty in this country has reached epidemic proportions . \n 这个国家很多人处于贫困之中。 \n, Crime and poverty are epidemic in the city. \n 犯罪和贫穷如瘟疫一般在这个城市肆虐。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukepe/ukepee_010.mp3'),('epidemiology','流行病学的','uk :ˌep.ɪ.diː.miˈɒl.ə.dʒi, us :ˌep.ə.diːmiˈɑː.lə.dʒi','[]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd10/epd10065.mp3'),('episode','事件；（相关的）一连串事件；一段经历（尤指电视或广播节目的）一集，一节，片断','uk :ˈep.ɪ.səʊd, us :ˈep.ə.soʊd','[This latest episode in the fraud scandal has shocked a lot of people. \n 诈骗丑闻最新爆出的这一事件让很多人瞠目结舌。 \n, The drugs, the divorce, and the depression - it s an episode in his life that he wants to forget. \n 吸毒、离婚和消沉——这是他人生中不堪回首的一段经历。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukepe/ukepee_023.mp3'),('equity','（公司的）股本，股票值；股票资产净值公平；公正（英语国家的一种司法制度，允许在现存法律不适用时对案件作出公正判决的）衡平法','uk :ˈek.wɪ.ti, us :ˈek.wə.t̬i','[He sold his equity in the company last year. \n 他去年卖掉了这家公司的股票。 \n, The rights give holders the opportunity to purchase additional equity interests in the company at a big discount. \n 这些权利使得股票持有者有机会以很优惠的折扣价额外购买该公司股份。 \n, a society based on equity and social justice \n 建立在公平公正和社会正义基础之上的社会 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukequ/ukequip004.mp3'),('errand','（短程）差事；跑腿','uk :ˈer.ənd, us :ˈer.ənd','[I ll meet you at six, I ve got some errands to do/run first. \n 我会在6点和你见面，我得先去办些事情。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukero/ukeroge008.mp3'),('establishment','企业；机构；单位（尤指支持维持现状的）当权派，统治集团，权势集团建立；创立','uk :ɪˈstæb.lɪʃ.mənt, us :ɪˈstæb.lɪʃ.mənt',NULL,'2020-02-14',1,4,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukesq/ukesq__010.mp3'),('estate','（位于乡村的）大片私有土地，庄园，种植园（个人死后留下的全部）财产，遗产（按规划建造的）住宅区，工业区旅游汽车；客货两用轿车状况；状态','uk :ɪˈsteɪt, us :ɪˈsteɪt','[It s a typical country estate with a large house for the owner, farm buildings, and estate workers  houses. \n 这是一个典型的乡村庄园，建有主人的大宅子、许多农舍以及庄园工人的住处。 \n, She left her entire estate to her niece. \n 她把所有的遗产都留给了自己的侄女。 \n, a housing estate \n 住宅区 \n, an industrial estate (= a group of factories) \n 工业区 \n, the holy estate of marriage \n 婚姻的神圣性 \n]\n','2020-02-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukesq/ukesq__011.mp3'),('ethereal','轻飘的，缥缈的；优雅的；（尤指）超凡的','uk :iˈθɪə.ri.əl, us :iˈθɪr.i.əl','[an ethereal being \n 精灵 \n, ethereal beauty \n 超凡的美 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukete/uketern005.mp3'),('evade','逃脱，躲开；回避，逃避回避议题／问题（等等）','uk :ɪˈveɪd, us :ɪˈveɪd','[The police have assured the public that the escaped prisoners will not evade recapture for long. \n 警方向公众保证，逃犯很快就会再次落网。 \n, She leaned forward to kiss him but he evaded her by pretending to sneeze. \n 她身子前倾想要吻他，可他假装打喷嚏躲开了。 \n, An Olympic gold medal is the only thing that has evaded her in her remarkable career. \n 在其辉煌的运动生涯中，唯一没有得到的荣誉就是奥运会金牌。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n He can t evade doing military service forever. \n 他不可能永远逃避服兵役。 \n, Just give me an answer and stop evading the question! \n 直截了当地回答我，不要再回避问题！ \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeur/ukeuro_013.mp3'),('evaluate','评估，评价；估值','uk :ɪˈvæl.ju.eɪt, us :ɪˈvæl.ju.eɪt','[It s impossible to evaluate these results without knowing more about the research methods employed. \n 如不能对使用的研究方法有更多了解，就无法对其结果作出评价。 \n, [ + question word ] \n We shall need to evaluate how the new material stands up to wear and tear. \n 我们需要对新材料的耐磨损度作出鉴定。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeur/ukeuro_014.mp3'),('exclude','阻止…进入；把…排斥在外（有意地）不包括排除…；不考虑…；认为…不可能','uk :ɪkˈskluːd, us :ɪkˈskluːd','[Women are still excluded from the club. \n 这家俱乐部仍然把女性拒之门外。 \n, Microbes must, as far as possible, be excluded from the room during an operation. \n 在手术过程中，要尽可能防止细菌进入手术室。 \n, Tom has been excluded from school (= he is not allowed to go to school) for bad behaviour. \n 汤姆因为行为不端被学校开除了。 \n, The price excludes local taxes. \n 这个价格不包括地方税。 \n, We can t exclude the possibility that he is dead. \n 我们不能排除他已经死亡的可能性。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexc/ukexces020.mp3'),('exemption','免税','uk :ɪɡˈzemp.ʃən, us :ɪɡˈzemp.ʃən','[andidates with a qualification in chemistry have exemption from this course.\n, Organizations may qualify for exemption from income tax if they operate exclusively as charities.\n,  U ] \n He was granted exemption from military service during World War II.\n,  C ] \n a tax exemption\n, xemption from sth \n Formula One was granted an exemption from a ban on tobacco advertising.\n, xemption from doing sth \n Can the parent company claim exemption from preparing a cash flow statement?\n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexc/ukexcre028.mp3'),('exert','运用；行使（权威、权力等）；施加（影响等）用力；尽力；努力','uk :ɪɡˈzɜːt, us :ɪɡˈzɝːt','[If you were to exert your influence they might change their decision. \n 如果你能施加你的影响，他们或许会改变决定。 \n, Some managers exert considerable pressure on their staff to work extra hours without being paid. \n 一些老板向员工施加巨大的压力迫使他们无偿加班。 \n, I was too tired to exert myself. \n 我太累了，心有余而力不足。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexe/ukexert001.mp3'),('exhausted','极其疲惫的；精疲力竭的','uk :ɪɡˈzɔː.stɪd, us :ɪɡˈzɑː.stɪd','[Exhausted, they fell asleep. \n 他们精疲力尽，倒头就睡。 \n, By the time they reached the summit they were exhausted. \n 他们登到山顶时，已经精疲力竭了。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexe/ukexert010.mp3'),('exhibit','展出，展览；展示展品；展出物；陈列品（一批）展品，展览（法庭上出示的）证据，物证','uk :ɪɡˈzɪb.ɪt, us :ɪɡˈzɪb.ɪt','[He frequently exhibits at the art gallery. \n 他经常在艺术馆展出作品。 \n, In the summer the academy will exhibit several prints that are rarely seen. \n 该学会将于今年夏天对外展出几幅罕见的版画作品。 \n, He exhibited great self-control considering her rudeness. \n 她那么无礼，他表现出如此的克制力已很不错了。 \n, The museum has a fascinating collection of exhibits ranging from Iron Age pottery to Inuit clothing. \n 这个博物馆收藏的展品，从铁器时代的陶器，到因纽特人的衣物，丰富多彩，令人称奇。 \n, Let\'s go see the new dinosaur exhibit. \n 我们去看这个有关恐龙的新展览吧。 \n, Is exhibit C the weapon that you say was used? \n 物证C是不是你说的所使用的武器？ \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexe/ukexert016.mp3'),('expire','到期，期满；结束逝世，亡故','uk :ɪkˈspaɪər, us :ɪkˈspaɪr','[My passport expires next month. \n 我的护照下个月过期。 \n, The contract between the two companies will expire at the end of the year. \n 两公司之间的合同将在年底到期。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexp/ukexper014.mp3'),('exploit','利用；开发；发挥（出于私利）利用；剥削不寻常的行为；英勇的行为；奇遇','uk :ɪkˈsplɔɪt, us :ɪkˈsplɔɪt','[We need to make sure that we exploit our resources as fully as possible. \n 我们需要确保尽可能充分利用资源。 \n, Laws exist to stop companies exploiting their employees. \n 法律规定禁止公司剥削其员工。 \n, She was telling me about her exploits while travelling around Africa. \n 她跟我讲述了她在非洲各地旅游时的奇遇。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexp/ukexper030.mp3'),('extreme','极大的；极度的；极端的极严厉的；严重的；极糟的（信仰或政党）偏激的，过激的，极端的末端的，尽头的；（尤指）离中心最远的极度；极端（用于强调）极其，非常，极度极端；极端不同的事物','uk :ɪkˈstriːm, us :ɪkˈstriːm',NULL,'2020-01-07',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukext/ukextra024.mp3'),('exude','明显地流露，充分显露（爱、自信、痛苦等）散发；渗出，流出','uk :ɪɡˈzjuːd, us :ɪɡˈzuːd','[She just exudes confidence. \n 她显得信心十足。 \n, Some trees exude from their bark a sap that repels insect parasites. \n 一些树的树皮会分泌出一种汁液来驱除寄生在树上的昆虫。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukext/ukextri008.mp3'),('facial','面部的，脸上的面部美容护理','uk :ˈfeɪ.ʃəl, us :ˈfeɪ.ʃəl','[facial hair \n 脸部汗毛 \n, facial cleansers and moisturizers \n 面部清洁和保湿用品 \n, facial expressions \n 面部表情 \n, Beauty treatments range from an eyelash tint at £8 to a deep cleansing facial costing £80. \n 美容护理项目包括从收费8英镑的染睫毛到收费80英镑的面部深层清洁 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeye/ukeyeto025.mp3'),('fad','一时的风尚；短暂的狂热','uk :fæd, us :fæd','[the latest health fad \n 最新健康时尚 \n, K \n There was a fad for wearing ripped jeans a few years ago. \n 几年前有一阵子流行穿有洞的牛仔裤。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfac/ukfacin016.mp3'),('fade','（使）褪色；（使）变暗；（使）衰弱','uk :feɪd, us :feɪd','[If you hang your clothes out in the bright sun, they will fade. \n 衣服挂在光线强的地方晾晒会褪色。 \n, My suntan is already fading. \n 我晒黑的肤色已经开始变浅了。 \n, They arrived home just as the light was fading (= as it was getting dark). \n 天色变暗时，他们到家了。 \n, The sun had faded the blue walls. \n 太阳把蓝色的墙晒褪了色。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfac/ukfacin025.mp3'),('faint','微弱的；不清晰的；微小的根本不知道虚弱无力；感到眩晕；快要晕倒似的昏厥；晕倒昏厥；晕倒','uk :feɪnt, us :feɪnt','[a faint sound/noise/smell \n 微弱的声音／隐约的响声／淡淡的气味 \n, The lamp gave out a faint glow. \n 灯发出微弱的光。 \n, She gave me a faint smile of recognition. \n 她认出了我，冲我淡淡一笑。 \n, There s not the faintest hope of ever finding him. \n 没有丝毫找到他的希望。 \n, She bears a faint resemblance to my sister. \n 她和我姐姐长得有点儿像。 \n, I have a faint suspicion that you may be right! \n 我隐约觉得你可能是对的！ \n,  Is she going to stay?   I haven t the faintest idea.  \n “她要留下来吗？我一点儿也不知道。” \n, I don t have the faintest idea what you re talking about! \n 我根本不知道你在说什么！ \n, She felt faint with hunger. \n 她饿得头昏眼花。 \n, He faints at the sight of blood. \n 他一见血就晕。 \n, I nearly fainted in the heat. \n 我差点热晕过去。 \n, She took one look at the hypodermic needle and fainted (dead) away (= became unconscious immediately). \n 她一眼看到注射针头就昏了过去。 \n, On receiving the news, she fell into a dead faint. \n 听到消息，她昏死过去。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfag/ukfagge009.mp3'),('faith','信任；信心（某一）宗教宗教信仰','uk :feɪθ, us :feɪθ','[She has no faith in modern medicine. \n 她对现代医学没有信心。 \n, You ll cope - I have great faith in you. \n 你能应付得了——我对你很有信心。 \n, After the trial, his family said they had lost all faith in the judicial system. \n 审判之后，他的家人说，他们对司法体系已完全丧失信心。 \n, Politicians must start keeping their promises if they want to restore the people s faith in government. \n 如果政治人物想恢复人们对政府的信任，他们必须开始信守承诺。 \n, the Muslim/Christian/Jewish/Buddhist faith \n 伊斯兰教／基督教／犹太教／佛教 \n, They were persecuted for their faith. \n 他们因宗教信仰而遭受迫害。 \n, He was forced to practise his faith in secret. \n 他被迫对自己的宗教信仰保密。 \n, a multi-faith society \n 宗教信仰多元化的社会 \n, They were brought up in the true faith (= the religion which the speaker believes is the only true one). \n 他们在正统的宗教熏陶下长大。 \n, Even in the bad times she never lost her faith. \n 即使在困难时期，她也从未丧失信仰。 \n, Her faith in God was shattered when her baby died. \n 她的孩子死后，她对上帝的信仰破灭了。 \n, It s my faith that keeps me going. \n 是我的信仰在推动我前进。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfag/ukfagge021.mp3'),('fanciest','想要；想做爱慕，喜欢自认为是；自命不凡想象；认为（表示惊讶）真想不到！装饰的；花哨的；繁复的昂贵的；豪华的一时的兴趣（或爱好）喜欢上，爱上吸引…，中…的意想象（力）','uk :ˈfæn.si, us :ˈfæn.si','[Do you fancy a drink this evening? \n 你今晚想喝一杯吗？ \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n I didn t fancy swimming in that water. \n 我不想在那水里游泳。 \n, He could tell she fancied him. \n 他看得出她喜欢他。 \n, That Dave really fancies himself, doesn t he? \n 那个戴夫挺自命不凡的，是吧？ \n, He fancies himself as a bit of a singer. \n 他认为自己多少是个歌手。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n Who do you fancy to win the Cup this year? \n 你认为今年谁会赢得杯赛？ \n, [ + (that) ] \n literary \n I fancied (that) I saw something moving in the corner. \n 我觉得看见角落里有东西在动。 \n, ld-fashioned \n This isn t the first time this has happened, I fancy. \n 我想，这不是第一次发生这种事了。 \n, Fancy seeing you here! \n 没想到在这里遇见你！ \n,  They have eight children.   Fancy that (= how surprising)!  \n “他们有8个孩子。”“真想不到啊！” \n, I wanted a simple black dress, nothing fancy. \n 我想要一件简洁的黑色礼服，不要花哨的东西。 \n, The decorations were a little too fancy for my tastes. \n 这种装饰风格过于繁复，不合我的喜好。 \n, fancy cakes \n 花式蛋糕 \n, We stayed in a fancy hotel near the Champs-Élysées. \n 我们住在香榭丽舍大街附近一家豪华的酒店里。 \n, a fancy restaurant \n 豪华餐厅 \n, But for me, parachuting was no passing fancy. \n 但是对我来说，跳伞可不是一时的兴趣。 \n, Laura s taken a fancy to Japanese food. \n 劳拉喜欢上了日本料理。 \n, I looked in a lot of clothes shops but nothing really tickled my fancy. \n 我逛了很多服装店，但没什么衣服让我中意。 \n, She has enough money to buy anything that strikes her fancy. \n 她有足够的钱想买什么就买什么。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfal/ukfalsi025.mp3'),('fanciful','空想的；想象的','uk :ˈfæn.sɪ.fəl, us :ˈfæn.sɪ.fəl','[He has some fanciful notion about converting one room of his apartment into a gallery. \n 他幻想把他公寓的一间房间改成画廊。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfal/ukfalsi023.mp3'),('fancy','想要；想做爱慕，喜欢自认为是；自命不凡想象；认为（表示惊讶）真想不到！装饰的；花哨的；繁复的昂贵的；豪华的一时的兴趣（或爱好）喜欢上，爱上吸引…，中…的意想象（力）','uk :ˈfæn.si, us :ˈfæn.si','[Do you fancy a drink this evening? \n 你今晚想喝一杯吗？ \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n I didn t fancy swimming in that water. \n 我不想在那水里游泳。 \n, He could tell she fancied him. \n 他看得出她喜欢他。 \n, That Dave really fancies himself, doesn t he? \n 那个戴夫挺自命不凡的，是吧？ \n, He fancies himself as a bit of a singer. \n 他认为自己多少是个歌手。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n Who do you fancy to win the Cup this year? \n 你认为今年谁会赢得杯赛？ \n, [ + (that) ] \n literary \n I fancied (that) I saw something moving in the corner. \n 我觉得看见角落里有东西在动。 \n, ld-fashioned \n This isn t the first time this has happened, I fancy. \n 我想，这不是第一次发生这种事了。 \n, Fancy seeing you here! \n 没想到在这里遇见你！ \n,  They have eight children.   Fancy that (= how surprising)!  \n “他们有8个孩子。”“真想不到啊！” \n, I wanted a simple black dress, nothing fancy. \n 我想要一件简洁的黑色礼服，不要花哨的东西。 \n, The decorations were a little too fancy for my tastes. \n 这种装饰风格过于繁复，不合我的喜好。 \n, fancy cakes \n 花式蛋糕 \n, We stayed in a fancy hotel near the Champs-Élysées. \n 我们住在香榭丽舍大街附近一家豪华的酒店里。 \n, a fancy restaurant \n 豪华餐厅 \n, But for me, parachuting was no passing fancy. \n 但是对我来说，跳伞可不是一时的兴趣。 \n, Laura s taken a fancy to Japanese food. \n 劳拉喜欢上了日本料理。 \n, I looked in a lot of clothes shops but nothing really tickled my fancy. \n 我逛了很多服装店，但没什么衣服让我中意。 \n, She has enough money to buy anything that strikes her fancy. \n 她有足够的钱想买什么就买什么。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfal/ukfalsi025.mp3'),('fare','车费；车票价出租车乘客（餐馆的）饭菜成功；遭遇','uk :feər, us :fer','[Train fares are going up again. \n 火车票又涨价了。 \n, How did you fare in your exams? \n 你考得怎么样？ \n, Low-paid workers will fare badly/well under this government. \n 在这届政府执政期间，低收入工人的境况会很糟／很好。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfag/ukfagge012.mp3'),('fatal','致命的灾难性的；毁灭性的','uk :ˈfeɪ.təl, us :ˈfeɪ.t̬əl','[This illness is fatal in almost all cases. \n 这种病几乎是不治之症。 \n, the fatal shooting of an unarmed 15-year-old \n 对手无寸铁的15岁少年的致命枪击 \n, He made the fatal mistake/error of believing what they told him. \n 他听信了他们的话，犯了致命的错误。 \n, It just shows how you should never say how well things are going for you - it s fatal (= it causes bad things to happen). \n 这件事恰恰说明你决不能说事情进展很顺利——这么讲会带来大麻烦。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfar/ukfarth025.mp3'),('fella','伙计；小伙子；哥们儿男性伴侣；男朋友','uk :ˈfel.ə, us :ˈfel.ə','[There were a couple of fellas leaning up by the bar. \n 有几个小伙子斜倚在吧台边。 \n, Was she with her fella? \n 她和男朋友在一起吗？ \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfee/ukfeed_019.mp3'),('financial','财务的；财政的；金融的','uk :faɪˈnæn.ʃəl, us :faɪˈnæn.ʃəl','[financial difficulties/success \n 财政困难／经济上的成功 \n, financial affairs \n 金融事务 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfin/ukfinan003.mp3'),('firm','结实的；坚固的牢固的；稳固的坚决的；坚定的强有力的；紧紧的，牢牢的确定的；坚定不移的严格的，强硬的公司；商号使（土）变硬；使（土）坚实稳定下来；保持不变','uk :fɜːm, us :fɝːm','[I d rather sleep on a firm mattress than a soft one. \n 我宁愿睡硬床垫，也不要软的。 \n, These pears are still too firm to eat. \n 这些梨还太硬，没法吃。 \n, The bridge provided a firm platform for the bungee jumpers. \n 这座桥为蹦极者提供了稳固的平台。 \n, The government remains firm in its opposition to tax reform. \n 政府仍坚决反对税收改革。 \n, a firm handshake \n 强有力的握手 \n, Keep a firm hold of the handrail as you go down. \n 下去时要牢牢抓住扶手。 \n, igurative \n No one seems to have a firm grip on the company at the moment. \n 目前似乎没有人能牢牢掌控公司。 \n, igurative \n You need a firm grasp of mathematics to become an astronaut. \n 要成为宇航员，数学知识必须非常扎实。 \n, He is a firm believer in traditional family values. \n 他坚信应遵循传统的家庭价值观念。 \n, Some people still claim that there is no firm evidence linking smoking with lung cancer. \n 有人仍声称没有确凿的证据表明吸烟与肺癌有关。 \n, I was always very firm with my children - they knew the rules and I made sure they followed them. \n 我对孩子们总是很严格——他们知道规矩，我则监督他们守规矩。 \n, He works for a law firm called Neil and Vigliano. \n 他在一家名为尼尔和维利亚诺的律师事务所供职。 \n, He s just started working for an accountancy firm/a firm of accountants in Cambridge. \n 他刚刚开始在剑桥的一家会计师事务所工作。 \n, Firm the soil around the cuttings and water them in. \n 把插条四周的土压实，再浇上水。 \n, After a turbulent week on the markets, share prices firmed today. \n 经过一周的市场动荡，股票价格今天稳定下来了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfir/ukfirew004.mp3'),('fizzy','嘶嘶的，起泡的','uk :ˈfɪz.i, us :ˈfɪz.i','[fizzy orange/mineral water \n 起泡橘子水／矿泉水 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfis/ukfistf026.mp3'),('flagpole','旗杆','uk :ˈflæɡ.pəʊl, us :ˈflæɡ.poʊl','[]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfla/ukflacc009.mp3'),('flatfoot','條子','','null\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'null'),('fling','猛扔，猛投，猛掷迅猛移动；猛地做…气呼呼地说，愤怒地说短暂的欢乐时光','uk :flɪŋ, us :flɪŋ','[He crumpled up the letter and flung it into the fire. \n 他把信揉成一团，猛地扔进火中。 \n,  And you can take your ring back too!  she cried, flinging it down on the table. \n “你可以把你的戒指也拿走！”她喊道，猛地把戒指摔到桌子上。 \n, K informal \n Could you fling the paper over here (= give me the paper)? \n 你能把报纸丢过来吗？ \n, She flung her arms around his neck. \n 她猛地搂住他的脖子。 \n, The door was flung open by the wind. \n 风把门猛地吹开了。 \n, Sergei flung himself down on the sofa. \n 谢尔盖猛地扑倒在沙发上。 \n, K informal \n Let me just fling (= quickly put) a few things into my bag, and I ll be right with you. \n 让我往包里塞几样东西，马上就跟你去。 \n, K informal \n They were flung (= quickly put) in prison. \n 他们很快被投入监狱。 \n, They were flinging bitter accusations at each other. \n 他们彼此破口大骂。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  I don t care what you think , she flung (back) at him. \n “我不在乎你怎么想，”她气呼呼地回敬他道。 \n, The girls are going to the beach for one last fling before the end of summer. \n 姑娘们要去海滩享受夏季结束前最后一段短暂的欢乐时光。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfli/ukflick017.mp3'),('flip','（使）快速翻转；迅速翻动翻烤（食物）迅速转售（稍作装修后的房子）以获取利润翻动，翻转（flippant的非正式说法）“不！”（感叹词，表示愠怒）','uk :flɪp, us :flɪp','[I flipped the book (over) to look at the back cover. \n 我很快地把书翻过去看了看封底。 \n, I lost my place in my book when the pages flipped over in the wind. \n 风把书页吹乱了，我找不到正在看的那个地方了。 \n, You turn the machine on by flipping (= operating) the switch on the side. \n 把边上的开关按一下，机器就启动了。 \n, The captains flipped a coin into the air (= made it turn over in the air to see which side it landed on) to decide which side would bat first. \n 两队队长向空中抛出一枚硬币，决定哪一方先击球。 \n, I don t want to spend the rest of my life flipping burgers. \n 我可不想一辈子都翻烤汉堡。 \n, I am going to take three weeks  vacation and flip this house. \n 我要休假三个星期，稍微装修一下这个房子然后卖掉。 \n, a flip of a coin \n 抛硬币 \n, The acrobats were doing somersaults and flips (= jumping and turning their bodies over in the air). \n 杂技演员们正在翻筋斗和空翻。 \n, Oh, flip, I ve missed the bus. \n 哦不！我错过公交车了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfli/ukflick020.mp3'),('flock','>羊群；鸟群；人群>（特定类型的）一群人>（充填垫子等的）软填料；（在墙纸或窗帘上制作凸起图案用的）短绒，绒屑>聚集；蜂拥>用软材料覆盖表面装饰','uk :>flɒk, us :>flɑːk',NULL,'2020-02-13',5,10,1,NULL),('flout','公然藐视，无视，违背（规定、法律或习俗）','uk :flaʊt, us :flaʊt','[Many motorcyclists flout the law by not wearing helmets. \n 许多骑摩托车的人无视法律，不戴头盔。 \n, The orchestra decided to flout convention/tradition, and wear their everyday clothes for the concert. \n 管弦乐队决定一改传统，在音乐会上穿日常服装。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflo/ukflori020.mp3'),('fluent','（指人说某种语言）流利的（语言）讲得流利的','uk :ˈfluː.ənt, us :','[She s fluent in French. \n 她的法语很流利。 \n, He s a fluent Russian speaker. \n 他的俄语讲得很流利。 \n, He speaks fluent Chinese. \n 他汉语讲得很流利。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukfluct004.mp3'),('fluid','液体；流质流畅的（情况、想法或计划）不固定的，易变的','uk :ˈfluː.ɪd, us :ˈfluː.ɪd','[If you have a fever you should drink plenty of fluids. \n 如果发烧，应多喝流质。 \n, power steering fluid \n 助力转向液 \n, The virus is contracted through exchange of bodily fluids (= liquids, such as blood, that come from the human body). \n 这种病毒通过体液感染。 \n, fluid movements \n 流畅的动作 \n, The military situation is still very fluid. \n 军事局势依然很不稳定。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukfluct009.mp3'),('flustered','心烦意乱的；慌张的；紧张的','uk :ˈflʌs.təd, us :ˈflʌs.tɚd','[She seemed a little flustered. \n 她似乎有点儿紧张。 \n, If I look flustered it s because I m trying to do so many things at once. \n 如果我看上去很慌乱，那是因为我正试图同时做很多件事情。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukflush003.mp3'),('flutter','（使）飘动，挥动，颤动；拍（翅）；鼓（翼）（心）怦怦乱跳；（胃）颤动一阵兴奋（或激动）（尤指赛马中的）小赌注振动；颤动；忽闪','uk :ˈflʌt.ər, us :ˈflʌt̬.ɚ','[Brightly coloured flags were fluttering in the breeze. \n 鲜艳的彩旗在微风中飘扬。 \n, Leaves fluttered down onto the path. \n 树叶飘落到小径上。 \n, Butterflies fluttered about in the sunshine. \n 蝴蝶在阳光下翩翩飞舞。 \n, A white bird poised on a wire and fluttered its wings. \n 一只白鸟立在电线上，扑打着翅膀。 \n, Every time I think about my exams my stomach flutters! \n 每次一想到考试，我心里就不舒服！ \n, The publication of her first novel last spring caused a flutter of excitement. \n 去年秋天她的第一部小说出版后引起一阵轰动。 \n, Auntie Paula likes to have a bit of a flutter on the horses. \n 葆拉姨妈喜欢在赛马上下一点儿小赌注。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukflush007.mp3'),('flux','不断的变动，不停的变化（助）熔剂','uk :flʌks, us :flʌks','[Our plans are in a state of flux at the moment. \n 我们的计划目前处在不断变化之中。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukflush009.mp3'),('foe','敌人地球之友（一个国际环保组织，Friends of the Earth的缩写）','uk :fəʊ, us :foʊ','[The two countries have united against their common foe. \n 两国联合起来对抗共同的敌人。 \n, They were bitter foes for many years. \n 他们结仇多年。 \n, Foes of the government will be delighting in its current difficulties. \n 政府的敌人会对政府目前的困难处境幸灾乐祸。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfob/ukfob__009.mp3'),('foldaway','可折叠的；折叠式的','uk :ˈfəʊld.ə.weɪ, us :ˈfoʊld.ə.weɪ','[a foldaway bed \n 折叠床 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfob/ukfob__021.mp3'),('foremost','最重要的；最佳的；领先的','uk :ˈfɔː.məʊst, us :ˈfɔːr.moʊst','[This is one of the country s foremost arts centres. \n 这是全国最重要的艺术中心之一。 \n, She s one of the foremost experts on child psychology. \n 她是儿童心理学领域最顶尖的专家之一。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukforef019.mp3'),('formula','惯例；配方；处方公式，方程式分子式（婴儿）配方奶','uk :ˈfɔː.mjə.lə, us :ˈfɔːr.mjə.lə',NULL,'2020-01-07',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukforgi030.mp3'),('fortified','（尤指为防御而）加强，增强','uk :ˈfɔː.tɪ.faɪ, us :ˈfɔːr.t̬ə.faɪ','[a fortified town \n 设防的城镇 \n, They hurriedly fortified the village with barricades of carts. \n 他们匆忙用马车搭起路障，加强村子的防御。 \n, The argument had fortified her resolve to prove she was right. \n 这番争论增强了她证明自己正确的决心。 \n, He fortified himself with a drink and a sandwich before driving on. \n 继续开车之前，他喝了杯饮料吃了块三明治来增强体力。 \n, a fruit drink fortified with vitamin C (= with vitamin C added) \n 添加了维生素C的果汁饮料 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukformu028.mp3'),('foundation','>创建；建立>基金会>（幼儿学校）小班>地基；房基>无根据>（化妆打底用的）粉底霜','uk :>faʊnˈdeɪ.ʃ, us :>faʊnˈdeɪ.ʃ',NULL,'2020-01-07',1,2,0,NULL),('fountain','泉水；（尤指具有装饰效果的）喷泉','uk :ˈfaʊn.tɪn, us :ˈfaʊn.tɪn','[]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukfortn030.mp3'),('fountain-pen','钢笔','Gāngbǐ','\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=fountain-pen&tl=ja&tk=617265.1007429&client=webapp&prev=input'),('foyer','（剧院、宾馆等公共建筑物入口处内的）门厅（房子或公寓的）门廊，前厅','uk :ˈfɔɪ.eɪ, us :ˈfɔɪ.ɚ','[I ll see you downstairs in the foyer in half an hour. \n 我们半个小时以后在楼下门厅见。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfou/ukfours014.mp3'),('fragile','易损坏的；易碎的；脆弱的','uk :ˈfrædʒ.aɪl, us :ˈfrædʒ.əl','[Be careful with that vase - it s very fragile. \n 拿那只花瓶要小心——它很容易碎。 \n, The assassination could do serious damage to the fragile peace agreement that was signed last month. \n 这起行刺事件可能会对上月签署的脆弱的和平协定造成严重损害。 \n, I felt rather fragile (= weak) for a few days after the operation. \n 手术后几天内我感觉自己非常虚弱。 \n, K humorous \n No breakfast for me, thanks - I m feeling a little fragile (= ill, upset, or tired) after last night s party. \n 我不吃早餐了，谢谢——昨晚聚会后到现在我还觉得很不舒服。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfou/ukfours025.mp3'),('fragility','脆弱性','uk :frəˈdʒɪl.ə.ti, us :frəˈdʒɪl.ə.t̬i','[ deficiency of copper can cause increased bone fragility.\n, The fragility of donor hearts, livers and other organs means they are usually transported by air. \n, he collapse of the bank is an ominous reminder of the fragility of the world\'s banking system.\n, The latest violence has underlined the fragility of the region\'s security.\n, ragility of sth \n It had been a difficult year and the fragility of the economy could make the situation worse.\n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfou/ukfours026.mp3'),('fragment','小片，小块；（尤指）碎片，碎块（使）支离破碎；打碎；（使）分裂','uk :ˈfræɡ.mənt, us :ˈfræɡ.mənt','[The road was covered with fragments of glass from the shattered window. \n 公路上到处是车窗的碎玻璃片。 \n, Literary scholars are piecing together her last unpublished novel from fragments of a recently discovered manuscript. \n 文学研究者们正在把最近发现的她最后一部未发表小说的手稿残片一点点拼凑起来。 \n, The satellite will fragment and burn up as it falls through the earth s atmosphere. \n 卫星坠经地球大气层时会碎裂起火，化为灰烬。 \n, His day was fragmented by meetings and phone calls. \n 他一天的时间因为各种会议和电话而变得支离破碎。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfou/ukfours027.mp3'),('fraud','诈骗（罪）骗子；骗人的事物','uk :frɔːd, us :frɑːd','[credit card fraud \n 信用卡诈骗 \n, He is fighting extradition to Hong Kong to face trial on fraud charges. \n 他正在力争免于被引渡到香港就诈骗指控接受审判。 \n, She was a psychic who was later revealed to be a fraud. \n 她是一个通灵巫师，后来被发现是个骗子。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfra/ukfrate006.mp3'),('fray','（使）（布料或绳子）磨损，（使）磨散（渐渐地）烦躁，恼火（常指乱糟糟的）干劲十足的努力，充满活力的活动；激战；激烈争吵','uk :freɪ, us :freɪ','[Denim frays so easily. \n 劳动布很容易磨损。 \n, I frayed the edges of my jeans since that was the fashion in those days. \n 我把牛仔裤的边儿磨毛了，在那个时代这样很时髦。 \n, Tempers frayed as thousands of drivers began the Christmas holiday with long waits in traffic jams. \n 圣诞假期一开始就有数千人开着车排成长龙拥堵在道路上，令大家恼火不已。 \n, With a third country about to enter (= take part in) the fray, the fighting looks set to continue. \n 由于有第三国要加入冲突，战斗看来很可能会继续下去。 \n, A good holiday should leave you feeling refreshed and ready for the fray (= ready to work) again. \n 好好度一个假应该能使人感到精神振奋，为重新投入忙碌的工作作好准备。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfra/ukfrate013.mp3'),('frenzy','疯狂，狂热，狂暴','uk :ˈfren.zi, us :ˈfren.zi','[In a frenzy of rage she hit him. \n 她盛怒之下打了他。 \n, the media frenzy over the celebrity wedding \n 媒体对公众人物婚礼表现出的极大兴趣 \n, The audience worked/whipped themselves into a frenzy as they waited for her to come on stage. \n 观众在期待她登上舞台的过程中情绪变得狂热起来。 \n, There was a frenzy of activity in the financial markets yesterday. \n 昨天金融市场极度活跃。 \n, In a moment of jealous frenzy, she cut the sleeves off all his shirts. \n 她嫉妒得发疯，把他所有的衬衫袖子都剪掉了。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfre/ukfrene003.mp3'),('friction','摩擦力；摩擦（观点不同者之间的）摩擦，不和','uk :ˈfrɪk.ʃən, us :ˈfrɪk.ʃən','[When you rub your hands together the friction produces heat. \n 揉搓双手时，摩擦会产生热量。 \n, There\'s a lot of friction between my wife and my mother. \n 我妻子和我母亲之间有很多龃龉。 \n, Politics is a source of considerable friction in our family. \n 政治问题在我们家是矛盾的一大根源。 \n, Border clashes have led to increased friction between the two countries. \n 边境冲突引发了两国间更大的摩擦。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfri/ukfrica002.mp3'),('frontier','国境，边境（十九世纪时定居者开始搬入并居住的美国西部）前沿地带','uk :ˈfrʌn.tɪər, us :frʌnˈtɪr','[Some of the frontier between Germany and Poland follows the course of the river Oder. \n 德国与波兰的部分边界是沿奥德河划分的。 \n, Nepal has frontiers with both India and China. \n 尼泊尔与中国和印度都接壤。 \n, They lived in a town close to the frontier. \n 他们居住在一个离边界很近的城镇。 \n, The Homestead Act of 1862 gave free land to pioneers who settled the frontier. \n 1862年的《宅地法》免费把土地给予到西部前沿地区定居的先驱者。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfro/ukfrom_009.mp3'),('fundamental','基础的，基本的主要的，根本的','uk :ˌfʌn.dəˈmen.təl, us :ˌfʌn.dəˈmen.t̬əl','[We need to make fundamental changes to the way in which we treat our environment. \n 我们需要从根本上改变对待环境的态度。 \n, It s one of the fundamental differences between men and women. \n 这是男女之间的基本差别之一。 \n, The school is based on the fundamental principle that all children should reach their full potential. \n 这所学校的基本原则是充分发挥每个孩子的最大潜力。 \n, Diversity is of fundamental importance to all ecosystems and all economies. \n 多样性对所有的生态系统和经济结构都极为重要。 \n, Some understanding of grammar is fundamental to learning a language. \n 掌握一些语法对学习一种语言来说很重要。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfum/ukfumes013.mp3'),('funeral','葬礼，丧礼','uk :ˈfjuː.nər.əl, us :ˈfjuː.nɚ.əl','[The funeral will be held next Friday. \n 葬礼将在下周五举行。 \n, Over 300 mourners attended the funeral. \n 300多名哀悼者参加了葬礼。 \n, a funeral procession \n 送葬的队伍 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfum/ukfumes020.mp3'),('gastrointestinal','胃肠（里）的；与肠胃相关的','uk :ˌɡæs.trəʊˌɪn.tesˈtaɪ.nəl, us :ˌɡæs.troʊ.ɪnˈtes.tən.əl','[the gastrointestinal tract \n 胃肠道 \n, gastrointestinal bleeding \n 胃肠出血 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd12/epd12072.mp3'),('genre','（尤指艺术的）风格，类型，体裁属于某类型的；按某种风格创作的','uk :ˈʒɑ̃ː.rə, us :ˈʒɑːn.rə','[What genre does the book fall into - comedy or tragedy? \n 这本书属于什么体裁——喜剧还是悲剧？ \n, a literary/musical/film genre \n 文学体裁／音乐风格／电影类型 \n, a genre movie \n 类型电影 \n, genre fiction \n 类型小说 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgen/ukgenit008.mp3'),('geographic','地理的；地理学的','uk :ˌdʒi.əˈɡræf.ɪ.kəl, us :ˌdʒi.əˈɡræf.ɪ.kəl','[a geographical region \n 地理区域 \n, geographical features \n 地理特征 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgeo/ukgeogr002.mp3'),('gist','要旨，要点；大意','uk :dʒɪst, us :dʒɪst','[That was the gist of what he said. \n 那就是他的话的大意。 \n, I think I got (= understood) the gist of what she was saying. \n 我想我明白她说的话的大意了。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgir/ukgiraf020.mp3'),('glance','瞥一眼，迅速地看一眼，扫视闪耀，闪光，闪烁瞥一眼，迅速地看一眼，扫视立刻乍看之下，最初看到时','uk :ɡlɑːns, us :ɡlæns','[She glanced around/round the room to see who was there. \n 她扫视了一眼房间，看看谁在里面。 \n, He glanced up from his book as I passed. \n 我走过的时候，正埋头读书的他抬头瞥了我一眼。 \n, Could you glance over/through this letter and see if it s alright? \n 你能不能看一下这封信，看看写得行不行？ \n, The sunlight glanced on the lake. \n 湖面上波光粼粼。 \n, She took/cast a glance at her watch. \n 她看了一下手表。 \n, He could tell at a glance that something was wrong. \n 他一眼就看出问题了。 \n, At first glance I thought it was a dog (but I was mistaken). \n 乍一看我还以为是一条狗呢（但是我看走眼了）。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgla/ukglaci023.mp3'),('glare','（长久的）怒视，瞪眼刺眼的光发出刺眼的光怒视，瞪眼','uk :ɡleər, us :ɡler','[She gave me a fierce glare. \n 她恶狠狠地瞪了我一眼。 \n, Tinted windows will reduce the glare/the sun s glare. \n 有色玻璃窗会遮挡刺眼的阳光。 \n, This screen gives off a lot of glare. \n 这种屏幕发出的光太刺眼。 \n, The sun was glaring right in my eyes. \n 强烈的阳光直刺我的眼睛。 \n, She glared angrily at everyone and stormed out of the room. \n 她横眉怒目地瞪了大家一眼，气呼呼地冲出房间。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgla/ukglaci027.mp3'),('glimmer','发出微弱的光；隐约闪烁闪烁的微光；微弱的亮光微弱的（好）迹象；一丝，一线','uk :ˈɡlɪm.ər, us :ˈɡlɪm.ɚ','[The lights of the village were glimmering in the distance. \n 远处村庄微弱的灯光时隐时现。 \n, The sky glimmered with stars. \n 天空闪烁着点点星光。 \n, a glimmering candle \n 暗淡摇曳的烛光 \n, We saw a glimmer of light in the distance. \n 我们看到远处有一线微光。 \n, This month s sales figures offer a glimmer of hope for the depressed economy. \n 这个月的销售额给萧条的经济带来一丝希望。 \n, She s never shown a glimmer of interest in classical music. \n 她对古典音乐从没有表现出过一丁点儿兴趣。 \n, The first glimmer of light (= sign of development or understanding) has appeared in the peace talks. \n 和平会谈首次出现了一丝转机。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgla/ukglass026.mp3'),('glove-compartment','（汽車前排座位前面放小物件的）雜物箱','','null\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'null'),('goggling','（由于惊奇）瞪大眼睛看','uk :ˈɡɒɡ.əl, us :ˈɡɑː.ɡəl','[The cathedral was full of goggling tourists. \n 大教堂里挤满了游客，一个个瞪大眼睛，惊奇地看着。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgod/ukgodpa009.mp3'),('goon','（受人雇用的）打手，杀手，暴徒傻瓜，蠢人','uk :ɡuːn, us :ɡuːn','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgon/ukgonad026.mp3'),('grant','（尤指政府为特殊目的给予个人或组织的）拨款，补助金（通常指官方）同意，准予，授予（常指在表达相反的意见之前表示让步）承认，同意认为…是理所当然的视…为理所当然（而不去表示感激）；（认为理所当然而）不去重视…因为','uk :ɡrɑːnt, us :ɡrænt','[a student/research grant \n 助学金／研究拨款 \n, a local authority/government grant \n 当地行政机构／政府拨款 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n They gave/awarded her a grant to study abroad for one year. \n 他们给／授予她一笔奖学金供她出国留学1年。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n They granted her an entry visa. \n 他们发给她入境签证。 \n, He was granted asylum. \n 他的避难请求被接受了。 \n, ormal \n She granted their request/wish. \n 她答应了他们的请求／满足了他们的愿望。 \n, I grant that it must have been upsetting but even so I think she overreacted. \n 我承认这事肯定很让人心烦，但即使是这样，我觉得她也有点小题大做。 \n, I grant you (= it is true that), it s a difficult situation but I feel sure he could have handled it more sensitively. \n 不错，这种局面是很棘手，但是我确实觉得他本可以更加理智地来处理。 \n, I didn t realize that Melanie hadn t been to college - I suppose I just took it for granted. \n 我不知道梅拉妮没上大学——我只是想当然地认为她上过了。 \n, One of the problems with relationships is that after a while you just take each other for granted. \n 恋爱中会遇到的一个问题是，相处一段时间后，双方就都把对方为自己所做的一切当成理所当然。 \n, Granted (that) the story s true, there s not a lot you can do about it. \n 因为这件事情是真的，你实在没有办法做什么。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgrand029.mp3'),('grapple','（尤指为了得到某物而）扭打，搏斗','uk :ˈɡræp.əl, us :ˈɡræp.əl','[The children grappled for the ball. \n 孩子们为了争球打成一团。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgranu019.mp3'),('greenback','美钞','uk :ˈɡriːn.bæk, us :ˈɡriːn.bæk','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgravi026.mp3'),('grit','砂，沙砾，沙粒勇气，毅力（尤指作为早餐的）粗玉米粉，玉米子（为防滑）在（路面上）撒沙砾','uk :ɡrɪt, us :ɡrɪt','[The road had been covered with grit. \n 以前这条路一直铺满沙砾。 \n, It takes true (= real) grit to stand up to a bully. \n 面对一个恃强凌弱者奋起反抗确实需要勇气。 \n, Council lorries had been out gritting the icy roads the night before. \n 政务委员会在头天夜里派出卡车在结冰的路面上撒了沙砾。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgri/ukgrind012.mp3'),('guilty','>内疚的，愧疚的，自责的>有过失的，犯了罪的，有罪责的>有过错的一方；犯罪的一方','uk :>ˈɡɪl.ti, us :>ˈɡɪl.ti',NULL,'2020-02-14',1,5,1,NULL),('gulp','大口地吃（或喝）；（因为害怕、吃惊、激动等）倒吸气，喘不过气来大口大口地吸（气）吞，咽','uk :ɡʌlp, us :ɡʌlp','[She gulped down her drink and made a hasty exit. \n 她大口喝下饮料后急匆匆地出去了。 \n, When it was his turn to dive, he gulped and stepped up onto the diving board. \n 轮到他跳水时，他深吸了一口气后走上跳板。 \n, He swallowed his drink in one gulp. \n 他把杯中的酒一饮而尽。 \n, She rose to the surface of the water once every minute to get/take a gulp of air. \n 她每隔一分钟要把头探出水面吸一大口气。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgui/ukguime016.mp3'),('gum','齿龈，牙龈，牙床树胶，树脂胶，粘合剂口香糖（同 chewing gum）；泡泡糖（同 bubble gum）透明果味糖；胶姆糖；橡皮软糖用胶粘','uk :ɡʌm, us :ɡʌm','[sore gums \n 牙龈疼痛 \n, fruit/wine gums \n 水果胶姆糖／酒胶糖 \n, The labels were already gummed to the envelopes. \n 标签已经粘贴在信封上了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgui/ukguime017.mp3'),('habitually','习惯性地','uk :həˈbɪtʃ.ə.li, us :həˈbɪtʃ.ə.li','[here is something wrong with anyone who is so habitually rude.\n, There were schools where more than half the students were habitually late.\n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgyr/ukgyros012.mp3'),('hail','雹，冰雹（同时抛向某人的）一阵招呼，呼喊下冰雹','uk :heɪl, us :heɪl','[a hail of bullets \n 一阵弹雨 \n, The prime minister was greeted with a hail of insults as she arrived at the university. \n 首相来到大学时遭到一阵辱骂。 \n, Shall we hail a taxi? \n 我们要叫出租车吗？ \n, I tried to hail her from across the room. \n 我在屋子的另一端冲她喊。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhae/ukhaema015.mp3'),('halt','（使）停止，停下停止，停下，中止停止，中止','uk :hɒlt, us :hɑːlt','[ Halt!  called the guard.  You can t go any further without a permit.  \n “站住！”警卫喊道，“没有通行证不能入内。” \n, Production has halted at all of the company s factories because of the pay dispute. \n 由于工资纠纷，这家公司所有工厂都停产了。 \n, Security forces halted the demonstrators by blocking the road. \n 警卫部队用封路的办法来制止示威者前进。 \n, the recent halt in production \n 最近的停产 \n, Severe flooding has brought trains to a halt (= prevented them from moving) on several lines in Scotland. \n 凶猛的洪水使苏格兰几条铁路线上的火车停驶。 \n, The bus came to a halt (= stopped) just in time to avoid hitting the wall. \n 公共汽车正好及时停下，没有撞到墙上。 \n, If traffic increases beyond a certain level, the city grinds to a halt (= stops completely). \n 如果交通流量的增长超过一定限度，城市就会陷于瘫痪状态。 \n, The car screeched to a halt (= stopped suddenly and noisily) just as the lights turned red. \n 这辆车就在信号灯变红时嘎吱一声刹住了车。 \n, How many more people will have to die before they call a halt to the fighting? \n 还要死多少人他们才会停战？ \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhal/ukhallw006.mp3'),('handbill','传单，小广告','uk :ˈhænd.bɪl, us :ˈhænd.bɪl','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd13/epd13378.mp3'),('harass','骚扰；使烦恼，打扰','uk :ˈhær.əs, us :həˈræs','[Stop harassing me! \n 别烦我！ \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhap/ukhapha013.mp3'),('harpsichord','羽管键琴，古键琴','uk :ˈhɑːp.sɪ.kɔːd, us :ˈhɑːrp.sɪ.kɔːrd','[]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhar/ukharne005.mp3'),('haunting','（因一种令人忧伤的美丽而）让人难忘的，萦绕心头的','uk :ˈhɔːn.tɪŋ, us :ˈhɑːn.t̬ɪŋ','[a haunting melody \n 难忘的旋律 \n, the haunting beauty of Africa \n 非洲令人难忘的美丽 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhas/ukhasty027.mp3'),('hearse','灵车，柩车','uk :hɜːs, us :hɝːs','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhea/ukheads026.mp3'),('hedge','（尤指花园、田块或马路边缘的）树篱保护（或控制、限制）手段让表述内容的严重程度降低的单词（或词组）严格限制避免答复，拐弯抹角，回避','uk :hedʒ, us :hedʒ','[a privet hedge \n 女贞树篱 \n, She\'d made some overseas investments as a hedge against rising inflation in this country. \n 在海外有一些投资，可以抵消该国不断上升的通货膨胀所带来的损失。 \n, We\'ve got permission, but it\'s hedged about/around with strict conditions. \n 我们得到了许可，但却有严格的限制条件。 \n, Stop hedging and tell me what you really think. \n 别再拐弯抹角了，告诉我你的真实想法。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhea/ukheave019.mp3'),('hedge fund','对冲基金','Duìchōng jījīn','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=hedge fund&tl=ja&tk=889337.763277&client=webapp&prev=input'),('hence','因此，所以从此，从现在起','uk :hens, us :hens','[His mother was Italian, hence his name - Luca. \n 他母亲是意大利人，所以他的名字叫——卢卡。 \n, The project will be completed at the end of the decade, two years hence. \n 本项目将于这个10年期结束时完成，从现在算起还有两年时间。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhel/ukhellu022.mp3'),('heptagon','七边形','uk :ˈhep.tə.ɡən, us :-ɡɑːn','[]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhen/ukhenpe004.mp3'),('heterosexual','异性恋者','uk :ˌhet.ər.əˈsek.ʃu.əl, us :ˌhet̬.ə.roʊˈsek.ʃu.əl','[]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukher/ukherse017.mp3'),('highball','高杯酒（用威士忌和水或汽水混合制成）','uk :ˈhaɪ.bɔːl, us :ˈhaɪ.bɑːl','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/cal/cald4/cald4uk0731.mp3'),('hillbilly','（住在山区的）乡巴佬，土包子','uk :ˈhɪlˌbɪl.i, us :ˈhɪlˌbɪl.i','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/cal/cald4/cald4uk0741.mp3'),('hippopotamus','河马','uk :ˌhɪp.əˈpɒt.ə.məs, us :ˌhɪp.əˈpɑː.t̬ə.məs','[]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhim/ukhimal028.mp3'),('hooch','烈酒；（尤指）烈性威士忌','uk :huːtʃ, us :huːtʃ','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/cal/cald4/cald4uk0768.mp3'),('horn','角；角质（车辆的）喇叭（乐器）号','uk :hɔːn, us :hɔːrn','[The driver blew/sounded (informal honked) her horn. \n 那个司机按了喇叭。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhoo/ukhoove019.mp3'),('hostility','敌意，不友好不同意，不喜欢战斗；战争行为','uk :hɒsˈtɪl.ə.ti, us :hɑːˈstɪl.ə.t̬i',NULL,'2020-02-14',9,8,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhor/ukhorsi024.mp3'),('hotspot','多事之地；热点地区；可能发生战争（或骚乱）的地方热闹场所（可接上无线宽带上网的）热点','uk :ˈhɒt.spɒt, us :ˈhɑːt.spɑːt','[The border has become a major hotspot. \n 边境地区已经变成了主要的热点。 \n, The Manhattan is one of the best hotspots in town. \n 曼哈顿是城里最热闹的地方之一。 \n, There are wi-fi hotspots in all our cafés. \n 我们所有的咖啡馆里都有上网热点。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/uka33/uka33350.mp3'),('hum','发出连续低沉的声音，嗡嗡作响哼（曲子）忙乱，忙碌；嘈杂持续低沉的噪音；嗡嗡声','uk :hʌm, us :hʌm','[The computers were humming in the background. \n 计算机在背景中嗡嗡作响。 \n, What\'s that strange humming sound? \n 那种奇怪的嗡嗡声是什么？ \n, She hummed to herself as she walked to school. \n 她在上学的路上边走边哼曲子。 \n, I\'ve forgotten how that song goes - could you hum it for me? \n 我忘了那个调子怎么唱了——你能给我哼一下吗？ \n, The bar was really humming last night. \n 昨晚酒吧里一片乱哄哄的。 \n, Our house is on a main road, so we can hear the constant hum of traffic. \n 我们的房子在大路旁，所以能听见持续不断的交通噪声。 \n, There\'s an annoying hum on this computer. \n 这台计算机总是发出一种让人心烦的嗡嗡声。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhuf/ukhuffi018.mp3'),('humdrum','乏味的，单调的，令人厌倦的','uk :ˈhʌm.drʌm, us :ˈhʌm.drʌm','[We lead such a humdrum life/existence. \n 我们的生活／日子过得真是乏味。 \n, Most of the work is fairly humdrum. \n 这工作大部分都相当单调。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhum/ukhuman007.mp3'),('humidity','湿润，潮湿湿度','uk :hjuːˈmɪd.ə.ti, us :hjuːˈmɪd.ə.t̬i','[I don t like the humidity of this climate. \n 我不喜欢这种潮湿的天气。 \n, The temperature is almost 80 degrees, and the humidity 35%. \n 温度已经接近80度，湿度为30多一点。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhum/ukhuman013.mp3'),('humiliation','羞辱','uk :hjuːˌmɪl.iˈeɪ.ʃən, us :hjuːˌmɪl.iˈeɪ.ʃən','[fter the humiliation of last week\'s defeat, the Mets were back on form.\n, Imagine the humiliation of having to apologize.\n, I felt a deep humiliation and wanted the ground to swallow me up.\n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhum/ukhuman017.mp3'),('hunch','直觉；预感弓（背），弯腰','uk :hʌntʃ, us :hʌntʃ','[[ + that ] \n I had a hunch that you d be here. \n 直觉告诉我你会来这儿。 \n, Sometimes you have to be prepared to act on/follow a hunch. \n 有时候你得准备好按直觉行事。 \n, We hunched round the fire to keep warm. \n 我们弓着身子围在火边取暖。 \n, Stand up straight and don t hunch your back. \n 站直了，别弯着腰。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhun/ukhunch001.mp3'),('hurl','（通常指愤怒或用力地）抛，扔大声辱骂（某人）','uk :hɜːl, us :hɝːl','[In a fit of temper he hurled the book across the room. \n 他一怒之下把书扔到了房间的另一头。 \n, Youths hurled stones at the soldiers. \n 年轻人向士兵们投掷石块。 \n, I wasn t going to stand there while he hurled abuse at me! \n 我不会站在那儿任他大声辱骂！ \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhun/ukhunch030.mp3'),('hybrid','（动物或植物的）杂交种，混合种（两种完全不同的东西的）混合用汽油以及其他形式的能源（通常为电力）一同发动的机动车','uk :ˈhaɪ.brɪd, us :ˈhaɪ.brɪd','[The garden strawberry is a large-fruited hybrid. \n 人工栽培的草莓是一种果实较大的杂交品种。 \n, The animal looks like a hybrid of a zebra and a horse. \n 这只动物看上去像是斑马和马杂交所得。 \n, His work is an interesting hybrid of popular and classical music. \n 他的作品是经典与流行音乐有趣的混合。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhur/ukhurly027.mp3'),('hypocrite','伪君子，伪善者','uk :ˈhɪp.ə.krɪt, us :ˈhɪp.ə.krɪt','[He s a hypocrite - he s always lecturing other people on the environment but he drives around in a huge car. \n 他是个伪君子——他总在教导别人要保护环境，可他自己却开着辆大排量的汽车到处转。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhyp/ukhyper020.mp3'),('illicit','非法的；违禁的；社会不容许的','uk :ɪˈlɪs.ɪt, us :ɪˈlɪs.ɪt','[illicit drugs such as cocaine and cannabis \n 可卡因和大麻之类的违禁药物 \n, the illicit trade in stolen vehicles \n 非法的赃车交易 \n, an illicit love affair \n 不正当的恋情 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukele/ukelect027.mp3'),('illuminate','为…照明，照亮阐明，解释','uk :ɪˈluː.mɪ.neɪt, us :ɪˈluː.mə.neɪt','[The streets were illuminated with strings of coloured lights. \n 街道被一串串彩灯照亮了。 \n, an article which illuminates the issues at stake \n 对一些紧要的问题进行阐述的文章 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukign/ukignor025.mp3'),('immune','免疫的不受影响的免除的，豁免的','uk :ɪˈmjuːn, us :ɪˈmjuːn',NULL,'2020-02-14',3,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod011.mp3'),('immunity','免疫；免除；豁免','uk :ɪˈmjuː.nə.ti, us :ɪˈmjuː.nə.t̬i','[The vaccination gives you immunity against the disease for up to six months. \n 注射这种疫苗会使你对这种疾病有长达6个月的免疫力。 \n, He was granted immunity from prosecution because he confessed the names of the other spies. \n 他因供出了其他间谍的名字而免受起诉。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod012.mp3'),('immunosuppression','免疫抑制（通常通过药物有意识地抑制免疫反应，尤其用在阻止或降低机体对移植器官的排斥反应）','uk :ˌɪm.jə.nəʊ.səˈpreʃ.ən, us :ˌɪm.jə.noʊ.səˈpreʃ.ən','[High levels of immunosuppression are needed to prevent rejection of transplanted tissue or organs. \n 需要高强度的免疫抑制来防止对移植器官或组织的排斥。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod017.mp3'),('impact','冲击（力）；撞击（力）（尤指新事物的）巨大影响，强大作用（对…）产生影响','uk :ˈɪm.pækt, us :ˈɪm.pækt','[The impact of the crash reduced the car to a third of its original length. \n 撞车时的冲击力使车身变形，仅剩原长的三分之一。 \n, The bullet explodes on impact (= when it hits another object). \n 子弹击中物体时爆炸。 \n, The anti-smoking campaign had had/made quite an impact on young people. \n 禁烟运动对年轻人影响很大。 \n, The new proposals were intended to soften the impact of the reformed tax system. \n 新的提议旨在减轻改革后的税制所造成的影响。 \n, Falling export rates have impacted (on) the country\'s economy quite considerably. \n 出口率的下降对该国的经济造成了相当大的影响。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod023.mp3'),('impassable','（道路）不能通行的，无法通过的','uk :ɪmˈpɑː.sə.bəl, us :ɪmˈpæs.ə.bəl','[Many roads were flooded and impassable following the storm. \n 暴风雨过后，许多道路被淹，无法通行。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpar005.mp3'),('implacable','不饶人的；坚定的；无法改变的','uk :ɪmˈplæk.ə.bəl, us :ɪmˈplæk.ə.bəl',NULL,'2020-02-14',3,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpet012.mp3'),('implicate','牵连，涉及','uk :ˈɪm.plɪ.keɪt, us :ˈɪm.plə.keɪt','[Have they any evidence to implicate him in the robbery? \n 他们有证据表明他涉嫌抢劫案吗？ \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpet022.mp3'),('imply','暗指，暗示正如…所暗示的必然包含；使成为必需','uk :ɪmˈplaɪ, us :ɪmˈplaɪ','[[ + (that) ] \n Are you implying (that) I\'m fat? \n 你是在暗示我长得胖吗？ \n, I\'m not implying anything about your cooking, but could we eat out tonight? \n 我并不是暗示你做的饭不好吃，只是想提议我们今晚去外面吃，好吗？ \n, I detected an implied criticism of the way he was treated. \n 我觉察到他在含蓄地批评自己受到的待遇。 \n, Variable rate loans, as the name implies, have a variable interest rate. \n 可变利率贷款，正如名字所暗示的，是一种利率可能变化的贷款。 \n, Socialism implies equality. \n 社会主义必然包含平等。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimplo002.mp3'),('impose','推行；强制实行把（尤指信仰或生活方式）强加于勉强；打扰，麻烦','uk :ɪmˈpəʊz, us :ɪmˈpoʊz','[Very high taxes have recently been imposed on cigarettes. \n 最近对香烟开征很高的税。 \n, Judges are imposing increasingly heavy fines for minor driving offences. \n 法官们对轻微的违章驾驶开始处以越来越重的罚款。 \n, The council has imposed a ban on alcohol in the city parks. \n 市政会禁止在城市公园中饮酒。 \n, I don t want them to impose their religious beliefs on my children. \n 我不希望他们把自己的宗教信仰强加给我的孩子们。 \n, We must impose some kind of order on the way this office is run. \n 我们得给这个办公室的管理定出规章来。 \n, Are you sure it s all right for me to come tonight? I don t want to impose. \n 你肯定我今天晚上来没有问题吗？我不想太麻烦你。 \n, She s always imposing on people - asking favours and getting everyone to do things for her. \n 她总是强人所难——要人帮忙做这做那。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimplo017.mp3'),('impressionable','（通常指年轻人）易受影响的','uk :ɪmˈpreʃ.ən.ə.bəl, us :ɪmˈpreʃ.ən.ə.bəl','[He s at that impressionable age when he s very easily led by other children. \n 他正处于那种易受影响的年龄，行为非常容易受其他孩子左右。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpra012.mp3'),('impunity','（惩罚、坏结果的）免除','uk :ɪmˈpjuː.nə.ti, us :ɪmˈpjuː.ə.t̬i','[Criminal gangs are terrorizing the city with apparent impunity. \n 犯罪集团使市民人心惶惶却显然没有受到惩罚。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpro014.mp3'),('in force','in large number','null','null\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'null'),('incandescent','白炽的，白热的极亮的极度愤怒的；极度高兴的杰出的，卓越的','uk :ˌɪn.kænˈdes.ənt, us :ˌɪn.kænˈdes.ənt','[an incandescent lamp \n 白炽灯 \n, The mountain s snow-white peak was incandescent against the blue sky. \n 雪白的山顶在蓝天的映衬下十分耀眼。 \n, He was incandescent with rage. \n 他大发雷霆。 \n, Her beauty had an incandescent quality to it. \n 她貌美绝伦，光彩照人。 \n, an incandescent performance/career \n 炉火纯青的表演／辉煌的事业 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukina/ukinaug015.mp3'),('incubate','孵（卵），孵化（细菌或病毒在体内）潜伏','uk :ˈɪŋ.kjə.beɪt, us :ˈɪŋ.kjə.beɪt','[The female bird incubates the eggs for about 16 days. \n 雌鸟孵卵16天左右。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinc/ukincor025.mp3'),('incubation','孵化, 疾病, （細菌或病毒在體內）潛伏','uk :ˌɪŋ.kjəˈbeɪ.ʃən, us :ˌɪŋ.kjəˈbeɪ.ʃən','[he incubation period varies depending on the time of year when the eggs were laid.\n, The chemical makes eggshells so thin and porous that they break during incubation. \n, n smallpox, there is an incubation period of 8–18 days between initial infection and first symptoms.\n, After about two weeks of incubation, symptoms begin.\n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinc/ukincor026.mp3'),('indice','指数，索引','ˈɪndɪsiːz','null\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'null'),('infant','婴儿幼儿学校的学生幼儿学校（同 infant school）学前班的，幼儿的','uk :ˈɪn.fənt, us :ˈɪn.fənt','[a newborn infant \n 新生儿 \n, Jenny is a top-year infant now. \n 珍妮现在是一所幼儿学校的大班生。 \n, Andrew s still in the infants. \n 安德鲁还在上幼儿学校。 \n, an infant teacher/class \n 幼师／学前班 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukine/ukinexp019.mp3'),('infidelity','（夫妇间的）不忠实，不贞行为','uk :ˌɪn.fɪˈdel.ə.ti, us :ˌɪn.fəˈdel.ə.t̬i','[marital/sexual infidelity \n 婚姻／性方面的不忠 \n, She could not forgive his many infidelities. \n 她不能原谅他的诸多不忠行为。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinf/ukinfec017.mp3'),('informally','非公式','null','null\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'null'),('infrastructure','基础设施','uk :ˈɪn.frəˌstrʌk.tʃər, us :ˈɪn.frəˌstrʌk.tʃɚ','[The war has badly damaged the country\'s infrastructure. \n 战争严重破坏了该国的基础设施。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinf/ukinfor009.mp3'),('inhabit','居住于','uk :ɪnˈhæb.ɪt, us :ɪnˈhæb.ɪt','[These remote islands are inhabited only by birds. \n 这些偏僻的岛屿上只有鸟类栖息。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/uking/ukingra007.mp3'),('inhale','吸气；吸入狼吞虎咽','uk :ɪnˈheɪl, us :ɪnˈheɪl','[She flung open the window and inhaled deeply. \n 她打开窗户，深深地吸了口气。 \n, She became ill shortly after inhaling the fumes. \n 她吸入浓烟后不久就生病了。 \n, Tony inhaled his burger. \n 托尼狼吞虎咽地吃汉堡。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/uking/ukingra011.mp3'),('inlay','镶嵌图案（或装饰）','uk :ˈɪn.leɪ, us :ˈɪn.leɪ','[The walls of the palace are marble with silver inlay. \n 宫殿的墙壁是镶银大理石的。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukini/ukiniti021.mp3'),('innate','天生的，固有的','uk :ɪˈneɪt, us :ɪˈneɪt','[Cyril s most impressive quality was his innate goodness. \n 西里尔给人印象最深的品质是他天生的善良。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukini/ukiniti027.mp3'),('inoculation','接种','uk :ɪˌnɒk.jəˈleɪ.ʃən, us :ɪˌnɑː.kjəˈleɪ.ʃən','[fter inoculation with the 2nd vaccine the animals\' temperature will go up.\n, He received a cholera inoculation.\n, A doctor visits the clinic monthly to give inoculations.\n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinn/ukinnin023.mp3'),('insane','疯癫的，精神失常的疯狂的；荒唐的精神病患者','uk :ɪnˈseɪn, us :ɪnˈseɪn','[For the last ten years of his life he was clinically insane. \n 在生命的最后10年，他处于临床上的精神失常状态。 \n, nformal \n I sometimes think I m going insane (= I feel very confused). \n 我有时觉得自己快要疯了。 \n, It would be insane not to take advantage of this opportunity. \n 如果不抓住这一机会的话那就太荒唐了。 \n, a hospital for the criminally insane \n 为患有精神病的犯人开设的医院 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukino/ukinorg016.mp3'),('insinuate','含沙射影地说，影射','uk :ɪnˈsɪn.ju.eɪt, us :ɪnˈsɪn.ju.eɪt','[[ + (that) ] \n Are you insinuating (that) I m losing my nerve? \n 你是在暗示我胆怯了吗？ \n, What are you insinuating, Daniel? \n 丹尼尔，你究竟在影射什么？ \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsin003.mp3'),('inspection','检查；视察鉴定，查勘（建筑物）','uk :ɪnˈspek.ʃən, us :ɪnˈspek.ʃən','[Her passport seemed legitimate, but on closer inspection, it was found to have been altered. \n 她的护照看似合法，但仔细检查，发现做过手脚。 \n, She arrived to carry out/make a health and safety inspection of the building. \n 她来对大楼进行安全卫生检查。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsin030.mp3'),('instigate','促使发生；发起','uk :ˈɪn.stɪ.ɡeɪt, us :ˈɪn.stə.ɡeɪt','[The government will instigate new measures to combat terrorism. \n 政府将采取新措施打击恐怖主义。 \n, The revolt in the north is believed to have been instigated by a high-ranking general. \n 北方的叛乱据信是由一名高级将领唆使的。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinspe019.mp3'),('institutional','机构的','uk :ˌɪn.stɪˈtʃuː.ʃən.əl, us :ˌɪn.stəˈtuː.ʃən.əl','[The hospital provides typically awful institutional food. \n 医院供应的是公共机构常见的那种难吃的食物。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinspe028.mp3'),('insufficiency','不够，不足；不充分（器官和身体部分）机能不全，功能不全','uk :ˌɪn.səˈfɪʃ.ən.si, us :ˌɪn.səˈfɪʃ.ən.si','[Sometimes we blame all our problems on an insufficiency of money. \n 有时候我们把所有问题都归咎于钱不够。 \n, Pancreatic insufficiency is associated with excess fat in stool. \n 胰功能不全和粪便中脂肪过多有关联。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinstr015.mp3'),('insurance','保险','uk :ɪnˈʃɔː.rəns\nɪnˈʃʊə.rəns, us :ɪnˈʃɜ.r.əns','[life/