.vəl','[We see each other at regular intervals - usually about once a month. \n 我们定期见面——通常大约是每月一次。 \n, The plants should be spaced at six-inch intervals. \n 这些植物应该以六英尺的间隔栽种。 \n, There will be two 20-minute intervals during the opera. \n 歌剧演出中有两次20分钟的幕间休息。 \n, He scored his first goal of the match three minutes after the interval. \n 下半场刚开始3分钟，他就射入了他本场比赛的第一个进球。 \n, In the event of fire, the alarm will sound at 15-second intervals/at intervals of 15 seconds. \n 发生火灾时，警报每隔15秒就会响一次。 \n, an interval of a fifth (= between one note and another one four notes higher) \n 五度音程 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukinter318.mp3'),('intestinal','肠的','uk :ˌɪnˈtes.tɪn.əl, us :ˌɪnˈtes.tɪn.əl','[intestinal surgery \n 肠部手术 \n, Foul-smelling brown vomit can be a symptom of low intestinal obstruction. \n 呕吐物为棕色带恶臭可能是低位肠梗阻的症状。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintes001.mp3'),('intonation','（尤指对话语意义有影响的）语调，声调（演奏或歌唱时音符的）音准','uk :ˌɪn.təˈneɪ.ʃən, us :ˌɪn.təˈneɪ.ʃən','[The end of a sentence that is not a question is usually marked by falling intonation. \n 非疑问句的句尾通常用降调。 \n, The violinist had good intonation, and a wonderful pure tone. \n 这位小提琴演奏家对音准把握得很好，音色也很纯。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintes019.mp3'),('intoxicating','（饮品）醉人的（经历或想法）令人陶醉的，令人极其兴奋的','uk :ɪnˈtɒk.sɪ.keɪ.tɪŋ, us :ɪnˈtɑːk.sɪ.keɪ.t̬ɪŋ','[intoxicating liquor \n 烈酒 \n, an intoxicating thought \n 令人陶醉的想法 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintes024.mp3'),('intranasal','鼻内','null','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('intrusive','打搅的；侵扰的','uk :ɪnˈtruː.sɪv, us :ɪnˈtruː.sɪv','[intrusive questioning \n 唐突的盘问 \n, intrusive lighting \n 扰人的照明 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintru004.mp3'),('invest','投（资），投入','uk :ɪnˈvest, us :ɪnˈvest','[The institute will invest five million in the project. \n 该机构将在这个项目上投资500万。 \n, He\'s not certain whether to invest in the property market. \n 他拿不定主意该不该投资房地产市场。 \n, You have all invested significant amounts of time and energy in making this project the success that it is. \n 你们都为这个项目的成功投入了大量的时间和精力。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinv/ukinvei015.mp3'),('investigator','调查人员','uk :ɪnˈves.tɪ.ɡeɪ.tər, us :ɪnˈves.tə.ɡeɪ.t̬ɚ','[Investigators have studied the possible effects of contamination. \n 调查人员研究了污染可能造成的后果。 \n, a private investigator \n 私家侦探 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinv/ukinvei019.mp3'),('investor','投资者','uk :ɪnˈves.tər, us :ɪnˈves.t̬ɚ','[A New York investor offered to acquire the company s shares for $13 each. \n 一名纽约投资商提出以每股13美元的价格收购这家公司的股票。 \n, Small investors (= people who invest only a small amount of money) are hoping that the markets will improve. \n 小额投资者希望市场会好转。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinv/ukinvei023.mp3'),('invulnerable','无法伤害的；无法损坏的','uk :ɪnˈvʌl.nər.ə.bəl, us :ɪnˈvʌl.nɚ.ə.bəl','[The command bunker is virtually invulnerable, even to a nuclear attack. \n 这个指挥部掩体即使是核武器都难以攻破。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinv/ukinvig026.mp3'),('irony','具有讽刺意味的是','uk :ˈaɪ.rə.ni, us :ˈaɪ.rə.ni','null\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'null'),('isolate','隔离；孤立；分离隔离（人或动物）孤立（人、国家或组织）','uk :ˈaɪ.sə.leɪt, us :ˈaɪ.sə.leɪt','[A high wall isolated the house from the rest of the village. \n 一堵高墙将这栋房子与村庄的其他部分隔离开来。 \n, They tried to isolate (= find) the cause of the problem. \n 他们试图找出问题的原因。 \n, pecialized \n Virus particles were eventually isolated from the tissue. \n 终于将病毒粒子与组织分离开了。 \n, He was isolated from all the other prisoners. \n 他被与其他所有囚犯隔离开来。 \n, This policy will isolate minority groups and prevent integration. \n 这一政策将孤立少数人群社区，阻碍融合。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukiso/ukisola001.mp3'),('jaw','下颌，下巴颌；颚（尤指大型凶猛动物的）口部，嘴钳夹部分；钳口险境闲谈喋喋不休，唠唠叨叨','uk :dʒɔː, us :dʒɑː','[a broken jaw \n 骨折的下颌 \n, S \n a punch in the jaw \n 打在下巴上的一拳 \n, K \n a punch on the jaw \n 打在下巴上的一拳 \n, He has a strong/square jaw. \n 他长着结实的／方下巴。 \n, upper/lower jaw \n 上／下颚 \n, The lion opened its jaws and roared. \n 狮子张开大嘴咆哮起来。 \n, His foot was caught in the jaws of the trap. \n 他的脚被夹在捕兽夹的钳口里。 \n, The rescuers snatched the children from the jaws of death. \n 救援人员将孩子们从死亡的险境中救了出来。 \n, I met Jane and we had a good jaw over lunch. \n 我遇到了简，并且在吃午饭时两个人好好聊了一番。 \n, He was jawing away to his girlfriend for hours on the phone. \n 他和女朋友煲了几个小时的电话粥。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjau/ukjaund009.mp3'),('jeopardise','使处于危险境地；危及，损害','uk :ˈdʒep.ə.daɪz, us :ˈdʒep.ɚ.daɪz','[She knew that by failing her finals she could jeopardize her whole future. \n 她知道考试不及格会影响自己的整个前程。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjeh/ukjehov010.mp3'),('jest','笑话；滑稽事开玩笑地，诙谐地开玩笑','uk :dʒest, us :dʒest','[His proposal was no jest - he was completely sincere. \n 他的建议不是开玩笑，他完全是认真的。 \n, I only said it in jest - you re obviously not fat. \n 我那么说是开玩笑——很显然，你不胖。 \n, Would I jest about something so important? \n 我会拿这么重要的事开玩笑吗？ \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjeh/ukjehov024.mp3'),('jewish','犹太教','ˈdʒuː.ɪʃ',NULL,'2020-01-07',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjet/ukjetsa012.mp3'),('judiciary','（政府的）司法部；司法系统','uk :dʒuːˈdɪʃ.ər.i, us :dʒuːˈdɪʃ.ɚ.i',NULL,'2020-02-14',2,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjud/ukjudic003.mp3'),('jurisdiction','司法权；管辖权；审判权','uk :ˌdʒʊə.rɪsˈdɪk.ʃən, us :ˌdʒʊr.ɪsˈdɪk.ʃən','[The court has no jurisdiction in/over cases of this kind. \n 该法庭无权审判此类案件。 \n, School admissions are not under/within our jurisdiction. \n 我们无权批准入学。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjun/ukjun__015.mp3'),('jury','陪审团（竞赛的）裁判团，评判委员会','uk :ˈdʒʊə.ri, us :ˈdʒʊr.i','[members of the jury \n 陪审团成员 \n, The jury has/have been unable to return a verdict (= reach a decision). \n 陪审团未能作出裁决。 \n, Police officers aren t usually allowed to be/sit/serve on a jury. \n 警察通常不允许进入陪审团。 \n]\n','2020-01-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjet/ukjetsa014.mp3'),('justification','正当的理由；辩解','uk :ˌdʒʌs.tɪ.fɪˈkeɪ.ʃən, us :ˌdʒʌs.tə.fəˈkeɪ.ʃən',NULL,'2020-02-14',3,4,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjun/ukjun__023.mp3'),('keen','热衷的；热心的；渴望的强烈的，激烈的敏锐的；敏捷的尖利的；寒风刺骨的（尤指因某人死去而）恸哭热衷；渴望','uk :kiːn, us :kiːn',NULL,'2020-02-14',2,3,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukk/ukkaz/ukkazak010.mp3'),('lack','没有…，…匮乏，…短缺缺少，缺乏','uk :læk, us :læk','[Her only problem is a lack of confidence. \n 她唯一的问题是缺乏自信。 \n, Lack of sleep had made him irritable. \n 睡眠不足令他烦躁易怒。 \n, If he fails it won t be for/through lack of effort (= he has certainly tried). \n 他若失败了，那肯定不是因为他努力不够。 \n, We won t be going away this year - lack of funds, I m afraid. \n 今年我们恐怕不会去度假了——因为没钱。 \n, He just lacks a little confidence. \n 他只是有点缺乏自信。 \n, What we lack in this house is space to store things. \n 我们这所房子缺少的是储物空间。 \n, We are lacking three members of staff due to illness. \n 我们有3人因病缺席。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklab/uklabia021.mp3'),('lane','乡间小路；小巷，小街，胡同车道；（田径比赛的）跑道；泳道航道，航线','uk :leɪn, us :leɪn','[He drives so fast along those narrow country lanes. \n 在那些狭窄的乡间小路上他把车开得飞快。 \n, I live at the end of Church Lane. \n 我住在教堂巷的最里面。 \n, a bus/bike/cycle lane \n 公共汽车／自行车车道 \n, The northbound lane is closed because of an accident. \n 北行的车道因发生事故已经封闭。 \n, I find driving in the fast lane very stressful. \n 我发现在快车道行驶时精神非常紧张。 \n, The German runners/swimmers are in lanes 4 and 6. \n 德国径赛／游泳选手处在第4道和第6道。 \n, The English Channel is the busiest shipping lane in the world. \n 英吉利海峡是世界上最繁忙的水运航道。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklai/uklaidb003.mp3'),('lapis-lazuli','青金石','/ˈlæpɪs ˈlæzjʊli','\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=lapis-lazuli&tl=ja&tk=439866.33358&client=webapp&prev=input'),('latex','胶乳；（尤指橡胶树的）橡浆；橡胶，乳胶','uk :ˈleɪ.teks, us :ˈleɪ.teks','[a latex mask \n 乳胶口罩 \n, a pair of latex surgical gloves \n 一副乳胶外科手套 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklat/uklat__013.mp3'),('latter','后半程的，靠后的，末尾的（提及的两者中的）后者（已提及的两个以上的人、事物或群体中的）最后一个','uk :ˈlæt.ər, us :ˈlæt̬.ɚ','[Building of the new library should begin in the latter part of next year. \n 新图书馆的建设应该在明年下半年开工。 \n, In the latter stages of the fight he began to tire. \n 到那场拳击赛的后半段他开始支持不住了。 \n, She offered me more money or a car and I chose the latter. \n 她提出给我更多的钱或者一辆汽车，我选择了后者。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklat/uklat__026.mp3'),('lawn','（尤指房屋附近或公园的）草地，草坪','uk :lɔːn, us :lɑːn','[Will you mow the lawn at the weekend? \n 周末你修剪一下草坪好吗？ \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklaw/uklawle002.mp3'),('leaden','深灰色的，灰蒙蒙的呆滞的；缺乏感情的','uk :ˈled.ən, us :ˈled.ən','[leaden skies \n 灰蒙蒙的天空 \n, a leaden expression/performance \n 呆滞的表情／缺乏感情的表演 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukldr/ukldriv006.mp3'),('leaflet','传单，活页；（单页）广告散发，发放（传单或广告）','uk :ˈliː.flət, us :ˈliː.flət','[Demonstrators handed out leaflets to passers-by. \n 示威者向路人发放传单。 \n, A leaflet about the new bus services came through the door today. \n 今天从门缝塞进来一张介绍公交车新增服务的广告。 \n, They leafleted the area two weeks before the event. \n 活动开始前两周他们就在该地区散发了广告。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukldr/ukldriv013.mp3'),('leap','跳，跳跃快速提供（帮助、保护等）一举获得（常指名望或权势）激增；猛涨；快速提高巨变；激增；提高跳，跳跃；突然的动作','uk :liːp, us :liːp','[He leaped out of his car and ran towards the house. \n 他跳下车朝那所房子跑去。 \n, I leaped up to answer the phone. \n 我跳起来去接电话。 \n, The dog leaped over the gate into the field. \n 狗越过大门朝田野跑去。 \n, He leaped to his friend s defence. \n 他立即为他的朋友进行辩护。 \n, Scott leapt to the rescue when he spotted the youngster in difficulty. \n 斯科特一发现那孩子处境艰难就立即出手帮忙。 \n, Mr Davies leaped in to explain. \n 戴维斯先生赶忙出来解释。 \n, He leapt to fame after his appearance in a Broadway play. \n 他在参加一出百老汇演出后一举成名。 \n, Shares in the company leaped 250 percent. \n 公司的股票大涨250%。 \n, a leap in profits \n 利润激增 \n, It takes quite a leap of the imagination to believe that it s the same person. \n 让人相信这是同一个人着实要费一番脑筋。 \n, With one leap he crossed the stream. \n 他一跃跳过了小溪。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukldr/ukldriv023.mp3'),('leash','（拴狗等动物用的）绳索，链子','uk :liːʃ, us :liːʃ','[Please keep your dog on a leash when on the beach. \n 在海滩上请牵住你的狗。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklea/uklearn006.mp3'),('lecture','（尤指面向学生的）讲座，课教训，训斥，斥责（常指在大学里）讲课，讲授教训，训斥，斥责','uk :ˈlek.tʃər, us :ˈlek.tʃɚ','[We went to a lecture on Italian art. \n 我们去参加了一个关于意大利艺术的讲座。 \n, Who s giving the lecture this afternoon? \n 今天下午的课由谁来讲？ \n, My dad gave me a lecture on the evils of alcohol last night. \n 昨天晚上爸爸教训了我一顿，给我讲了酒的危害。 \n, For ten years she lectured in law. \n 她教了10年的法律课。 \n, She travelled widely in North America, lecturing on women s rights. \n 她到北美各地宣讲妇女的权利。 \n, His parents used to lecture him on his table manners. \n 以前他的父母经常批评他的餐桌礼仪。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklea/uklearn027.mp3'),('leech','水蛭，蚂蟥（指人）吸血鬼，寄生虫','uk :liːtʃ, us :liːtʃ','[]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukldr/ukldriv002.mp3'),('legislate','立法','uk :ˈledʒ.ɪ.sleɪt, us :ˈledʒ.ə.sleɪt','[They promised to legislate against cigarette advertising. \n 他们承诺要立法来打击香烟广告。 \n, It\'s hard to legislate for (= make a law that will protect) the ownership of an idea. \n 通过立法来保护创意所有权非常困难。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukleg/uklegal012.mp3'),('legislative','法律的；立法的','uk :ˈledʒ.ɪ.slə.tɪv, us :ˈledʒ.ə.slə.t̬ɪv',NULL,'2020-02-14',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukleg/uklegal014.mp3'),('leisure','空闲，闲暇，休闲','uk :ˈleʒ.ər, us :ˈliː.ʒɚ','[leisure activities \n 休闲活动 \n, Most people only have a limited amount of leisure time. \n 大多数人只有有限的空闲时间。 \n, The town lacks leisure facilities such as a swimming pool or squash courts. \n 这个城镇缺少游泳池、壁球场等休闲设施。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukleg/uklegal030.mp3'),('lesion','（对人体或体内器官的）伤害，损伤','uk :ˈliː.ʒən, us :ˈliː.ʒən','[skin/brain lesions \n 皮肤／大脑损伤 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukles/ukles__004.mp3'),('lest','以免，唯恐','uk :lest, us :lest','[They were afraid to complain about the noise lest they annoyed the neighbours. \n 他们不敢对噪声有任何抱怨，唯恐惹恼了邻居。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukles/ukles__009.mp3'),('lethal','致命的；极其危险的','uk :ˈliː.θəl, us :ˈliː.θəl','[Three minutes after the fire started, the house was full of lethal fumes. \n 起火3分钟后，房子里充满了致命的毒气。 \n, In the car the police found guns, knives, and other lethal weapons (= weapons that can kill). \n 警察在车里找到了枪支、刀具及其他一些凶器。 \n, A 59-year-old man was executed by lethal injection (= by having a poisonous substance put into his body) this morning. \n 今晨一位59岁的男性罪犯被执行注射死刑。 \n, nformal \n That combination of tiredness and alcohol is lethal (= has a very bad effect). \n 身体的疲劳加上酒精的作用会产生非常严重的后果。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukles/ukles__013.mp3'),('lighter','打火机','uk :ˈlaɪ.tər, us :ˈlaɪ.t̬ɚ','[a cigarette lighter \n 香烟打火机 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklif/uklifes009.mp3'),('linger','停留，逗留；徘徊','uk :ˈlɪŋ.ɡər, us :ˈlɪŋ.ɡɚ','[After the play had finished, we lingered for a while in the bar hoping to catch sight of the actors. \n 戏演完后我们在酒吧里等了一会儿，希望能与演员见上一面。 \n, The smell from the fire still lingered days later. \n 大火过后好几天还能闻到烧焦的味道。 \n, It s impossible to forget such horrific events - they linger (on) in the memory forever. \n 这样恐怖的事件让人难以忘记——会永远留在人们的记忆中。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklin/uklinct017.mp3'),('lining','内衬，里衬','uk :ˈlaɪ.nɪŋ, us :ˈlaɪ.nɪŋ','[a coat/jacket lining \n 外套／夹克衫里衬 \n, the lining of the stomach \n 胃黏膜 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklin/uklinct030.mp3'),('liquor','白酒，烈酒','uk :ˈlɪk.ər, us :ˈlɪk.ɚ','[]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/cal/cald4/cald4uk0951.mp3'),('lit','（light的过去式及过去分词）文学；（尤指有传世价值的）文学作品（literature的缩写）','uk :lɪt, us :lɪt','[a degree in English Lit 