ign \n 霓虹灯／霓虹灯广告牌 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/ukneg/uknegot023.mp3'),('neonate','不足四周的婴儿','uk :ˈniː.əʊ.neɪt, us :ˈniː.əˌneɪt','[We provide intensive care for seriously ill neonates. \n 我们为病情严重的新生儿提供重症特别护理。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/ces/cespu/cespuk000757.mp3'),('neuroinvasive','神经侵袭','null','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('nickel','镍（美国或加拿大的）5分镍币','uk :ˈnɪk.əl, us :ˈnɪk.əl','[a nickel alloy \n 镍合金 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknic/ukniche003.mp3'),('nod','点头；（尤指）点头赞同，点头致意，点头示意点头','uk :nɒd, us :nɑːd','[Many people in the audience nodded in agreement. \n 许多听众点头表示赞同。 \n, When I suggested a walk, Elena nodded enthusiastically. \n 当我提议去散步时，埃琳娜使劲地点头。 \n, She looked up and nodded for me to come in. \n 她抬起头，点头示意让我进来。 \n, Chen gave her a nod of recognition across the crowded room. \n 陈从挤满人的房间的另一头向她点头致意。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknoc/uknoctu003.mp3'),('nonagon','九角形','uk :ˈnɒn.ə.ɡən, us :ˈnɑː.nə.ɡɑːn','[]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0318uknona0941.mp3'),('nonconformity','不合规','uk :ˌnɒn.kənˈfɔː.mə.ti, us :ˌnɑːn.kənˈfɔːr.mə.t̬i',NULL,'2020-02-14',6,6,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknon/uknonag011.mp3'),('nosocomial','院内()染','/nɒsəˈkoʊmi.əl/','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('notable','显要的；显著的；值得注意的显要人物；名流','uk :ˈnəʊ.tə.bəl, us :ˈnoʊ.t̬ə.bəl','[a notable collection of rare plants \n 一批引人注目的奇花异草 \n, Getting both sides to agree was a notable achievement. \n 使双方达成共识是一项显著的成就。 \n, This attractive building is particularly notable for its woodland setting. \n 这幢漂亮的建筑因其树林背景而格外引人注目。 \n, Other notables among his pupils were the kings of Saudi Arabia and Thailand. \n 他的学生中，另外两位显要人物是沙特阿拉伯国王和泰国国王。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknos/uknosh_011.mp3'),('notion','观念；看法缝纫用品；缝纫用品店；缝纫用品部','uk :ˈnəʊ.ʃən, us :ˈnoʊ.ʃən','[[ + that ] \n The show\'s director rejects the notion that seeing violence on television has a harmful effect on children. \n 节目制片人们并不认为看到电视上的暴力场景会对孩子们造成不良影响。 \n, I have only a vague notion of what she does for a living. \n 我不太清楚她靠什么谋生。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknot/uknotif004.mp3'),('novel','https://www.99lib.net/book/2126/62122.htm',NULL,NULL,'2020-02-13',0,1001,1,NULL),('nudge','（尤指用肘部）轻推，轻触接近（更高点或水平）轻推','uk :nʌdʒ, us :nʌdʒ','[The children were giggling and nudging each other. \n 孩子们咯咯地笑着，互相推来推去。 \n, He nudged the cat off the sofa so that he could sit down. \n 他把猫轻轻推下沙发，这样自己可以坐下来。 \n, Oil prices continue to nudge higher. \n 油价持续上涨。 \n, Peter must be nudging 40 now. \n 彼得现在肯定将近40岁了。 \n, I gave him a nudge to wake him up. \n 我轻轻推醒他。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknow/uknowac021.mp3'),('nuke','用核武器攻击用微波炉加热；用微波炉烹制核武器','uk :njuːk, us :nuːk','[The two countries were threatening to nuke each other. \n 两个国家都威胁要对对方使用核武器。 \n,  No nukes here!  the banner read. \n 横幅上写着“禁止在此使用核武器！” \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknow/uknowac028.mp3'),('numb','（身体部位）麻木的，失去感觉的（由于过度震惊或恐惧而）麻木的，思维迟钝的使麻木，使失去感觉','uk :nʌm, us :nʌm','[I was lying in a weird position and my leg went numb. \n 我躺卧的姿势很奇怪，结果腿都麻了。 \n, My fingers were numb with cold. \n 我的手指冻僵了。 \n, When she first heard the news, she was numb with disbelief. \n 她最初听到这条消息的时候，简直不敢相信自己的耳朵。 \n, Ever since his girlfriend left him he has felt numb. \n 自从女朋友离开他之后，他就变得麻木迟钝了。 \n, The extreme cold numbed her face and hands. \n 她的脸和手在严寒中冻得都麻木了。 \n, The children are still numbed by their father s death. \n 孩子们仍旧沉浸在父亲去世的打击中，麻木迟钝。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknow/uknowac030.mp3'),('numerous','许多的，大量的','uk :ˈnjuː.mə.rəs, us :ˈnuː.mə.rəs','[We have discussed these plans on numerous occasions. \n 我们已经多次讨论过这些计划。 \n, Retailers of this type, once rare, are now numerous. \n 这种商店从前很少见，但现在已经遍地开花。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknum/uknumbe013.mp3'),('oblivion','被遗忘，被忘却；湮没完全被毁灭；彻底被消灭无知觉，无意识；不省人事','uk :əˈblɪv.i.ən, us :əˈblɪv.i.ən','[He was another minor poet who was consigned to oblivion. \n 他又是一位湮没无闻的小诗人。 \n, These toys will be around for a year or two, then fade/slide/sink into oblivion. \n 这些玩具会风行一两年，然后渐渐被人遗忘。 \n, The planes bombed the city into oblivion. \n 飞机将该市炸成一片废墟。 \n, He sought oblivion in a bottle of whisky. \n 他试图用一瓶威士忌酒来忘却一切。 \n]\n','2019-11-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobj/ukobjec020.mp3'),('obscene','猥亵的；淫秽的；下流的；粗俗的伤风败俗的；骇人听闻的；令人震惊的','uk :əbˈsiːn, us :əbˈsiːn','[In the raid, police found several boxes of obscene DVDs. \n 警方在这次突击搜查中发现了几箱淫秽光盘。 \n, He was jailed for making obscene phone calls (= ones in which unwanted sexual suggestions were made to the listener). \n 他因拨打色情骚扰电话而入狱。 \n, obscene language/graffiti \n 下流的语言／涂鸦 \n, to make obscene profits \n 大捞一笔 \n, The salaries some bankers earn are obscene. \n 有些银行高管的薪水高得令人咋舌。 \n, He eats obscene amounts of food. \n 他食量惊人。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobj/ukobjec030.mp3'),('obscure','无名的；鲜为人知的；默默无闻的费解的，晦涩的；模糊的，朦胧的；不清楚的遮掩；遮蔽；使不分明隐藏，掩盖；使难理解，使晦涩','uk :əbˈskjʊər, us :əbˈskjʊr','[an obscure island in the Pacific \n 太平洋中的无名小岛 \n, an obscure 12th-century mystic \n 12世纪一位鲜为人知的神秘主义者 \n, Official policy has changed, for reasons that remain obscure. \n 官方的政策已改变，原因尚不清楚。 \n, His answers were obscure and confusing. \n 他的回答模糊不清，令人费解。 \n, Two new skyscrapers had sprung up, obscuring the view from her window. \n 两座新摩天大楼拔地而起，挡住了她窗外的风景。 \n, The sun was obscured by clouds. \n 太阳被云层遮住了。 \n, Managers deliberately obscured the real situation from federal investigators. \n 经理们故意对联邦调查人员掩盖真实情况。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce003.mp3'),('obsessive','着迷的；迷恋的；难以释怀的过分（到不正常程度）的强迫症患者','uk :əbˈses.ɪv, us :əbˈses.ɪv','[He s obsessive about punctuality. \n 他过分讲究准时。 \n, obsessive secrecy \n 过分的遮遮掩掩 \n, obsessional behaviour \n 痴迷的行为 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce019.mp3'),('obsolete','废弃的；过时的；淘汰的；老化的','uk :ˌɒb.səlˈiːt, us :ˌɑːb.səlˈiːt','[Gas lamps became obsolete when electric lighting was invented. \n 电灯发明以后煤气灯就被淘汰了。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce024.mp3'),('obstacle','障碍；阻碍；妨碍','uk :ˈɒb.stə.kəl, us :ˈɑːb.stə.kəl','[The biggest obstacle in our way was a tree trunk in the road. \n 我们路上最大的障碍是横在路上的一棵树。 \n, This decision has removed the last obstacle to the hostages\' release. \n 这个决定清除了释放人质的最后障碍。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce025.mp3'),('obstruct','阻塞，堵塞，阻挡（道路、通道、入口等）阻碍；阻止，阻挠；妨碍','uk :əbˈstrʌkt, us :əbˈstrʌkt',NULL,'2020-02-14',5,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsti004.mp3'),('occasional','偶尔的；不经常的','uk :əˈkeɪ.ʒən.əl, us :əˈkeɪ.ʒən.əl','[I play the occasional game of tennis. \n 我偶尔打打网球。 \n, He has the occasional cigar after dinner. \n 他饭后偶尔抽支雪茄。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsti023.mp3'),('occupy','占有，占用，占据（空间或时间）使（某人）忙于；使（某人）感兴趣（军队或一伙人）占领，占据','uk :ˈɒk.jə.paɪ, 