ese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukopp/ukoppre011.mp3'),('ornament','装饰物，饰品装饰，摆设装饰，点缀','uk :ˈɔː.nə.mənt, us :ˈɔːr.nə.mənt','[a glass ornament \n 玻璃饰物 \n, garden ornaments such as statues and fountains \n 如雕像、喷泉等花园装饰物 \n, The building relies on clever design rather than on ornament for its impressive effect. \n 这幢大楼依靠其巧妙设计而非装饰给人留下了深刻的印象。 \n, She ornamented her letters with little drawings in the margin. \n 她在信的页边空白处画上小图案来作装饰。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukori/ukorigi005.mp3'),('out-in-force','in','null','null\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'null'),('outpost','前哨','Qiánshào','\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=outpost &tl=ja&tk=945297.547045&client=webapp&prev=input'),('pale','（脸色或肤色）苍白的，白的暗淡的；浅的，淡的变苍白，失去血色','uk :peɪl, us :peɪl','[You re looking pale - are you feeling well? \n 你看上去脸色苍白——你病了吗？ \n, She has a naturally pale complexion and dark hair. \n 她天生肤色白皙，头发乌黑。 \n, She wore a pale blue hat. \n 她戴着一顶浅蓝色的帽子。 \n, pale winter sunlight \n 冬天惨淡的日光 \n, His face paled and he looked as if he might faint. \n 他脸色变得苍白，看上去像要晕倒一样。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpad/ukpaddl025.mp3'),('palm','手掌，手心给（某人）看手相（算命）棕榈树（变戏法或偷窃时）把…藏在手心内','uk :pɑːm, us :pɑːm','[This tiny device fits into the palm of your hand. \n 这种微型装置可以放入你的掌心。 \n, date palms \n 枣椰树 \n, palm fronds \n 棕榈叶 \n, The island has long golden beaches fringed by palm trees. \n 这个小岛周围金色海滩绵延，环抱于绿色的棕榈中。 \n, I suspected that he had palmed a playing card. \n 我怀疑他把一张纸牌藏在了手心里。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpal/ukpalef019.mp3'),('panel','（选定的）专家小组嵌板，镶板仪表板；操纵台嵌板，镶板','uk :ˈpæn.əl, us :ˈpæn.əl','[The competition will be judged by a panel of experts. \n 这次竞赛将由一个专家小组来评判。 \n, a beautiful old door with oak panels \n 一扇嵌有橡木板的漂亮的老式门 \n, White silk panels were inset into the sides of the dress. \n 衣边镶有白绸布。 \n, At the bottom of each page is a panel with grammatical information. \n 每页底部都有语法知识板块。 \n, a control/instrument panel \n 控制／仪表板 \n, The walls of the dining hall were panelled in oak. \n 餐厅的墙上嵌了橡木板。 \n, a panelled room/wall/door \n 有镶板的房间／墙／门 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpam/ukpampe018.mp3'),('parasite','寄生生物；寄生动物；寄生植物靠他人为生者，寄生虫','uk :ˈpær.ə.saɪt, us :ˈper.ə.saɪt','[The older drugs didn t deal effectively with the malaria parasite. \n 以前的药物不能有效对付引起疟疾的寄生虫。 \n, Financial speculators are parasites on the national economy. \n 金融投机者是国民经济的寄生虫。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparag030.mp3'),('parlor','（提供某种服务或销售某种商品的）店堂，店铺（尤指旧时的）起居室，客厅，会客室','uk :ˈpɑː.lər, us :ˈpɑːr.lɚ','[a beauty parlour \n 美容院 \n, an ice-cream/pizza parlour \n 冷饮店／比萨屋 \n, the front parlour \n 前厅 \n, an Edwardian parlour \n 爱德华七世时代的客厅 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparis016.mp3'),('parlour','（提供某种服务或销售某种商品的）店堂，店铺（尤指旧时的）起居室，客厅，会客室','uk :ˈpɑː.lər, us :ˈpɑːr.lɚ','[a beauty parlour \n 美容院 \n, an ice-cream/pizza parlour \n 冷饮店／比萨屋 \n, the front parlour \n 前厅 \n, an Edwardian parlour \n 爱德华七世时代的客厅 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparis016.mp3'),('particle','小品词，语助词微粒，粒子极小量','uk :ˈpɑː.tɪ.kəl, us :ˈpɑːr.t̬ə.kəl','[In the sentence  I tidied up the room , the adverb  up  is a particle. \n 在句子 I tidied up the room 中，副词 up 是个小品词。 \n, Dust particles must have got into the motor. \n 发动机里一定是进灰了。 \n, Electrons are atomic particles. \n 电子是原子粒子。 \n, She wouldn t give me even the slightest particle of information about what she d been doing. \n 对于她所做的事情，她一丁点消息都不会透露给我。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparsi022.mp3'),('particularly','特别，尤其，异乎寻常地','uk :pəˈtɪk.jə.lə.li, us :pɚˈtɪk.jə.lɚ.li','[We\'re particularly interested to hear from people who speak two or more European languages. \n 我们特别希望能收到说两种或两种以上欧洲语言的人的来信。 \n, I didn\'t particularly want to go, but I had to. \n 我并不是特别想去，但我不得不去。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparsi026.mp3'),('partnerships','合伙关系，伙伴关系合伙企业，合股公司','uk :ˈpɑːt.nə.ʃɪp, us :ˈpɑːrt.nɚ.ʃɪp','[the John Lewis Partnership \n 约翰‧刘易斯合伙公司 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparti006.mp3'),('pathogen','病原体','uk :ˈpæθ.ə.dʒən, us :ˈpæθ.ə.dʒən','[a dangerous pathogen \n 一种危险的病原体 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpat/ukpatch023.mp3'),('patriot','爱国者','uk :ˈpæt.ri.ət, us :ˈpeɪ.tri.ɑːt',NULL,'2020-01-20',4,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpat/ukpatie016.mp3'),('pattern','方式，形式；模式图案，花样范本，典范；榜样图样，底样样品，样本','uk :ˈpæt.ən, us :ˈpæt̬.ɚn','[The pattern of family life has been changing over recent years. \n 近年来家庭生活的模式一直在变化。 \n, A pattern is beginning to emerge from our analysis of the accident data. \n 我们对事故数据进行分析后发现一种模式开始显现出来。 \n, In this type of mental illness, the usual pattern is bouts of depression alternating with elation. \n 这种精神病通常的发病症状是时而萎靡不振，时而兴高采烈。 \n, Many behaviour(al) patterns have been identified in the chimp colony. \n 黑猩猩群体中的许多行为模式已被识别。 \n, Look, the frost has made a beautiful pattern on the window. \n 看啊，霜在窗户上形成了美丽的图案。 \n, The curtains had a floral pattern. \n 窗帘上有花的图案。 \n, The design is so good it s sure to set the pattern for many others. \n 这个设计太好了，一定会成为许多其他设计的样板。 \n, a knitting pattern \n 编织图样 \n, a dress pattern \n 服装底样 \n, Cut out all of the pieces from the paper pattern and pin them on the cloth. \n 剪下服装纸样上的每一片，把它们别在布上。 \n, a pattern book \n 样书 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpat/ukpatie028.mp3'),('pearl','珍珠珍珠首饰人造珍珠液态珠状物珠灰色，银白色珍珠母（同 mother-of-pearl）','uk :pɜːl, us :pɝːl','[a string of pearls \n 一串珍珠 \n, a pearl necklace \n 珍珠项链 \n, He gave her pearls for her birthday. \n 他送给她珍珠首饰作为生日礼物。 \n, cultured pearls \n 养殖的珍珠 \n, There were pearls of dew on the grass. \n 草地上有点点露珠。 \n, pearl buttons \n 珍珠母纽扣 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpay/ukpayro030.mp3'),('penitence','忏悔苦行','uk :ˈpen.ɪ.təns, us :ˈpen.ə.təns','[e expressed penitence for what he had done.\n, She cried tears of penitence.\n, e expressed his penitence for what he had done.\n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpenet008.mp3'),('pension','养老金；退休金；抚恤金','uk :ˈpen.ʃən, us :ˈpen.ʃən','[S \n a government pension \n 政府养老金 \n, K \n a state pension. \n 政府养老金 \n, He won\'t be able to draw (= receive) his pension until he\'s 65. \n 他得等到65岁以后才能领取养老金。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpenet022.mp3'),('pentagon','五边形，五角形美国五角大楼，美国国防部','uk :ˈpen.tə.ɡən, us :-t̬ə.ɡɑːn','[The Pentagon is aiming to cut US forces by over 25 percent in the next five years. \n 美国国防部计划在接下来的五年内裁军25%以上。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpenet027.mp3'),('perception','认识，观念，看法感觉，知觉；感知感知能力；认识能力；洞察力','uk :pəˈsep.ʃən, us :pɚ-','[We have to change the public s perception that money is being wasted. \n 公众认为是在浪费钱，我们必须改变他们的这种看法。 \n, These photographs will affect people s perceptions of war. \n 这些照片会影响人们对战争的看法。 \n, Drugs can alter your perception of reality. \n 毒品会改变你对现实的感知。 \n, She has extraordinary powers of perception for one so young. \n 她年纪轻轻就有着非凡的洞察力。 \n, He s not known for his perception. \n 他的洞察力并不怎么样。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpente025.mp3'),('perch','坐在…（的边缘）上；栖息于；停留于（使）位于高处（或…的边缘）；（使）栖息在高处（或…的边缘）河鲈（鸟的）栖息处（尤指鸟笼里的细杆）（常指能很好地俯视低处的）高座，高处','uk :pɜːtʃ, us :pɝːtʃ','[We perched on bar stools and had a beer. \n 我们坐在酒吧高凳上，喝了一杯啤酒。 \n, A blackbird was perching on the gate. \n 一只乌鸫停落在大门上。 \n, The village is perched on top of a high hill. \n 村子坐落在一个高山顶上。 \n, We watched the parade from our perch on the scaffolding. \n 我们从脚手架的高处观看游行。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpente029.mp3'),('peril','巨大的危险；险情，险境自冒风险做…','uk :ˈper.əl, us :ˈper.əl','[I never felt that my life was in peril. \n 我从未意识到我的生命受到了严重的威胁。 \n, The journey through the mountains was fraught with peril (= full of dangers). \n 穿越山岭的旅途充满了危险。 \n, Teenagers must be warned about the perils of unsafe sex. \n 必须告诫青少年不安全性行为存在重大危险。 \n, We underestimate the destructiveness of war at our peril. \n 我们低估了战争的破坏性，这对我们是很危险的。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperfu006.mp3'),('permanently','总是；持久地；永久地','uk :ˈpɜː.mə.nənt.li, us :ˈpɝː.mə.nənt.li','[Smoking is likely to damage your health permanently. \n 吸烟可能会永久性地损害你的健康。 \n, Michael and his family have settled permanently in the States. \n 迈克尔和他的家人在美国永久定居下来。 \n, I seem to be permanently broke. \n 我似乎永远一贫如洗。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperki009.mp3'),('perpetrate','犯（罪）；施（暴）；干（坏事）','uk :ˈpɜː.pə.treɪt, us :ˈpɝː.pə.treɪt','[In this country, half of all violent crime is perpetrated by people who have been drinking alcohol. \n 在这个国家，一半的暴行是酗酒者犯下的。 \n, Federal soldiers have been accused of perpetrating atrocities against innocent people. \n 联邦士兵被控对无辜民众犯下暴行。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperki026.mp3'),('perpetual','永久的，永恒的；长期的不断重复的；永无休止的','uk :pəˈpetʃ.u.əl, us :pɚˈpetʃ.u.əl','[They lived in perpetual fear of being discovered. \n 他们长期生活在恐惧中，担心被发现。 \n, He has hard, cold eyes and his mouth is set in a perpetual sneer. \n 他双眼又凶又冷，嘴角总是挂着一丝蔑笑。 \n, a perpetual student \n 终生学习者 \n, perpetual vandalism \n 对公共财物不断的蓄意破坏 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperki029.mp3'),('persist','持续；存留坚持不懈；执意','uk :pəˈsɪst, us :pɚˈsɪst','[If the pain persists, consult a doctor. \n 如果疼痛持续就去看医生。 \n, The cold weather is set to persist throughout the week. \n 寒冷天气很可能将持续整个星期。 \n, If he persists in asking awkward questions, then send him to the boss. \n 如果他没完没了地问令人尴尬的问题，就把他打发到老板那里去。 \n, The government is persisting with its ambitious public works programme. \n 政府在坚持实施其雄心勃勃的市政工程规划。 \n]\n','2020-01-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperpe018.mp3'),('persistent','持续的；存留的；顽强存在的坚持不懈的；执意的','uk :pəˈsɪs.tənt, us :pɚˈsɪs.tənt','[a persistent smell/skin rash \n 持续不散的气味／顽固的皮疹 \n, Symptoms of the illness include a high temperature and a persistent dry cough. \n 病症包括高烧和持久的干咳。 \n, There have been persistent rumours that the principal might take early retirement. \n 不断有谣言说校长可能会提前退休。 \n, Be persistent - don t give up. \n 要坚持不懈——别放弃。 \n, He has been a persistent critic of the president. \n 他一贯对总统持批评态度。 \n, She is a persistent offender and has been arrested five times this year for shoplifting. \n 她是个惯犯，今年已5次因在商店行窃被捕。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperpe020.mp3'),('pervert','侵害；歪曲；使走上邪路，使变坏妨碍司法公正，枉法性行为反常者，性变态者','uk :pəˈvɜːt, us :pɚˈvɝːt','[Her ideas have been shamelessly perverted to serve the president s propaganda campaign. \n 为了配合总统的宣传活动，她的想法被无耻地曲解了。 \n, The history teacher tried to pervert (= persuade into unacceptable sexual activity) the boys by showing them pornographic magazines. \n 这名历史教师给男学生们看色情杂志，想引他们走上邪路。 \n, The two police officers were charged with perverting the course of justice by fabricating evidence in the trial. \n 两名警官因在审判中伪造证据被控妨碍司法公正。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperv_011.mp3'),('pestilence','瘟疫，疫病毒瘤，日益严重的问题','uk :ˈpes.tɪ.ləns, us :ˈpes.təl.əns','[The report states that vandalism is a pestilence that must be stamped out. \n 该报告说明，恶意破坏行为是一种毒瘤，必须铲除。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperv_023.mp3'),('petition','请愿书（向法院递交的）上诉书，诉状（向法院）递交上诉书，上诉','uk :pəˈtɪʃ.ən, us :pəˈtɪʃ.ən','[I signed a petition against the proposed closure of the local hospital today. \n 今天我在反对关闭当地医院的请愿书上签了名。 \n, She s filing a petition for divorce. \n 她将要递交离婚诉状。 \n, They re petitioning for/about better facilities for disabled people. \n 他们正在请愿，希望当局能为残疾人安装更好的设施。 \n, [ + obj + to infinitive ] \n I think we should petition the government to increase the grant for the project. \n 我认为我们应该请求政府增加对该项目的拨款。 \n, She is petitioning for a re-trial. \n 她将上诉要求重审。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpet/ukpeter006.mp3'),('phase-out','停用','null','null\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'null'),('phony','虚伪的；假冒的，伪造的','uk :ˈfəʊ.ni, us :ˈfoʊ.ni','[All salespeople seem to have the same phoney smile. \n 所有推销员的微笑似乎都一样，假惺惺的。 \n, He gave the police a phoney address. \n 他给了警察一个假地址。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpho/ukphone004.mp3'),('phrase','短语说法；用语；警句乐句；乐节用…方式表达，以…措词表达','uk :freɪz, us :freɪz','[We are governed, in Lord Hailsham s famous phrase, by an  elective dictatorship . \n 套用一下黑尔什姆勋爵的名言，我们被“选举出来的独裁者”统治着。 \n, The declaration was carefully/cleverly/tactfully, etc. phrased. \n 宣言措词谨慎／巧妙／圆滑等。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpho/ukphoto010.mp3'),('physicist','物理学家','uk :ˈfɪz.ɪ.sɪst, us :ˈfɪz.ɪ.sɪst',NULL,'2019-12-27',1,3,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpho/ukphoto018.mp3'),('pick','挑选；选择挑挑拣拣；精挑细选从…上剔除，从…摘下（从植物或树上）采，摘弹拨，弹奏（吉他等弦乐器）挑选；选择可以挑选；任意挑选挑选，选择镐；鹤嘴锄（同 pickaxe）牙签（弹弦乐器用的）拨子，琴拨','uk :pɪk, us :pɪk','[Pick a card from the pack. \n 从这纸牌中挑出一张。 \n, One of my sisters has been picked for the Olympic team. \n 我的一个姐姐入选了奥运代表队。 \n, [ + obj + to infinitive ] \n She was picked to play for the team. \n 她被选中代表该队参赛。 \n, The police asked him if he could pick (out) the killer from a series of photos. \n 警察问他能否从一组照片中认出凶手。 \n, The fairest way to decide the winner is to pick a name out of a hat/at random (= without looking or choosing). \n 决出优胜者最公平的办法是任意／随机选取一个名字。 \n, They picked their way (= carefully chose a route) down the broken steps. \n 他们小心翼翼地走下断裂的台阶。 \n, He s brilliant at picking winners (= choosing what will be successful). \n 他在判断谁能获胜方面很有眼力。 \n, The richest universities can pick and choose which students they take. \n 最有钱的大学可以对生源精挑细选。 \n, I picked a piece of fluff off my shiny black suit. \n 我从闪闪发亮的黑色套装上拽掉一根绒毛。 \n, The child continued picking (at) a sore on his leg (= trying to remove parts of it with his fingers). \n 那个孩子不停地抓挠他腿上的疮。 \n, [ + obj + adj ] \n The carcass had been picked clean (= all the flesh had been removed) by other animals and birds. \n 动物尸体上的肉已被别的动物和鸟吃得干干净净。 \n, isapproving \n He kept picking his nose (= removing mucus from it with his finger). \n 他在不停地掏鼻孔。 \n, They were picking strawberries for twelve hours a day. \n 他们每天摘12小时的草莓。 \n, I picked some roses this morning. \n 今天早上我摘了一些玫瑰。 \n, Machines pick the fruit (from/off the trees). \n 机器把果子（从树上）摘下来。 \n, You can have first pick of the desserts. \n 你可以头一个挑选甜点。 \n, The plane was fairly empty so we had our pick of seats. \n 飞机很空，所以我们可以自由选择座位。 \n, The shirts come in five different colours - just take your pick. \n 这种衬衣有5种不同的颜色——你随便挑吧。 \n, picks and shovels \n 镐和铲 \n, a toothpick \n 牙签 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpia/ukpiano004.mp3'),('pickle','腌菜，泡菜；菜酱醋渍黄瓜（片）；腌黄瓜（片）（用醋或盐水）腌制，腌渍','uk :ˈpɪk.əl, us :ˈpɪk.əl','[cheese and pickle sandwiches \n 奶酪和腌菜三明治 \n, Have some pickles with your sandwich. \n 在色拉里加些泡菜。 \n, a sweet/sour pickle \n 甜／酸黄瓜 \n, The onions had been pickled in brine. \n 洋葱已经在卤水中腌过了。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpia/ukpiano016.mp3'),('pierce','刺穿，刺透，刺破（光、声音等）透入，进入','uk :pɪəs, us :pɪrs','[The needle pierces the fabric four times a second. \n 针穿过织物的速度是每秒钟4次。 \n, I couldn t wear these earrings because my ears aren t pierced. \n 我没法戴这些耳环，因为我没有穿耳孔。 \n, The gun fires a shell capable of piercing the armour of an enemy tank. \n 这种炮发射的炮弹能穿透敌人坦克的装甲。 \n, The hole they drilled pierces six kilometres into the earth s crust. \n 他们钻的孔深入地壳6公里。 \n, A few rays of sunlight pierced the smoke. \n 几缕阳光穿透了烟幕。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpic/ukpictu012.mp3'),('pile','摞；垛；堆一堆一大堆，许多（建筑物的）柱，桩（地毯或天鹅绒等布料的）绒面高大建筑物，大厦痔，痔疮把…堆积（或堆叠）起来（人群）拥，挤，蜂拥','uk :paɪl, us :paɪl','[a pile of books \n 一摞书 \n, a pile of dirty clothes \n 一大堆脏衣服 \n, a large pile of sand \n 一大堆沙子 \n, I ve got piles/a pile of things to do today. \n 我今天有一大堆事情要做。 \n, a luxurious deep-pile carpet \n 豪华的长毛地毯 \n, They ve got a great big Victorian pile somewhere out in the country. \n 他们在乡下的某个地方有一座雄伟的维多利亚式的房子。 \n, We piled plenty of logs up next to the fire. \n 我们在炉火旁堆了很多木柴。 \n, Please pile your homework books neatly on the table as you leave. \n 离开时请把你们的作业本整齐地叠放在桌子上。 \n, Her plate was piled (high) with salad. \n 她的盘子里盛满了色拉。 \n, Snow had piled up against the walls. \n 雪在墙根堆积起来。 \n, As soon as the train stopped, they all piled in/out. \n 火车刚停下，他们就挤了进去／出来。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpig/ukpigmy016.mp3'),('pillage','（尤指在战争中）掠夺，抢劫，劫掠','uk :ˈpɪl.ɪdʒ, us :ˈpɪl.ɪdʒ','[Works of art were pillaged from many countries in the dark days of the Empire. \n 在该帝国一手遮天的黑暗时期，许多国家的艺术品被肆意掠夺。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpig/ukpigmy022.mp3'),('pillow','枕头坐垫；靠垫（同 cushion）','uk :ˈpɪl.əʊ, us :ˈpɪl.oʊ','[Do you prefer a feather pillow or a foam pillow? \n 你喜欢羽绒枕头还是海绵枕头？ \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpig/ukpigmy028.mp3'),('pipe','管；管子；管道烟斗笛（子）；管乐器（bagpipes 的另一种说法）（管风琴的）音管计算机键盘上的“|”键用尖嗓子说；尖声唱管道运输','uk :paɪp, us :paɪp','[a water/gas/sewer pipe \n 供水／煤气／下水管道 \n, a burst/fractured/leaking pipe \n 爆裂／破裂／泄漏的管道 \n, I ordered some tea for myself and lit my pipe. \n 我叫了茶，点着了烟斗。 \n, Hot water is piped to all apartments from the central boiler room. \n 热水从中央锅炉房通过管道输送到每个公寓套房。 \n, igurative \n Music is piped throughout the hotel complex. \n 音乐声在整座酒店大楼里回荡。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpin/ukpinkn023.mp3'),('pique','（尤指因自尊心受损而产生的）不悦，生气','uk :piːk, us :piːk','[He stormed from the room in a fit of pique, shouting that he had been misunderstood. \n 他怒气冲冲地冲出房间，嚷嚷着说他被误解了。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpay/ukpayro024.mp3'),('plank','木板；板条（尤指政治组织的）政纲条目，政策准则','uk :plæŋk, us :plæŋk','[oak/concrete planks \n 橡木／水泥板 \n, a plank of wood \n 一块木板条 \n, We used a plank to cross the ditch. \n 我们用一块跳板过了沟。 \n, Educational reform was one of the main planks of their election campaign. \n 教育改革是他们竞选活动的主要纲领之一。 \n, The party s policy is based on five central planks. \n 该党的政策基于5条中心政治纲领。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpla/ukplain011.mp3'),('plate','盘子，碟子一盘；一盘之量平板；板条；板材印版（书籍的）插图，彩色插图（棒球运动中的）本垒板（home plate的非正式说法）表面有镀层的金属制品贵重金属制品（尤指餐具）镀上；用（金、银等）覆镀','uk :pleɪt, us :pleɪt','[paper/plastic/china plates \n 纸／塑料／瓷盘子 \n, a dinner/salad plate \n 餐盘／色拉盘 \n, clean/dirty plates \n 干净／脏盘子 \n, There s still lots of food on your plate. \n 你的盘子里还有很多食物。 \n, Stephen ate three plates of spaghetti. \n 斯蒂芬吃了3盘意大利面条。 \n, Thick bony plates protected the dinosaur against attack. \n 厚厚的骨质鳞甲帮助恐龙抵御攻击。 \n, The ship s deck is composed of steel plates. \n 该船的甲板由钢板构成。 \n, The three birds differ in small features (see Plate 4). \n 这3只鸟的细微特征有区别（见插图4）。 \n, The knives and forks are silver plate. \n 这些刀叉是镀银的。 \n, The thieves got away with a large quantity of church plate. \n 小偷盗走了教堂中大量的餐具。 \n, We normally plate the car handles with nickel and then chrome. \n 我们通常先用镍再用铬来镀汽车的拉手。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpla/ukplate001.mp3'),('pledge','誓言；诺言；保证发誓；保证','uk :pledʒ, us :pledʒ','[[ + to infinitive ] \n All the candidates have given/made pledges not to raise taxes if they are elected. \n 所有的候选人都保证当选后不增税。 \n, Thousands of people made pledges (= promised to give money) to the charity campaign. \n 数千人许诺向救助儿童慈善运动捐款。 \n, I give you this ring as a pledge of my everlasting love for you. \n 我把这枚戒指送给你作为我永远爱你的信物。 \n, We are asking people to pledge their support for our campaign. \n 我们正请求人们承诺支持我们的运动。 \n, If you join the armed forces, you have to pledge allegiance to your country. \n 如果参军，你必须宣誓效忠你的祖国。 \n, So far, £50,000 has been pledged (= people have promised to pay this amount) in response to the appeal. \n 到目前为止，人们已承诺捐款5万英镑以响应这项呼吁。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n Both sides have pledged to end the fighting. \n 双方均已保证停战。 \n, I\'ve been pledged to secrecy. \n 我已发誓保守秘密。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukple/ukplebb008.mp3'),('ploy','计谋，策略；手法，花招','uk :plɔɪ, us :plɔɪ','[There are various ploys we can use if necessary. \n 必要的话，我们可以用各种手段。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n He only said he had a meeting as a ploy to get her to leave. \n 他说他有一个会议要参加，只是为了把她支开。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukplo/ukplodd014.mp3'),('plunge','（使）（某人或某物）骤然移动，骤然下降（价值或程度）暴跌，骤降跳入；下跌；落下暴跌，骤降','uk :plʌndʒ, us :plʌndʒ','[We ran down to the beach and plunged into the sea. \n 我们跑向海滩，纵身跳入海中。 \n, The car went out of control and plunged over the cliff. \n 轿车失去控制坠下悬崖。 \n, Cook the peas by plunging them into boiling water. \n 把豌豆倒入沸水中煮。 \n, Niagara Falls plunges 55.5 metres. \n 尼亚加拉大瀑布落差为55.5米。 \n, The fall in demand caused share prices to plunge. \n 需求下降导致股价大幅下跌。 \n, Our income has plunged dramatically. \n 我们的收入骤减。 \n, I really enjoyed my plunge (= jumping in and swimming) in the pool. \n 我很喜欢在游泳池里跳水游泳。 \n, We are expecting a plunge in profits this year. \n 我们预计今年利润将大幅下降。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukplu/ukplump004.mp3'),('pneumonia','肺炎得肺炎','uk :njuːˈməʊ.ni.ə, us :nuːˈmoʊ.njə','[People who are bedridden can easily get pneumonia. \n 长期卧床的人易患肺炎。 \n, She ll catch pneumonia going out without a coat in this weather! \n 她这种天气不穿大衣出去会得肺炎的！ \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpmt/ukpmt__004.mp3'),('poignancy','激痛','uk :ˈpɔɪ.njən.si, us :ˈpɔɪ.njən.si','[he production took on added poignancy due to the director\'s recent death.\n, The poem has a haunting poignancy.\n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpog/ukpogos003.mp3'),('pole','杆，柱（地球的）极（点）（意见、立场或特点）截然相反的一端，极端波兰人','uk :pəʊl, us :poʊl','[a telegraph/electricity pole \n 电线杆 \n, A flag fluttered from a 40-foot pole. \n 一面旗帜在40英尺高的旗杆上飘扬。 \n, the North/South Pole \n 北／南极 \n, Most weather satellites are stationed over the Equator or travel over the poles. \n 大部分气象卫星定位于赤道上空或绕地球两极飞行。 \n, These two men might be thought to represent the opposite poles of economic ideology. \n 这两个人可能被认为是两种截然相反的经济思想体系的代表者。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpol/ukpolar007.mp3'),('pop-out','弹出','Dànchū','\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=pop-out&tl=ja&tk=443174.63314&client=webapp&prev=input'),('pope','教皇（头衔）','uk :pəʊp, us :poʊp','[Pope John Paul II \n 教皇约翰•保罗二世 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpon/ukponti022.mp3'),('popinjay','自负的家伙','uk :ˈpɒp.ɪn.dʒeɪ, us :ˈpɑː.pɪn.dʒeɪ','[e regarded his rival as a conceited popinjay.\n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0318ukpopi1094.mp3'),('populist','平民主义的；民粹主义的','uk :ˈpɒp.jə.lɪst, us :ˈpɑː.pjə.lɪst','[a populist manifesto \n 民粹主义宣言 \n, a populist leader \n 民粹主义领袖 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpop/ukpopsi013.mp3'),('portfolios','公文包；文件夹（尤指艺术家的）代表作选辑（个人或机构的）投资组合（部长或大臣）职务；（部长或大臣）职责不管部的（指在英国政府中任要职但并不具体负责某个部门）','uk :ˌpɔːtˈfəʊ.li.əʊ, us :ˌpɔːrtˈfoʊ.li.oʊ','[She\'s trying to build up a portfolio of work to show during job interviews. \n 她正想整理出自己的代表作以便找工作面试时展示一下。 \n, The prime minister offered her the foreign affairs portfolio. \n 首相邀请她出任外交部长。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta013.mp3'),('portion','一部分；一份（食物的）一份，一客','uk :ˈpɔː.ʃən, us :ˈpɔːr.ʃən','[A large/major portion of the company s profit goes straight back into new projects. \n 公司利润的一大部分／主要部分又直接投入了新的项目。 \n, I accept my portion of the blame. \n 我承担部分责任。 \n, The portions are very generous in this restaurant. \n 这家饭店每份菜量都很足。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta019.mp3'),('portrait','肖像，画像；人像照片电影（或书中）的描写，描述；表现竖向（描述计算机文件打印的一种方式，即纸的短边置于顶部和底部）','uk :ˈpɔː.trət, us :ˈpɔːr.trɪt','[She s commissioned an artist to paint her portrait/paint a portrait of her. \n 她委托一位画家为她画一幅肖像。 \n, a portrait gallery \n 肖像画廊 \n, a portrait painter \n 肖像画家 \n, Her latest novel paints a very vivid portrait of the aristocracy in the 1920s. \n 她最新的一部小说生动地描绘了20世纪20年代的贵族生活。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta025.mp3'),('portray','描绘，描述，描写把（某人）刻画成，将（某人）塑造成','uk :pɔːˈtreɪ, us :pɔːrˈtreɪ',NULL,'2020-02-14',11,4,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta027.mp3'),('possum','负鼠（同 opossum）','uk :ˈpɒs.əm, us :ˈpɑː.səm','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpos/ukposer023.mp3'),('pouch','小袋；一小袋东西（某些雌性动物的）育儿袋（某些动物贮存食物的）喉囊，颊袋','uk :paʊtʃ, us :paʊtʃ','[All our electric shavers are supplied with a free travel pouch. \n 我们的电动剃须刀都免费提供一个旅行套。 \n, Food sealed in foil pouches lasts for a long time. \n 密封在箔纸袋中的食物可以放很长时间。 \n, Kangaroos carry their young in pouches. \n 袋鼠将它们的幼崽放在育儿袋中。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpot/ukpotti003.mp3'),('precious','珍贵的，宝贵的过分讲究的，做作的（表示讨厌和／或恼怒）宝贝似的极其，非常（同 very）','uk :ˈpreʃ.əs, us :ˈpreʃ.əs','[a precious gift \n 珍贵的礼物 \n, a precious moment/memory \n 宝贵的时刻／记忆 \n, Clean water is a precious commodity in many parts of the world. \n 在世界上很多地方洁净的水是昂贵的商品。 \n, You re so precious to me. \n 你对我来说就是珍宝。 \n, He s so precious about his work that he never gets anything done. \n 他对自己的活儿太讲究了，反而什么都做不成。 \n, Don t you hate the precious way she speaks, pronouncing each single consonant so precisely. \n 她讲话做作的样子真让人讨厌，每个辅音都发得那么准确。 \n, You and your precious car - it s all you re interested in! \n 你心里只有你和你那辆宝贝车！ \n, Lots of people will start, but precious few will finish. \n 许多人将开始去做，但极少数能完成。 \n, Be careful - you ll be precious little help if you come back injured. \n 小心——如果你受了伤回来就帮不上什么忙了。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpra/ukpraye022.mp3'),('precise','精确的；准确的，确切的（尤指在细节上）严谨的，细致的','uk :prɪˈsaɪs, us :prəˈsaɪs','[The bunker s precise location is a closely guarded secret. \n 掩体的确切位置严格保密。 \n, He caught me at the precise moment that I fainted. \n 他正好在我晕倒的那一刻抓住了我。 \n, There was a good turnout for the meeting - twelve of us to be precise. \n 出席会议的人不少——确切地说有我们12个人。 \n, Years of doing meticulous research had made her very precise in her working methods. \n 多年来一丝不苟的研究使她养成了严谨的工作方法。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukpreci003.mp3'),('premium','奖金，津贴；加价；附加费保险费优质汽油，高级汽油（品质）高级的；优质的，顶级的','uk :ˈpriː.mi.əm, us :','[We re willing to pay a premium for the best location. \n 为了得到最好的地段，我们愿意多支付些钱。 \n, Because of their location, these offices attract a premium. \n 由于地段好，这些办公室租金更高。 \n, The modified cars are available at a premium of five percent over the original price. \n 改进后的汽车的售价要比原价高5%。 \n, The busy shopper puts a premium on (= appreciates and will pay more for) finding everything in one big store. \n 时间有限的购物者若能在一家大商店买齐所有的东西，价钱高点儿也是愿意的。 \n, Car insurance premiums have increased this year. \n 今年汽车保险费涨了。 \n, The premiums for healthcare plans are high. \n 保健计划的保险费很高。 \n, premium ice cream \n 优质冰激凌 \n, The building is on a premium site. \n 这幢大楼建在一块风水宝地上。 \n]\n','2019-12-10',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukpremi005.mp3'),('prerogative','独有的权利（或权力），特权','uk :prɪˈrɒɡ.ə.tɪv, us :prɪˈrɑː.ɡə.t̬ɪv',NULL,'2020-01-07',2,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprepo008.mp3'),('president','总统；国家主席（机构的）负责人，会长，主席；（尤指美国的）总裁，董事长','uk :ˈprez.ɪ.dənt, us :ˈprez.ɪ.dənt','[President Kennedy \n 肯尼迪总统 \n, the president of France \n 法国总统 \n, [ as form of address ] \n Thank you, Mr/Madam President. \n 谢谢您，总统阁下。 \n, a former president of the Royal Society \n 皇家学会的前会长 \n, ainly US \n She s a friend of the president of the bank. \n 她是银行总裁的朋友。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprese007.mp3'),('prevention','阻止，妨碍；预防','uk :prɪˈven.ʃən, us :prɪˈven.ʃən','[crime prevention \n 预防犯罪 \n, The organization is committed to AIDS prevention and education. \n 该组织致力于艾滋病的预防和教育。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprete023.mp3'),('pride','自豪，得意为…自豪，为…骄傲自尊（心）自负，骄傲狮群','uk :praɪd, us :praɪd','[She felt a great sense of pride as she watched him accept the award. \n 看着他接过那个奖，她感到非常自豪。 \n, He felt such pride walking his little daughter down the street. \n 他陪着小女儿在街上走，感到非常自豪。 \n, If you don t take professional pride in your work, you re probably in the wrong job. \n 如果你对自己的工作没有职业自豪感，那可能是入错了行。 \n, She has too much pride to accept any help. \n 她自尊心太强，不肯接受任何帮助。 \n, The country s national pride has been damaged by its sporting failures. \n 体育方面的失利使这个国家的民族自尊心受到了伤害。 \n, Pride was his downfall. \n 骄傲是他失败的原因。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpri/ukprice009.mp3'),('primarily','主要地','uk :praɪˈmer.əl.i, us :praɪˈmer.əl.i','[We re primarily concerned with keeping expenditure down. \n 我们主要关心的是缩减开支。 \n, Baseball is primarily a summer game. \n 篮球基本上是一项夏季运动。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpri/ukprice024.mp3'),('primeval','原始的；早期的','uk :praɪˈmiː.vəl, us :praɪˈmiː.vəl','[primeval forests \n 原始森林 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpri/ukprice029.mp3'),('profile','传略；人物简介公众注意（面部的）侧面（像）','uk :ˈprəʊ.faɪl, us :ˈproʊ.faɪl','[We need to increase our company s profile in Asia. \n 我们需要扩大公司在亚洲的影响力。 \n, There is a growing number of women in high-profile positions (= positions which they are noticed) in the government. \n 在备受注目的政府职位上，女性的数量在逐渐增长。 \n, Drawing profiles is somehow easier than drawing the full face. \n 不知为什么画侧面像要比画整张脸容易。 \n, a strong profile \n 轮廓分明的侧影 \n, The actor is photographed in profile, smoking a cigarette. \n 这个演员被人从侧面拍了一张抽烟的照片。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprofi002.mp3'),('profit','利润，盈利开始盈利好处，益处','uk :ˈprɒf.ɪt, us :ˈprɑː.fɪt','[She makes a big profit from selling waste material to textile companies. \n 她将废弃材料卖给纺织公司，从中赚取大笔利润。 \n, A year ago the Tokyo company had a pretax profit of 35 million yen. \n 一年以前，东京公司的税前利润是3500万日元。 \n, Company profits are down from last year s figures. \n 从去年的统计数字看，公司的利润下降了。 \n, You don t expect to make much profit within the first couple of years of setting up a company. \n 你不要指望在开办公司的头几年里赚取很多利润。 \n, He sold his house at a huge profit. \n 他卖掉自己的房子，赚了很多钱。 \n, He’s been in business five years, but has not yet turned a profit. \n 他进入这个行业已有五年，但还没有开始盈利。 \n, There s no profit to be gained from endlessly discussing whose fault it was. \n 没完没了地讨论谁是谁非是徒劳无益的。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprofi003.mp3'),('profound','强烈的；深沉的；极度的造诣深的；思想深邃的','uk :prəˈfaʊnd, us :prəˈfaʊnd',NULL,'2020-02-14',8,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprofi013.mp3'),('progressive','逐渐的；渐进的（指思想或体制）进步的，先进的累进（税）的（动词）进行时的支持进步政策者；改革派人士','uk :prəˈɡres.ɪv, us :prəˈɡres.ɪv','[There s been a progressive decline in the standard of living over the past few years. \n 最近几年的生活水平每况愈下。 \n, a progressive disease \n 慢性病 \n, progressive ideas/attitudes \n 进步的思想／态度 \n, The left of the party is pressing for a more progressive social policy. \n 该政党的左派敦促实行更加进步的社会政策。 \n, a progressive school \n 实行进步教育法的学校 \n,  He s working hard at the moment  is an example of the present progressive form of the verb  work . \n He s working hard at the moment 是动词 work 的现在进行时的一个例子。 \n,  I was eating when the phone rang  is an example of the past progressive. \n I was eating when the phone rang 是过去进行时的一个例子。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprogr002.mp3'),('prohibition','禁止；禁令禁酒时期（1920至1933年间美国禁止生产和销售酒的时期）','uk :ˌprəʊ.ɪˈbɪʃ.ən, us :ˌproʊ.ɪˈbɪʃ.ən','[New York City has announced a prohibition on smoking on buses. \n 纽约市宣布禁止在公共汽车上吸烟。 \n, The environmental group is demanding a complete prohibition against the hunting of whales. \n 该环保团体要求彻底禁止捕猎鲸鱼。 \n, It s my feeling that the money spent on drug prohibition would be better spent on information and education. \n 我觉得花钱禁毒不如把钱用在信息和教育上。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprogr005.mp3'),('projectile','投掷物；抛射物；发射物（尤指子弹、炮弹等）投射的，推进的','uk :prəˈdʒek.taɪl, us :prəˈdʒek.təl','[The second projectile exploded after hitting a tank. \n 第二发炮弹击中坦克后爆炸了。 \n, projectile weapons \n 投射武器 \n, projectile vomiting \n 喷射性呕吐 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprogr011.mp3'),('prone','易于遭受（疾病）的；有（消极）倾向的俯卧的，趴着的较常碰到…问题的','uk :prəʊn, us :proʊn','[I ve always been prone to headaches. \n 我总是容易头疼。 \n, He was prone to depression even as a teenager. \n 甚至在青少年时期他就容易情绪抑郁。 \n, She s prone to exaggerate, that s for sure. \n 她喜欢夸大其词，这一点是肯定的。 \n, The photograph showed a man lying prone on the pavement, a puddle of blood around his head. \n 这张照片上一名男子趴在人行道上，头部周围有一滩血。 \n, accident-prone \n 易出事故的 \n, injury-prone \n 易受伤的 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpromi022.mp3'),('proportion','部分；份额比率，比例（某物各个组成部分或一物与另一物之间的）相称，协调，均衡，匀称尺寸；大小；形状；程度重要性，严重性','uk :prəˈpɔː.ʃən, us :prəˈpɔːr.ʃən','[Children make up a large proportion of the world s population. \n 孩子占世界人口的很大一部分。 \n, A higher proportion of men are willing to share household responsibilities than used to be the case. \n 现在愿意共同承担家务的男人比例比过去要高。 \n, The report shows that poor families spend a larger proportion of their income on food. \n 报告显示，贫困家庭食物支出所占其收入比例更大了。 \n, The proportion of women to men at my college was about five to one. \n 我所在大学的男女比例大约为1：5。 \n, The chart shows how weight increases in proportion to height (= the increase in weight depends on the increase in height). \n 图表表明了体重是如何随身高成正比例上升的。 \n, The level of crime in an area is almost always in direct proportion to the number of unemployed. \n 一个地区的犯罪率几乎总是与失业人数成正比。 \n, Your legs are very much in proportion to (= the right size for) the rest of your body. \n 你的腿和你身体的其他部位比例非常协调。 \n, His feet seem very small in proportion to his body. \n 和他的身体相比，他的脚似乎显得太小了。 \n, My head was much nearer the camera than the rest of me so I m all out of proportion. \n 我的脑袋比身体其他部位离相机近得多，所以照片里我显得比例失调了。 \n, a building of elegant proportions \n 造型优美的建筑物 \n, I m not very good at drawing people - I can never get the proportions right. \n 我画人物不太在行——我从来都拿不准比例。 \n, umorous \n She s a woman of generous proportions (= she is fat). \n 她是个胖女人。 \n, A small worry in the back of your mind can for no apparent reason assume/take on massive proportions in the middle of the night. \n 内心深处的一点点忧虑在深夜里便会莫名其妙地无限放大。 \n, You have to keep a sense of proportion (= the ability to understand what is important and what is not). \n 你得会辨别轻重缓急。 \n, I think a certain amount of worry about work is very natural, but you ve got got to keep it in proportion (= judge correctly its seriousness). \n 我认为对工作有点担心是很自然的，但不要过分担心。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukproof030.mp3'),('proposal','建议；计划；提案求婚','uk :prəˈpəʊ.zəl, us :prəˈpoʊ.zəl','[Congress has rejected the latest economic proposal put forward by the President. \n 议会否决了总统最近提出的经济计划。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n There has been an angry reaction to the government\'s proposal to reduce unemployment benefit. \n 政府削减失业救济金的计划遭到了强烈的反对。 \n, Have you read Steve\'s proposals for the new project? \n 你看了史蒂夫对新项目的建议了吗？ \n, [ + that ] \n There was anger at the proposal that a UN peacekeeping force should be sent to the area. \n 有人对向该地区派遣联合国维和部队的建议很恼火。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpropo007.mp3'),('propose','建议；提议；提出提名，推荐（某人）担任某职（或参加某组织）求婚提议为…祝酒；提议为…干杯计划，打算','uk :prəˈpəʊz, us :prəˈpoʊz','[[ + that ] \n I propose that we wait until the budget has been announced before committing ourselves to any expenditure. \n 我建议我们在预算没有宣布以前不要有任何支出。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n He proposed dealing directly with the suppliers. \n 他提议直接和供应商打交道。 \n, She proposed a boycott of the meeting. \n 她建议抵制这次会议。 \n, He proposed a motion that the chairman resign. \n 他提出了一项让主席辞职的动议。 \n, To be nominated for union president you need one person to propose you and another to second you. \n 要被提名为工会主席，你需要有一个推荐人和一个附议人。 \n, I remember the night your father proposed to me. \n 我记得你父亲向我求婚的那个晚上。 \n, Now, if you\'d all please raise your glasses, I\'d like to propose a toast to the bride and groom. \n 现在，请大家举起酒杯，让我们为新郎和新娘干杯。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n How do you propose to complete the project in such a short time? \n 你打算怎样在这么短的时间内完成这个项目？ \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n How do you propose tackling this problem? \n 你打算怎么解决这个问题？ \n, I do not propose to reveal details at this stage. \n 我不打算在这个阶段透露细节。 \n, What we are proposing is a radical change in approach. \n 我们打算在方法上来个彻底转变。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpropo008.mp3'),('proposition','（通常指商业上的）提议，建议主张；观点；见解要求与（某人）发生性关系，向…提出猥亵的要求','uk :ˌprɒp.əˈzɪʃ.ən, us :ˌprɑː.pəˈzɪʃ.ən','[He wrote to me last week regarding a business proposition he thought might interest me. \n 他上周写信给我，提出一项他认为我会感兴趣的商业建议。 \n, I ve put my proposition to the company director for his consideration. \n 我已将我的提议交给公司主管考虑。 \n, They were debating the proposition that  All people are created equal . \n 他们正就“人人生而平等”这一命题展开辩论。 \n, I was propositioned by a complete stranger. \n 一个素不相识的人提出想和我上床。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpropo011.mp3'),('protocol','礼仪，礼节（正式的国际性）条约，公约，议定书规程，协议（计算机之间交换信息的计算机语言）','uk :ˈprəʊ.tə.kɒl, us :ˈproʊ.t̬ə.kɑːl','[a breach of Royal protocol \n 对皇家礼仪的违反 \n, diplomatic protocol \n 外交礼仪 \n, The Geneva Protocol of 1925 prohibits the use of poisonous gases in war. \n 1925年通过的《日内瓦公约》禁止在战争中使用有毒气体。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprote013.mp3'),('prowess','杰出的才能；高超的技能','uk :ˈpraʊ.es, us :ˈpraʊ.es',NULL,'2020-02-14',9,11,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprowe001.mp3'),('psychedelic','迷幻的','Mí huàn de','\n','2019-12-10',1,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=psychedelic &tl=ja&tk=313923.196151&client=webapp&prev=input'),('psycho','精神失常者，精神病人，变态人格者心理的，精神的','uk :ˈsaɪ.kəʊ, us :ˈsaɪ.koʊ','[The man s a psycho. \n 那个男子是个变态狂。 \n, psychopharmacology (= the study of drugs which affect the mind) \n 精神药理学 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpss/ukpsst_011.mp3'),('puff','喘气气喘吁吁吸（烟），抽（烟）吹，喷出，冒出一小口（烟雾），一小股（空气）泡夫，松饼吹捧文字，吹捧的言论气喘吁吁，呼吸急促吸烟，抽烟','uk :pʌf, us :pʌf','[He came puffing up the stairs. \n 他气喘吁吁地上了楼。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  I ran all the way home,  she puffed (= said while puffing). \n “我是一路跑回家的，”她气喘吁吁地说。 \n, She was puffing on a cigarette at the time. \n 她当时正在吸烟。 \n, He sat there, puffing away at a cigarette. \n 他坐在那里，抽着烟。 \n, The engine puffed a huge cloud of steam, then rolled down the tracks. \n 火车头喷出一大股水蒸气，沿着轨道开始移动。 \n, The chimney was puffing out clouds of smoke. \n 烟囱向外冒出一股股的烟。 \n, Sean blew a puff of smoke at his reflection in the mirror. \n 肖恩朝镜中的自己喷了一口烟。 \n, He hit the ground with his stick and a puff of dust rose up into the air. \n 他用拐杖敲打地面，扬起一股浮尘。 \n, a cream/jam puff \n 奶油／果酱松饼 \n, cheese puffs \n 奶酪松饼 \n, She took a puff on her cigarette and thought for a moment. \n 她抽了一口烟，沉思了一会儿。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpue/ukpueri002.mp3'),('pulmonary','肺的','uk :ˈpʊl.mə.nər.i, us :ˈpʊl.mə.ner.i','[the pulmonary artery \n 肺动脉 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpue/ukpueri019.mp3'),('pulse','脉搏测（某人的）脉搏（声波或光波的）脉冲豆类植物的种子；荚果；豆子（以规律且强有力的节拍）跳动，搏动，振动','uk :pʌls, us :pʌls','[The child s pulse was strong/weak. \n 那个孩子的脉搏很有力／虚弱。 \n, Exercise increases your pulse rate. \n 锻炼能加快你的脉搏。 \n, The data, normally transmitted electronically, can be changed into pulses of light. \n 这一数据通常是电子传送的，现在可被改为光波脉冲。 \n, Pulses include peas, lentils, and chickpeas. \n 豆类包括豌豆、小扁豆和鹰嘴豆。 \n, I could feel the blood pulsing through my veins. \n 我能感觉到血液在我的血管里翻腾。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpue/ukpueri025.mp3'),('purgatory','（天主教教义中的）炼狱，涤罪所痛苦的经历','uk :ˈpɜː.ɡə.tər.i, us :ˈpɝː.ɡə.tɔːr.i','[I ve been on a diet for two weeks now, and it s purgatory! \n 我已经节食两周了，真是太痛苦了！ \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpun/ukpunst021.mp3'),('puzzle','令人费解的情况；难题；谜测验智力的游戏（或玩具）（使）感到迷惑；（使）感到为难，（使）感到困窘','uk :ˈpʌz.əl, us :ˈpʌz.əl','[Scientists have been trying to solve this puzzle for years. \n 多年来科学家们一直试图解开这个谜。 \n, a jigsaw puzzle \n 智力拼图玩具 \n, a crossword puzzle \n 纵横字谜 \n, a puzzle book \n 谜语书 \n, The findings of the survey puzzle me - they re not at all what I would have expected. \n 调查的结果使我感到迷惑——它们根本不像我原本预料的那样。 \n, [ + question word ] \n It puzzles me why she said that. \n 我想不通她为什么那么说。 \n, Management are still puzzling about/over how the accident could have happened. \n 管理层仍对事故发生的原因感到迷惑不解。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukput/ukputz_002.mp3'),('quantitative','定量的','uk :ˈkwɒn.tɪ.tə.tɪv, us :ˈkwɑːn.t̬ə.teɪ.t̬ɪv','[quantitative analysis \n 定量分析 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukq/ukqua/ukquali017.mp3'),('quartz','石英','uk :ˈkwɔːts, us :ˈkwɔːrts','[]\n','2019-10-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukq/ukqua/ukquart004.mp3'),('racial','种族的；种族间的；种族关系的人种的，种族的；作为人种（或种族、民族）特点的','uk :ˈreɪ.ʃəl, us :ˈreɪ.ʃəl','[racial discrimination/prejudice \n 种族歧视／偏见 \n, He had a vision of a society living in racial harmony. \n 他梦想在一个社会中各种族能和谐共处。 \n, They are members of a racial minority. \n 他们属于一个少数民族。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrab/ukrabbi014.mp3'),('raise','举起；抬起；提起增加；提高；改善引起，导致；使存在养育；喂养；种植（赌牌时）比对手多下赌注，提高（赌注），加赌注解除；终止；解（禁）（尤指通过电话或无线电）与…取得联系，与…通话加薪','uk :reɪz, us :reɪz','[Would all those in favour please raise their hands? \n 赞成的人请举手好吗？ \n, He raised the window and leaned out. \n 他把窗户推上去后探出身子。 \n, Mary Quant was the first fashion designer to raise hemlines. \n 玛丽．匡特是第一个把裙子裁短的时装设计师。 \n, The government plan to raise taxes. \n 政府计划增税。 \n, I had to raise my voice (= speak more loudly) to make myself heard over the noise. \n 在一片喧哗声中，我不得不提高嗓门好让大家听见。 \n, The inspector said that standards at the school had to be raised. \n 督学说学校必须提高办学标准。 \n, Our little chat has raised my spirits (= made me feel happier). \n 我们闲聊了一小会儿，我的情绪好些了。 \n, Her answers raised doubts/fears/suspicions in my mind. \n 她的回答使我心里感到疑惑／害怕／怀疑。 \n, This discussion has raised many important issues/problems. \n 这次讨论引出了很多重要的议题／问题。 \n, The announcement raised a cheer/laugh. \n 该通知引起大家一片欢呼／哄堂大笑。 \n, I want to raise (= talk about) two problems/questions with you. \n 我想跟你探讨／问你两个问题。 \n, I want to start my own business if I can raise (= obtain) the money/cash/capital/funds. \n 如果我能够筹集到钱款／现金／资本／资金的话，我想创办自己的公司。 \n, ormal \n The chapel was raised (= built) as a memorial to her son. \n 这座小教堂是为了纪念她的儿子而修建的。 \n, Her parents died when she was a baby and she was raised by her grandparents. \n 她从小父母就去世了，是祖父母把她抚养大的。 \n, The lambs had to be raised by hand (= fed milk by people) when their mother died. \n 母羊死后，这些小羊羔只得靠人工喂养。 \n, The farmer raises (= breeds) chickens and pigs. \n 这个农场主饲养鸡和猪。 \n, The soil around here isn t good enough for raising (= growing) crops. \n 这附近地区的土壤不够肥沃，不能种庄稼。 \n, I ll raise you. \n 我要提高赌注。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n I ll raise you $50. \n 我要比你多押50美元。 \n, They agreed to raise the trade embargo if three conditions were met. \n 如果满足3个条件，他们同意解除贸易禁运。 \n, After three weeks the siege was raised. \n 3个星期后解除了围困。 \n, I ve been trying to raise Jack/Tokyo all day. \n 我一整天都在试图与杰克／东京取得联系。 \n, She asked the boss for a raise. \n 她要求老板给她加薪。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrai/ukrains003.mp3'),('ratify','（尤指政府或组织）正式批准，使正式生效，正式签署','uk :ˈræt.ɪ.faɪ, us :ˈræt̬.ə.faɪ','[Many countries have now ratified the UN convention on the rights of the child. \n 很多国家现在已经正式签署了联合国儿童权利公约。 \n, The decision will have to be ratified (= approved) by the executive board. \n 这个决议必须要经过管理委员会的批准。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukras/ukrasp_017.mp3'),('raw','（食物）生的，未经烹调的，没煮的原料未经加工的，自然状态的（信息）没有经过处理的，未经分析的，原始的（人）无经验的，未经培训的，生疏无知的（感情、品质等）处于自然状态的，强烈的，粗犷的（文字）不加掩饰的，如实坦陈的，反映真实情况的（肌肉）擦掉表皮而外露的；（伤口）露肉而刺痛的；创痛的（天气）严寒的，寒冷的，刺骨的','uk :rɔː, us :rɑː','[raw fish \n 生鱼 \n, Oil is an important raw material that can be processed into many different products, including plastics. \n 石油是一种重要的原料，可以加工成包括塑料在内的许多种产品。 \n, They claimed that raw sewage was being pumped into the sea. \n 他们断言，下水道的污水未经处理就被直接排入了大海。 \n, raw data/evidence/figures \n 原始数据／第一手证据／初始数字 \n, I would prefer not to leave this job to John while he s still a raw recruit/beginner. \n 约翰刚被招进来／刚开始工作，还是个生手，我不想把这项工作留给他来做。 \n, We were struck by the raw energy/power of the dancers  performances. \n 舞蹈演员们那粗狂奔放、富有激情的表演给我们留下了很深的印象。 \n, Her emotions are still a bit raw after her painful divorce. \n 经历过那段痛苦的离婚后，她的情绪仍然无法平静下来。 \n, His new play is a raw drama about family life. \n 他的新剧本是家庭生活的真实写照。 \n, The shoe had rubbed a raw place on her heel. \n 鞋把她的一个脚后跟磨破了。 \n, a raw morning \n 一个寒冷的早晨 \n, a raw wind \n 刺骨的寒风 \n, The evening was cold and raw. \n 那个晚上寒冷刺骨。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrat/ukratio028.mp3'),('reactionary','反动分子；保守分子；反对进步者','uk :riˈæk.ʃən.ər.i, us :riˈæk.ʃən.er.i',NULL,'2020-02-14',4,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukray/ukrayon019.mp3'),('receptor','受体','uk :rɪˈsep.tər, us :-tɚ','[]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep001.mp3'),('reckless','鲁莽的；轻率的；不顾后果的','uk :ˈrek.ləs, us :ˈrek.ləs','[He was found guilty of reckless driving. \n 他被判鲁莽驾驶罪名成立。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep022.mp3'),('reckon','想；认为，以为认为；把…看作计算','uk :ˈrek.ən, us :ˈrek.ən','[I reckon it s going to rain. \n 我觉得天要下雨了。 \n, [ + (that) ] \n How much do you reckon (that) it s going to cost? \n 你认为这会花多少钱？ \n,  Can you fix my car today?   I reckon not/so (= probably not/probably).  \n “你能今天把我的汽车修好吗？”“我想不行／大概可以。” \n, I don t reckon much to (US of) their chances of winning (= I do not think they will win). \n 我认为他们获胜的希望不大。 \n, She was widely reckoned (to be) the best actress of her generation. \n 人们普遍认为她是她那一代最优秀的演员。 \n, Angela quickly reckoned the amount on her fingers. \n 安吉拉掰着手指头快速计算了一下数量。 \n, The inflation rate is now reckoned to be 10 percent. \n 据计算，现在的通货膨胀率是10%。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep025.mp3'),('recluse','隐居者；喜欢独处的人','uk :rɪˈkluːs, us :rɪˈkluːs','[He is a millionaire recluse who refuses to give interviews. \n 他是个喜欢独处的百万富翁，不接受别人的采访。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecli002.mp3'),('referendum','（就重大政治或社会问题进行的）全民公决，全民公投','uk :ˌref.əˈren.dəm, us :ˌref.əˈren.dəm','[Is it more democratic to hold a referendum, rather than let the government alone decide? \n 进行一次全民公决，而不是由政府自己作出决定，是不是要更民主些？ \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukred/ukredou021.mp3'),('regime','政府；政权；政体组织方法；管理体制；体系生活规则，养生之道（同 regimen）','uk :reɪˈʒiːm, us :reɪˈʒiːm','[The old corrupt, totalitarian regime was overthrown. \n 腐败的旧极权政府被推翻。 \n, The regime in this office is hard work and more hard work. \n 该事务所的管理方式是让人努力再努力。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregen008.mp3'),('regulation','规则，条例，法规；控制，管理一般的，普通的；规定的；正规的','uk :ˌreɡ.jəˈleɪ.ʃən, us :ˌreɡ.jəˈleɪ.ʃən','[safety/health/traffic/fire/security regulations \n 安全／卫生／交通／消防／保安条例 \n, The correct procedure is laid down in the rules and regulations. \n 正确的程序在规章条例中有规定。 \n, government regulation of inflation \n 政府对通货膨胀的控制 \n, businessmen in their regulation pinstripe suits \n 身着细条纹正式西服的商人 \n, It\'s regulation to wear suits at the office. \n 按规定在办公室要穿西服。 \n, a regulation football pitch \n 符合规范的足球场 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul006.mp3'),('regulatory','管理的；控制的；监管的','uk :ˌreɡ.jəˈleɪ.tər.i, us :ˈreɡ.jə.lə.tɔːr.i','[a regulatory body/organization \n 监管部门／组织 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul008.mp3'),('reincarnation','轮回转世说（灵魂的）转世化身，化身','uk :ˌriː.ɪn.kɑːˈneɪ.ʃən, us :ˌriː.ɪn.kɑːrˈneɪ.ʃən','[Hindus and Buddhists believe in reincarnation. \n 印度教徒和佛教徒相信轮回转世说。 \n, He believes he s a reincarnation of Julius Caesar. \n 他认为自己是尤利乌斯‧恺撒再生。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul022.mp3'),('reinforce','加固；使更结实强化，加深，进一步证实（观点、看法等）增援；加强…的力量；给…增强装备','uk :ˌriː.ɪnˈfɔːs, us :ˌriː.ɪnˈfɔːrs','[The pockets on my jeans are reinforced with double stitching. \n 我牛仔裤的裤兜缝了两道线，很结实。 \n, The final technical report into the accident reinforces the findings of initial investigations. \n 对事故作出的最终的技术性报告进一步证实了最初的调查结果。 \n, His behaviour merely reinforced my dislike of him. \n 他的行为只能使我更讨厌他。 \n, The garrison is to be reinforced with/by another two battalions of soldiers. \n 守备部队将得到另外两个营的增援。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul024.mp3'),('reinvent','（在已有事物的基础上）重新创造，改造（通过改换工作或形象、行为方式而）改造自己，洗心革面，换个活法','uk :ˌriː.ɪnˈvent, us :ˌriː.ɪnˈvent','[The story of Romeo and Juliet was reinvented as a Los Angeles gangster movie. \n 罗密欧和朱丽叶的故事被改编成了一部洛杉矶黑帮题材电影。 \n, He\'s one of those sportsmen who reinvent themselves as TV presenters. \n 他是那些半路出家做电视节目主持人的运动员之一。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01196.mp3'),('reiterate','反复地说，反复讲；重申','uk :riˈɪt.ər.eɪt, us :riˈɪt̬.ɚ.eɪt','[The government has reiterated its refusal to compromise with terrorists. \n 政府重申拒绝向恐怖分子妥协。 \n, [ + that ] \n She reiterated that she had never seen him before. \n 她一再重申自己以前从未见过他。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul030.mp3'),('relativity','相对论相对性','uk :ˌrel.əˈtɪv.ə.ti, us :ˌrel.əˈtɪv.ə.t̬i',NULL,'2020-01-07',0,3,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrej/ukrejec021.mp3'),('relentless','持续严厉的；持续强烈的','uk :rɪˈlent.ləs, us :rɪˈlent.ləs','[relentless criticism/pressure \n 不断的严厉批评／施压 \n, relentless heat \n 持续高温 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrel/ukrelen002.mp3'),('relieve','缓解，减轻，解除（疼痛或担忧）；使宽心，使宽慰缓和，缓解（令人不快的局势）救济；救援；救助接替；换…的班；替下将（某地从敌人的围困中）解围；解救撒尿，排尿（urinate 的礼貌性说法）','uk :rɪˈliːv, us :rɪˈliːv','[She was given a shot of morphine to relieve the pain. \n 医生给她注射了一针吗啡来止痛。 \n, She relieved her boredom at home by learning how to type. \n 她在家学打字来打发无聊的时光。 \n, New toll roads could help relieve congestion on other routes. \n 新建的收费道路可以帮助缓解其他道路的拥堵情况。 \n, emergency food aid to help relieve the famine \n 为了救济饥民而提供的紧急食品援助 \n, I\'m on duty until 2 p.m. and then Peter is coming to relieve me. \n 我要值班到下午两点，两点以后彼得就会来换班。 \n, An armoured battalion was sent to relieve the besieged town. \n 那个城市被困，一个装甲营被派去解围。 \n, He proceeded to relieve himself against a tree. \n 他走到一棵树旁小解。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrel/ukrelen014.mp3'),('remunerative','给酬报的；给酬劳的','uk :rɪˈmjuː.nər.ə.tɪv, us :rɪˈmjuː.nə.reɪ.t̬ɪv','[a highly remunerative (= well paid) job \n 高薪工作 \n, Charity work is not very remunerative. \n 做慈善工作报酬不是很高。 \n]\n','2020-02-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrem/ukremor015.mp3'),('render','使成为；使变得；使处于某种状态翻译；把…译成给予，提供；表达；表演粉刷；给（墙壁）抹灰（或水泥）','uk :ˈren.dər, us :ˈren.dɚ','[[ + adj ] \n His rudeness rendered me speechless. \n 他的粗暴无礼让我无言以对。 \n, New technology has rendered my old computer obsolete. \n 新技术发展太快，我的旧电脑已经过时了。 \n, She is rendering the book into English from French. \n 她正在把这本书从法语译成英语。 \n, The singers rendered the song with enthusiasm. \n 歌手们热情洋溢地演唱了这首歌。 \n, We see that freight railroads make good profits while rendering excellent service. \n 我们看到铁路货运公司在提供优质服务的同时也赢得了丰厚的利润。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrem/ukremor020.mp3'),('repel','驱逐；逐回；击退；抗御排斥；相斥使厌恶；使极反感','uk :rɪˈpel, us :rɪˈpel','[This coat has a special surface that repels moisture. \n 这件外套面料特殊，可以防潮。 \n, ormal \n The defenders repelled the attack without losing any men. \n 守军击退了敌人的进攻，自己没有损失一个人。 \n, Similar poles of magnets repel each other, and opposite poles attract. \n 磁铁同极相斥，异极相吸。 \n, She was repelled by his ugliness. \n 她厌恶他那丑陋的相貌。 \n, Her arrogance repels many people. \n 她的傲慢令很多人十分反感。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukren/ukrenni028.mp3'),('repent','后悔；悔过，忏悔','uk :rɪˈpent, us :rɪˈpent','[He repented (of his sins) just hours before he died. \n 在临死前数小时，他才（对自己的罪孽）做了忏悔。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukren/ukrenni030.mp3'),('repentatleisure','悔婚','','null\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'null'),('repulse','赶走，驱逐；击退（尤指进攻）；拒绝，拒绝接受令人厌恶；使人反感击退；败退；拒绝','uk :rɪˈpʌls, us :rɪˈpʌls',NULL,'2020-01-07',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrep/ukrepro011.mp3'),('reputation','名誉；声望；名望','uk :ˌrep.jəˈteɪ.ʃən, us :ˌrep.jəˈteɪ.ʃən','[The company has a worldwide reputation for quality. \n 这家公司的产品质量誉满全球。 \n, She has the reputation of being a good doctor. \n 作为一名优秀的医生，她很有声望。 \n, His reputation was destroyed when he was caught stealing some money. \n 他偷钱时被当场抓住，这使他声名扫地。 \n, The hotel has a bad/good reputation. \n 这家旅馆名声很好／坏。 \n, He earned/established/gained/acquired a reputation as an entertaining speaker. \n 他因为演讲妙趣横生而赢得／享有／得到／获得盛名。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrep/ukrepro016.mp3'),('rescue','救援；营救；解救救援；营救；解救','uk :ˈres.kjuː, us :ˈres.kjuː','[The lifeboat rescued the sailors from the sinking boat. \n 救生艇将水手们从正在下沉的船上救起。 \n, The government has refused to rescue the company from bankruptcy. \n 政府已经拒绝援助这家濒于破产的公司。 \n, Lifeboats carry out many rescues every month. \n 救生艇每月都会执行很多救援任务。 \n, We huddled together on the cliff ledge, waiting for rescue. \n 我们挤作一团蜷缩在悬崖边，等待救援。 \n, I didn\'t know anybody at the party, but the hostess came to my rescue (= helped me out of a difficult situation) by introducing me to a few people. \n 在聚会上我谁也不认识，但女主人过来救了我的驾，把我介绍给几个客人。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrer/ukrerun005.mp3'),('resemblance','相似；形似，相貌相似','uk :rɪˈzem.bləns, us :rɪˈzem.bləns','[There was a clear family resemblance between all the brothers. \n 所有兄弟都长得很像，一眼就看得出是一家人。 \n, These prices bear no resemblance to (= are completely different from) the ones I saw printed in the newspaper. \n 这些价格和我在报纸上看到的大相径庭。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrer/ukrerun010.mp3'),('resolution','决议；正式决定决心；决定决心；决意；坚决解决；解除；消除（显微镜、电视、计算机显示屏等的）清晰度，分辨率分解；解析','uk :ˌrez.əˈluː.ʃən, us :ˌrez.əˈluː.ʃən','[to approve/adopt a resolution \n 批准／通过决议 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n The United Nations passed (= voted to support) a resolution to increase aid to developing nations. \n 联合国通过了一项向发展中国家增加援助的决议。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n I made a resolution to give up chocolate. \n 我下决心不再吃巧克力了。 \n, He showed great resolution in facing the robbers. \n 面对强盗，他表现得英勇无畏。 \n, a successful resolution to the crisis \n 危机的成功解决 \n, a high/low resolution image \n 高／低清晰度图像 \n, the resolution of oil into bitumen and tar \n 石油分解成沥青和焦油 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukresid022.mp3'),('respirator','>人工呼吸器；呼吸机>防毒面具','uk :>ˈres.pɪ.reɪ.tə, us :>ˈres.pə.reɪ.t̬ɚ',NULL,'2020-01-20',10,12,1,NULL),('respiratory','呼吸的','uk :rɪˈspɪr.ə.tər.i, us :ˈres.pə.rə.tɔːr.i','[Smoking can cause respiratory diseases. \n 吸烟会导致呼吸系统疾病。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukresou021.mp3'),('retaliation','反击报复','uk :rɪˌtæl.iˈeɪ.ʃən, us :rɪˌtæl.iˈeɪ.ʃən','[he bomb attack was in retaliation for the recent arrest of two well-known terrorists.\n, She suffered severe retaliation for writing articles for the newspapers.\n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukrestr025.mp3'),('reveal','揭露；泄露；透露使显露；展现；显示（电视节目最后的）揭示','uk :rɪˈviːl, us :rɪˈviːl',NULL,'2020-02-13',5,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrev/ukrev__005.mp3'),('revere','>尊敬；崇敬','uk :>rɪˈvɪə, us :>rɪˈvɪr',NULL,'2020-02-13',7,9,1,NULL),('revert','回复','uk :rɪˈvɜːt, us :rɪˈvɝːt','[Please revert by email. \n 请通过电子邮件回复。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01216.mp3'),('revolution','（通常指改变政治体制的）革命革命性剧变；大变革旋转；绕转；循环运动（轮子等的）一转，一圈','uk :ˌrev.əˈluː.ʃən, us :ˌrev.əˈluː.ʃən','[The French Revolution changed France from a monarchy to a republic. \n 法国大革命使法国由君主政体变成共和政体。 \n, The country seems to be heading towards revolution. \n 这个国家似乎正在走向革命。 \n, a technological revolution \n 技术革命 \n, Penicillin produced a revolution in medicine. \n 青霉素的发现引起了医学上的一次革命。 \n, The revolution of the earth around the sun was proposed by Copernicus. \n 地球围绕太阳旋转这一观点是哥白尼提出的。 \n, Engine speed can be measured in revolutions per minute (abbreviation rpm). \n 发动机的速度可以每分钟转数（缩写为rpm）来表述。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrev/ukrevie017.mp3'),('rhythm','（音乐、诗歌和舞蹈的）节奏，韵律，节律规则的运动；（动作的）节奏；律动（尤指自然界中的）规则变化，规律，节律','uk :ˈrɪð.əm, us :ˈrɪð.əm','[He beat out a jazz rhythm on the drums. \n 他击出爵士乐节奏的鼓点。 \n, I ve got no sense of rhythm, so I m a terrible dancer. \n 我根本没有节奏感，所以舞跳得很差劲。 \n, She was lulled to sleep by the gentle rhythm of the boat in the water. \n 船在水中有节奏地轻轻摇动，使她昏昏入睡。 \n, She hit the ball so hard that her opponent had no chance to establish any rhythm in her game. \n 她凌厉的击球让对手根本没有机会找到比赛的节奏。 \n, the rhythm of the seasons \n 四季的交替 \n, Breathing and sleeping are examples of biological rhythms in humans. \n 呼吸和睡眠是人体生物节奏的例证。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrew/ukrewou029.mp3'),('ribbon','（捆扎或装饰用的）带子，丝带，缎带一缕；一条；一排勋带，绶带（打字机的）色带','uk :ˈrɪb.ən, us :ˈrɪb.ən','[Sandra often wears a ribbon in her hair. \n 桑德拉常在头发上扎条丝带。 \n, He tied up the present with ribbon. \n 他用缎带将礼物包扎起来。 \n, A ribbon of road stretched ahead of us across the desert. \n 沙漠中的一条路宛如一根细长的带子，在我们前方延伸。 \n, My typewriter needs a new ribbon. \n 我的打字机得换色带了。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrhy/ukrhyth008.mp3'),('rifle','来福枪；步枪迅速翻查；匆忙翻找','uk :ˈraɪ.fəl, us :ˈraɪ.fəl','[The safe had been rifled and the diamonds were gone. \n 保险柜被洗劫了，钻石不翼而飞。 \n, He rifled through the papers on the desk, but couldn t find the photographs. \n 他把桌上的一堆文件翻了个遍，但是没有找到照片。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrid/ukrider010.mp3'),('rigor','尸僵；死后强直','uk :ˌrɪɡ.ə ˈmɔː.tɪs, us :ˌrɪɡ.ɚ ˈmɔːr.t̬ɪs','[Rigor mortis usually sets in between two and four hours after death. \n 通常死后2至4小时就会开始出现尸僵。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrid/ukrider029.mp3'),('rigorously','严谨','uk :ˈrɪɡ.ər.əs.li, us :ˈrɪɡ.ɚ.əs.li','[he plutonium fuel cells had been rigorously tested.\n, Isabel thinks rigorously and creatively about many different things.\n, he rules were applied too rigorously.\n, Driving bans for serious offences should be rigorously enforced.\n, eputable manufacturers test rigorously to make sure their products perform at the highest level.\n, aws are rigorously enforced.\n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrig/ukrigor001.mp3'),('ripple','涟漪；微波；细浪（声音的）传播起伏；（感情的）逐渐扩散彩条冰激凌（使）起涟漪；（使）如波浪般起伏','uk :ˈrɪp.əl, us :ˈrɪp.əl','[The stone she threw caused ripples to spread across the lake. \n 她扔了一块石头，湖面泛起阵阵涟漪。 \n, A ripple of laughter/applause, etc. ran through the crowd. \n 人群中响起一阵阵笑声／掌声等。 \n, A ripple of excitement/unease, etc. flowed up her spine. \n 一阵激动／不安等顺着脊背传遍了她全身。 \n, News of the war hardly caused a ripple (= people showed little interest). \n 战争爆发的消息几乎没有引起任何反响。 \n, raspberry ripple \n 山莓彩条冰激凌 \n, The breeze rippled the water. \n 微风在水面吹起阵阵涟漪。 \n, His muscles rippled under his skin. \n 他皮肤下的肌肉一条条凸起。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrip/ukripof003.mp3'),('rival','竞争对手；敌手可与…相媲美，比得上','uk :ˈraɪ.vəl, us :ˈraɪ.vəl','[He beat his closest/nearest rival by 20 marks. \n 他以领先20分的成绩打败了和他水平最接近的对手。 \n, The companies produce rival versions of the toy. \n 这些公司生产的玩具跟我们的产品争夺市场。 \n, No computer can rival a human brain for/in complexity. \n 没有任何计算机比得上人脑复杂。 \n, The beauty of the country is only rivalled by (= is as great in degree as) the violence of its politics. \n 该国的美丽风光非同寻常，而其国内政治的残暴同样惊世骇俗。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrip/ukripof021.mp3'),('robe','长袍，罩袍；（尤指特别正式场合穿的）袍服，礼袍浴衣；睡袍','uk :rəʊb, us :roʊb','[Judges wear black robes when they are in court. \n 法官在法庭上都身穿黑袍。 \n, He wrapped a robe around himself before answering the door. \n 他裹了件浴衣过来开门。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrn_/ukrn___027.mp3'),('rodent','啮齿动物（如老鼠等）','uk :ˈrəʊ.dənt, us :ˈroʊ.dənt','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrob/ukrobot017.mp3'),('routine','惯例，常规；例行公事（表演中）一套固定的动作，固定的一套噱头，固定的表演节目（计算机的）例行程序常规的例行公事的；习惯性的平淡的；乏味的','uk :ruːˈtiːn, us :ruːˈtiːn','[There s no set/fixed routine at work - every day is different. \n 工作内容不固定——每天都不同。 \n, Most companies insure property and equipment against damage or theft as a matter of routine. \n 他只要开车就先习惯性地检查车下是否被安了炸弹。 \n, an exercise/dance routine \n 一套固定的练习／舞蹈动作 \n, He went into his usual  I m the head of the family  routine (= usual way of speaking). \n 他又故态复萌，重弹“我是一家之主”的老调子。 \n, a routine inspection/medical check-up \n 常规检查／体检 \n, a routine case of appendicitis \n 普通阑尾炎病例 \n, He died during a routine operation which went wrong. \n 他因一次常规手术出错而死亡。 \n, My job is so routine and boring - I hate it. \n 我的工作一成不变，枯燥乏味——我厌烦透了。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrou/ukrough019.mp3'),('ruffian','流氓，暴徒，恶棍（通常指男性）','uk :ˈrʌf.i.ən, us :ˈrʌf.i.ən','[]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukruc/ukrucks015.mp3'),('rumble','发出隆隆声；发出辘辘声；发出低沉连续的响声发现，察觉，看穿（某人的秘密或非法事情的真相）打架；打群架','uk :ˈrʌm.bəl, us :ˈrʌm.bəl','[Please excuse my stomach rumbling - I haven t eaten all day. \n 不好意思，我肚子在咕咕叫——我一整天都没吃东西了。 \n, Thunder rumbled in the distance. \n 雷声在远处隆隆作响。 \n, Convoys of tanks rumbled (= moved while rumbling) through the city streets.\n, His boss eventually rumbled him, and he was sacked. \n 他的老板最终看穿了他，把他解雇了。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrum/ukrum__003.mp3'),('ruthless','无情的；冷酷的；残忍的','uk :ˈruːθ.ləs, us :ˈruːθ.ləs','[ruthless ambition \n 冷酷无情的野心 \n, a ruthless dictator \n 残忍的独裁者 \n, Some people believe that to succeed in this world you have to be ruthless. \n 有些人认为，在这个世界上要想成功必须冷酷无情。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrun/ukruns_028.mp3'),('sabotage','（为阻止敌人或对手成功而）毁坏，破坏（设备、武器或建筑物）阴谋破坏，蓄意破坏（计划或行动）','uk :ˈsæb.ə.tɑːʒ, us :ˈsæb.ə.tɑːʒ','[The rebels had tried to sabotage the oil pipeline. \n 叛乱分子曾试图破坏输油管道。 \n, This was a deliberate attempt to sabotage the ceasefire. \n 这是一次蓄意破坏停火的行为。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrut/ukrutte015.mp3'),('sack','大布袋；麻袋；大纸袋；大塑料袋食品购物袋开除，解雇（通常指在战争中）洗劫，劫掠（美式橄榄球）擒杀（四分卫）床床上功夫（好或差）解雇，开除（美式橄榄球）擒杀（四分卫）（通常指在战争中）洗劫，劫掠','uk :sæk, us :sæk','[The corn was stored in large sacks. \n 玉米装在大麻袋里。 \n, a sack of potatoes/coal/flour \n 一袋土豆／煤／面粉 \n, a sack of groceries \n 一袋食品杂货 \n, They gave him the sack for being late. \n 因为迟到，他们开除了他。 \n, Two workers got the sack for fighting in the warehouse. \n 两名工人因为在仓库打架而被解雇了。 \n, The sack of Rome by the Visigoths occurred in the fifth century. \n 西哥特人洗劫罗马发生在公元5世纪。 \n, The Colts have allowed only six sacks this season. \n 小马队本赛季只遭受到六次擒杀。 \n, It\'s late - I\'m going to hit the sack (= go to bed). \n 时间不早了，我要上床睡觉了。 \n, He came home and found Judy and Brad in the sack (= in bed) together. \n 回到家，他发现朱迪和布拉德睡在一张床上。 \n, They sacked her for being late. \n 因为迟到，他们把她开除了。 \n, He got sacked from his last job. \n 他上一份工作是被解雇的。 \n, The quarterback was sacked only once and completed 16 out of 23 passes. \n 这名四分卫只被擒杀过一次，23次投掷成功了16次。 \n, The invaders sacked every village they passed on their route. \n 侵略者洗劫了他们途经的每个村庄。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrut/ukrutte018.mp3'),('saddle','马鞍；（自行车、摩托车等的）车座，鞍座骑马掌握，控制（动物的）脊肉给（马）装鞍','uk :ˈsæd.əl, us :ˈsæd.əl','[He swung himself into the saddle and rode off. \n 他跨上马鞍，骑马走了。 \n, The chairman is back in the saddle after his heart attack. \n 心脏病痊愈之后，主席又重新掌权了。 \n, saddle of lamb \n 羊脊肉 \n, She saddled (up) the horse for her friend. \n 她为朋友备好了马鞍。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksac/uksacri013.mp3'),('sadist','施虐狂者；性施虐狂者','uk :ˈseɪ.dɪst, us :ˈsæd.ɪst','[]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksac/uksacri017.mp3'),('sake','为了（某人）的利益；为了帮助（某人）因为；为了做做好事吧，看在上帝份上，看在老天份上日本清酒','uk :seɪk, us :seɪk','[Please do it, for David s sake. \n 为了戴维，请做这件事。 \n, Their parents only stayed together for the sake of the children. \n 他们的父母仅仅是为了孩子才没有分开。 \n, I hope for both our sakes that you re right! \n 为你我着想，我希望你是对的！ \n, Let s not disagree for the sake of (= because of) a few dollars. \n 咱们不要因为几块钱闹别扭。 \n, Let s say, just for the sake of argument/for argument s sake (= for the purpose of this discussion), that prices rise by three percent this year. \n 为了便于讨论，我们假设今年的价格上涨3％。 \n, You re only arguing for the sake of arguing (= because you like arguing). \n 你只是为争论而争论。 \n, For goodness  sake don t let her know I told you! \n 行行好，千万别让她知道是我告诉你的！ \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksaf/uksafek030.mp3'),('salve','药膏；软膏；油膏慰藉，宽慰使良心得到宽慰；减轻内疚感','uk :sælv, us :sæv','[He salves his conscience by giving money to charity. \n 他通过向慈善机构捐款来使自己良心得到宽慰。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksal/uksalti013.mp3'),('sanctuary','庇护，保护；避难所，庇护所禁猎区，鸟兽保护区圣殿，圣堂','uk :ˈsæŋk.tʃʊə.ri, us :ˈsæŋk.tʃu.er.i','[Illegal immigrants found/sought/took sanctuary in a local church. \n 非法移民把当地的一座教堂当作避难所。 \n, The chapel became a sanctuary for the refugees. \n 这座小教堂成为难民的庇护所。 \n, igurative \n If I want some peace and quiet, I take sanctuary in my study. \n 如果想清静一会儿，我就躲进自己的书房。 \n, a wildlife/bird sanctuary \n 野生动物／鸟类保护区 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksam/uksampl014.mp3'),('sanguine','乐观的，乐天的','uk :ˈsæŋ.ɡwɪn, us :ˈsæŋ.ɡwɪn','[They are less sanguine about the prospects for peace. \n 他们对和平的前景不乐观。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksan/uksands012.mp3'),('sardonic','讥讽的，冷嘲的，轻蔑的','uk :sɑːˈdɒn.ɪk, us :sɑːrˈdɑː.nɪk','[a sardonic smile/look/comment \n 讥讽的微笑／嘲讽的表情／尖刻的评论 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksap/uksappy012.mp3'),('scale','标度，刻度；等级比例；比例尺大小；规模；范围秤，磅秤一架天平音阶（鱼、蛇等动物皮肤表层的）鳞，鳞片（水管或容器内壁的）水垢爬越；攀登刮除（牙石或牙斑）','uk :skeɪl, us :skeɪl','[the Centigrade/Fahrenheit scale \n 摄氏／华氏温标 \n, How would you rate his work on a scale of 1 to 5? \n 按照1到5的等级，你给他的工作打几分？ \n, a scale of 1:50,000 \n 比例尺为1:50000 \n, This map is large scale (= things are shown in detail). \n 这张地图的比例尺很大。 \n, Is the bridge drawn to scale (= so that it shows the exact shape of the bridge, but much smaller)? \n 这座桥是按比例画的吗？ \n, He was building a scale model of the Empire State Building. \n 他正在做一个帝国大厦的比例模型。 \n, We don t yet know the scale of the problem. \n 我们还不知道问题有多严重。 \n, Nuclear weapons cause destruction on a massive scale (= cause a lot of destruction). \n 核武器杀伤力很大。 \n, My parents used to entertain friends on a large/small scale (= they had large/small parties). \n 我父母过去常常举行大／小规模的宴会招待朋友。 \n, kitchen/bathroom scales \n 厨房用秤／浴室体重秤 \n, the scale of G major \n G大调音阶 \n, You should practise your scales every day. \n 你得每天练习音阶。 \n, The prisoner scaled the high prison wall and ran off. \n 囚犯攀越监狱的高墙逃跑了。 \n, The dentist scaled and polished my teeth last week. \n 上星期牙医给我洗了牙并进行了抛光。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksax/uksax__019.mp3'),('scandal','丑行；丑闻；震惊；反感丑闻报道丢脸，耻辱','uk :ˈskæn.dəl, us :ˈskæn.dəl','[a financial/political/sex scandal \n 财政／政治／性丑闻 \n, Their affair caused/created a scandal in the office. \n 他们的风流韵事在办公室里成了丑闻。 \n, The scandal broke (= became public knowledge) right at the beginning of the Conservative Party Conference. \n 就在保守党大会开幕的那一刻，丑闻曝了出来。 \n, If there is the slightest suggestion/hint of scandal, the public will no longer trust us. \n 只要有哪怕一丝丑闻，公众就再也不会信任我们。 \n, Some magazines contain nothing but scandal and gossip. \n 有些杂志专门报道丑闻，散播小道消息。 \n, to spread scandal \n 传播丑闻 \n, [ + (that) ] \n It s a scandal (that) children are treated in this way. \n 这样对待孩子真是太可耻了。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscamp004.mp3'),('scar','疤，伤疤，伤痕精神创伤外观的破坏结疤；留下伤痕','uk :skɑːr, us :skɑːr','[a prominent/a noticeable/an ugly scar \n 凸出的／显眼的／丑陋的伤疤 \n, That burn will leave a bad scar. \n 烧伤会留下严重的伤疤。 \n, scar tissue \n 瘢痕组织 \n, His early years in the refugee camp left a deep psychological scar. \n 早年的难民营生活给他留下了深深的心理创伤。 \n, Every village bears the scars of war . \n 每一个村庄都布满了战争留下的疮痍。 \n, He was scarred as a result of the fire. \n 那场大火给他留下了伤疤。 \n, igurative \n His experiences in the army left him scarred for life (= had a serious mental effect on him for the rest of his life). \n 他的军旅生涯给他留下了终身的心灵创伤。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscamp016.mp3'),('scatter','散开，分散；使分散，驱散撒，撒播，撒于…上','uk :ˈskæt.ər, us :ˈskæt̬.ɚ','[The protesters scattered at the sound of gunshots. \n 听到枪声后抗议者便散开了。 \n, The soldiers came in and scattered the crowd. \n 士兵进来把人群驱散了。 \n, Scatter the powder around the plants. \n 把这种药粉撒在植物周围。 \n, I scattered grass seed all over the lawn. \n 我将草籽撒在整个草坪上。 \n, I scattered the whole lawn with grass seed. \n 我在整个草坪上都撒下草籽。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscarl009.mp3'),('scavenge','（从废弃物中）觅食；捡破烂（野生动物）以腐肉为食','uk :ˈskæv.ɪndʒ, us :ˈskæv.ɪndʒ','[The flood has left people and animals desperately scavenging for food. \n 因遭受水灾，村民和牲畜四处寻觅食物。 \n, We managed to scavenge a lot of furniture from the dump. \n 我们从当地的垃圾堆里捡到了许多家具。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscarl015.mp3'),('sceptical','怀疑的，持怀疑态度的','uk :ˈskep.tɪ.kəl, us :ˈskep.tɪ.kəl','[Many experts remain sceptical about/of his claims. \n 很多专家对他的主张仍然持怀疑态度。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscarl026.mp3'),('scholar','（尤指大学的）学者聪颖好学者；善于学习者','uk :ˈskɒl.ər, us :ˈskɑː.lɚ',NULL,'2020-02-13',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksch/uksched030.mp3'),('sclerosis','（尤指动脉的）硬化','uk :skləˈrəʊ.sɪs, us :-ˈroʊ-','[]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksci/uksciro005.mp3'),('screw','螺丝（钉）扭转，旋转监狱看守（尤为犯人用语）性行为；性伙伴（同 thumbscrew）用螺丝固定（或拧紧）（用类似螺丝的东西）固定，拧紧旋上，拧合（尤指出于不赞同或疼痛）扭曲（面部）将（尤指纸或布）揉成团拧牢，旋紧骗，欺骗（与…）发生性关系','uk :skruː, us :skruː',NULL,'2020-01-07',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukscr/ukscrap025.mp3'),('scrutiny','细看，仔细审查','uk :ˈskruː.tɪ.ni, us :ˈskruː.t̬ən.i',NULL,'2020-02-14',8,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukscr/ukscrum010.mp3'),('secede','退出，脱离（国家或政府）','uk :sɪˈsiːd, us :sɪˈsiːd','[There is likely to be civil war if the region tries to secede from the south. \n 如果这一地区想脱离南方而独立，很可能会爆发内战。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksea/uksear_030.mp3'),('secretarial','秘书的，文秘的','uk :ˌsek.rəˈteə.ri.əl, us :ˌsek.rəˈter.i.əl','[a secretarial school \n 文秘学院 \n, She s found some part-time secretarial work. \n 她找到了一份兼职的秘书工作。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/ukseces015.mp3'),('secretion','分泌；分泌液','uk :sɪˈkriː.ʃən, us :sɪˈkriː.ʃən','[The excessive secretion of gastric juices in the gut causes ulcers. \n 胃中胃液分泌过多会导致胃溃疡。 \n, toxic secretions \n 有毒分泌物 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/ukseces019.mp3'),('security','保护（措施）；安全（保障）保安人员保障；牢靠保证金；担保品证券；债券（在家庭或一段关系中）安全感；安心','uk :sɪˈkjʊə.rə.ti, us :səˈkjʊr.ə.t̬i','[The station was closed for two hours because of a security alert. \n 由于有安全警报，车站关闭了两小时。 \n, 30 demonstrators were killed in clashes with the security forces over the weekend. \n 周末，30名示威者在与保安部队的冲突中丧生。 \n, The tighter security measures/precautions include video cameras throughout the city centre. \n 加强安全保障措施包括在市中心安装摄像头。 \n, The students were deported because they posed a threat to national security. \n 这些学生因对国家安全构成威胁而被驱逐出境。 \n, The banks must tighten security against fraud. \n 银行必须加强安全措施，防止诈骗。 \n, The most dangerous criminals are held in maximum-security prisons (= prisons that are as difficult as possible to escape from). \n 最为危险的罪犯被关押在戒备最森严的监狱里。 \n, You\'ll need to notify security if you want to work late in the office. \n 如果想在办公室里工作到很晚，你需要通知保安人员。 \n, If it\'s a choice between higher pay and job security, I\'d prefer to keep my job. \n 如果在更高的薪酬和安稳的工作两者之间进行选择，我宁愿保住工作。 \n, I\'m on a temporary contract and have little financial security (= cannot be sure of having enough money to live on). \n 我签的是临时合同，没什么经济保障。 \n, She used her shares in the company as security against a $23 million bank loan. \n 她用自己在公司的股票作抵押向银行借了2300万美元。 \n, The hotel held onto our suitcases as security while we went to the bank to get money to pay the bill. \n 宾馆扣下我们的行李作为抵押，我们则去银行取钱来付账。 \n, Most children need the security of a stable family life. \n 大多数孩子需要稳定的家庭生活带来的安全感。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/uksecul006.mp3'),('seducer','引诱者；勾引者；诱奸者','uk :sɪˈdʒuː.sər, us :səˈduː.sɚ','[The play tells the story of a wealthy woman who seeks revenge on her heartless seducer. \n 该剧讲的是一个富有的女人试图报复一个引诱了她却又对她无情的人。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/uksecul020.mp3'),('seminary','神学院','uk :ˈsem.ɪ.nər.i, us :ˈsem.ɪ.ner.i','[]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksel/ukselfs024.mp3'),('sequel','（书、电影或戏剧的）续篇，续集后果；结局','uk :ˈsiː.kwəl, us :ˈsiː.kwəl','[I m reading the sequel to  Gone with the Wind . \n 我正在读《飘》的续集。 \n, There was a dramatic sequel to last Thursday s scandalous revelations when the minister suddenly announced his resignation. \n 部长突然宣布辞职，上星期四的丑闻曝光便有了戏剧般的结局。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksep/uksept_009.mp3'),('serrated','锯齿边的','uk :səˈreɪ.tɪd, us :səˈreɪ.t̬ɪd','[You really need a knife with a serrated edge for cutting bread. \n 你真的需要一把有锯齿刃的刀子来切面包。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukser/ukseren021.mp3'),('several','一些；几个各自的，分别的','uk :ˈsev.ər.əl, us :ˈsev.ɚ.əl','[I ve seen  Gone with the Wind  several times. \n 我已经看过好几遍《乱世佳人》了。 \n, Several people have complained about the plans. \n 已经有好几个人抱怨过这项计划了。 \n, Several of my friends are learning English. \n 我有几个朋友在学英语。 \n, We are striving to reach an agreement which will satisfy the several interests of the parties concerned. \n 我们正在努力达成一个能满足有关各方各自利益的协议。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksev/ukseven004.mp3'),('severe','非常严重的；剧烈的；惨重的极度的；非常困难的不和善的；冷酷的；严厉的；苛刻的不加装饰的，朴素的，简朴的','uk :sɪˈvɪər, us :səˈvɪr','[a severe chest infection/leg injury/toothache \n 十分严重的胸腔感染／腿伤／牙痛 \n, This is a school for children with severe learning difficulties. \n 这是一所为有严重学习障碍的孩子设立的学校。 \n, In parts of Africa there is a severe food/water shortage. \n 非洲的一些地方存在严重的粮食／水资源短缺问题。 \n, There is expected to be a severe frost tonight. \n 今晚预计会出现严重的霜冻。 \n, Severe cutbacks in public spending have been announced. \n 已经宣布对公共开支进行大幅度削减。 \n, This will be a severe test of our strength. \n 这将是对我们实力的严峻考验。 \n, The headteacher spoke in a severe voice. \n 校长说话的口吻很严厉。 \n, The president is currently facing severe criticism. \n 总统目前正遭到严厉的批评。 \n, There are severe penalties for failing to declare all your income to the Inland Revenue. \n 未向税务机关申报个人全部收入会受到严厉的处罚。 \n, She wore a severe black dress, and plain black shoes. \n 她穿了一件朴素的黑连衣裙和一双普通的黑鞋子。 \n, I don\'t like these severe modern buildings. \n 我不喜欢这些没有任何装饰的现代建筑。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksev/ukseven007.mp3'),('sewn','缝；做针线活儿缝制（衣服）缝合（伤口）','uk :səʊ, us :soʊ','[My grandmother taught me to sew. \n 我祖母教我做针线活儿。 \n, I made this skirt just by sewing two pieces of material together. \n 我把两块料子缝在一起，就做成了这条裙子。 \n, He sewed the badge neatly onto his uniform. \n 他把徽章精心地缝在制服上。 \n, She sews all her children s clothes. \n 孩子们的衣服都是她缝制的。 \n, The muscle layer needs to be sewn first. \n 先要缝合肌肉层。 \n, His finger was cut off when he caught it in a machine, but the surgeon was able to sew it back on. \n 他的手指被机器夹住切断了，不过外科医生把断指缝合上去了。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksev/ukseven010.mp3'),('shatter','（使）破碎；粉碎终结；严重破坏','uk :ˈʃæt.ər, us :ˈʃæt̬.ɚ','[The glass shattered into a thousand tiny pieces. \n 玻璃碎成无数块细小的碎片。 \n, His leg was shattered in the accident. \n 他在事故中腿骨碎裂。 \n, The book shattered all her illusions about the Romans. \n 这本书击碎了她对罗马人的一切幻想。 \n, Noisy motorbikes shattered the peace/calm/stillness. \n 吵闹的摩托车声打破了宁静／平静／静谧。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksha/ukshari015.mp3'),('shedding','（通常为木质、存放物品用的）棚子，小屋（用于特定活动的）大简易棚（常为报刊用语）去除，摆脱使脱落；使掉落；蜕；脱流泪／流血／发光（等等）（she had的缩略形式）（she would的缩略形式）','uk :ʃed, us :ʃed','[a tool/storage shed \n 工具／储物棚 \n, K \n a garden/bicycle shed \n 花园／自行车棚 \n, the lambing shed \n 产羔棚 \n, a cow shed \n 牛棚 \n, 900 jobs will be shed over the next few months. \n 接下来几个月中要裁减900个职位。 \n, Psychotherapy helped him to shed some of his insecurity/inhibitions. \n 心理疗法帮助他摆脱了一些不安全感／自我压制。 \n, I m going on a diet to see if I can shed (= become thinner by losing) a few pounds. \n 我要节食，看能不能瘦掉几磅。 \n, The trees shed their leaves in autumn. \n 树木在秋天落叶。 \n, They ran down to the water, shedding clothes as they went. \n 他们奔向大海，一边跑一边脱衣服。 \n, K \n A lorry had shed a load of gravel across the road. \n 一辆卡车在路上掉下了一堆碎石。 \n, She shed a few tears at her daughter s wedding. \n 她在女儿的婚礼上流下了泪。 \n, So much blood has been shed (= so many people have been badly hurt or killed) in this war. \n 这场战争造成了惨重的伤亡。 \n, She d found the answer, at last. \n 她最后终于找到了答案。 \n, She d be a great managing director, don t you think? \n 她会成为一位出色的总经理，难道你不这么认为吗？ \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukshe/uksheat005.mp3'),('sheepish','（因做错事或傻事而）窘迫的，不好意思的','uk :ˈʃiː.pɪʃ, us :ˈʃiː.pɪʃ','[She gave me a sheepish smile and apologized. \n 她窘迫地笑了一下，道了歉。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukshe/uksheat012.mp3'),('shelf','（通常指固定在墙上或橱柜中的）搁板，架子陆架，陆棚；岩棚（产品）现成的，不需订制的将…下架，不再出售','uk :ʃelf, us :ʃelf','[a glass shelf \n 玻璃架子 \n, on the top/bottom shelf \n 在顶层／底层架子上 \n, One wall had shelves from floor to ceiling, crammed with books. \n 一面墙是高及天花板的书架，上面塞满了书。 \n, It s often cheaper if you buy wallpaper off the shelf, rather than having to order it. \n 如果你买现成的墙纸，通常会比订购的要便宜。 \n, off-the-shelf goods/clothes \n 现成的货物／衣服 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukshe/uksheat023.mp3'),('simultaneously','同时地','uk :ˌsɪm.əlˈteɪ.ni.əs.li, us :ˌsaɪ.məlˈteɪ.ni.əs.li','[wo children answered the teacher\'s question simultaneously.\n, The network was broadcasting four games simultaneously across the country.\n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uks/uksim/uksimil023.mp3'),('siren','警报器，汽笛塞壬（古希腊神话中的海妖）妖妇，迷人而危险的女人','uk :ˈsaɪə.rən, us :ˈsaɪr.ən','[police sirens \n 警笛 \n, When the air raid siren went off people ran to their shelters. \n 空袭警报响起时，人们纷纷跑向掩蔽所。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksin/uksinle014.mp3'),('skinny','非常瘦的，皮包骨头的（尤指咖啡）低脂的紧身的（有关…的）确切消息，真实情况，贴身信息紧身牛仔裤','uk :ˈskɪn.i, us :ˈskɪn.i','[You should eat more - you re too skinny. \n 你应该多吃点儿，你太瘦了。 \n, a skinny latte \n 低脂牛奶咖啡 \n, skinny jeans \n 紧身牛仔裤 \n, Get the skinny on hundreds of celebs in our  People Profiles  section. \n 在我们的《人物介绍》栏目可以看到几百位明星的贴身信息。 \n, A white shirt and skinnies is always a good look. \n 白衬衫配紧身牛仔裤总是很好看。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukski/ukskinl002.mp3'),('slang','俚语谩骂','uk :slæŋ, us :slæŋ','[army slang \n 军队俚语 \n, a slang expression \n 一句俚语 \n,  Chicken  is slang for someone who isn t very brave. \n chicken 是用来称呼胆小者的俚语。 \n, The players started slanging each other in the middle of the game. \n 比赛到中局阶段时，球员们开始互相谩骂。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksla/uksland004.mp3'),('slicked','熟练自如的，娴熟的油滑的，华而不实的浮油（同 oil slick）高级亮光纸印刷的杂志（同 glossy magazine）使（头发）光滑，使亮滑','uk :slɪk, us :slɪk','[Manilow gave the slick, polished performance that we ve come to expect. \n 正如我们所期望的那样，马尼洛的表演挥洒自如、技艺精湛。 \n, A slick pass from Eaves to Brinkworth set up the goal. \n 布林克沃斯接伊夫斯的妙传射门成功。 \n, It s that sort of slick sales talk that I mistrust. \n 那种油腔滑调的推销宣传正是我所不相信的。 \n, He slicked his hair back with gel. \n 他打了发胶将头发向后梳平整。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksle/uksleep019.mp3'),('slippery','湿滑的，容易打滑的狡猾的，滑头的','uk :ˈslɪp.ər.i, us :ˈslɪp.ɚ.i','[slippery soap \n 湿滑的肥皂 \n, a slippery floor \n 湿滑的地板 \n, The road was wet and slippery. \n 道路又湿又滑。 \n, He s as slippery as an eel - you can never get a straight answer out of him. \n 他非常滑头——你永远无法从他嘴里得到直率的回答。 \n, He s a slippery customer (= person), and I ve never felt comfortable with him. \n 他是个狡猾的家伙，和他在一起我总是感到不舒服。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksli/ukslimm016.mp3'),('slog-away','辛苦干活','','null\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'null'),('slogging','苦干，锲而不舍地做（尤指困难或乏味的工作）艰难行进，跋涉（不加控制地）猛击（球）一段时间的艰苦努力（不加控制的）猛击','uk :slɒɡ, us :slɑːɡ','[I ve been slogging away for days on this essay and I m still not finished. \n 我为了这篇文章已经埋头苦干好几天了，但还没有完成。 \n, Despite the rain, they slogged on for another six miles. \n 尽管下着雨，他们还是又艰难跋涉了6英里。 \n, They slogged up the trail in the rain. \n 他们在雨中沿着小道向上跋涉。 \n, The soldiers slogged through mud. \n 士兵们在泥泞中跋涉。 \n, This semester was a long hard slog; I m glad it s over. \n 这个学期非常艰苦，很高兴终于结束了。 \n, That last hill before the finishing line was a long slog! \n 终点线前的最后一座小山是一段漫长而艰难的赛程！ \n, And that was a real slog from Kumar. \n 那是库马尔的一次真正的大力击球。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukslo/ukslobb004.mp3'),('slot','狭缝；（尤指）投币口，狭槽（为某活动安排的）时段被（能）放于狭槽中','uk :slɒt, us :slɑːt','[I put my money in the slot and pressed the button but nothing came out. \n 我把钱放入投币口，按了按钮，但没有东西出来。 \n, The holder has slots for 100 CDs. \n 这个CD架的槽口可以放100张CD。 \n, The programme will occupy that half-hour slot before the six o clock news. \n 那个节目将在六点新闻前的半小时这一时段播出。 \n, The legs of the chair are meant to slot into the holes at the back. \n 椅子腿应该要插到后面的孔里。 \n, Do these two pieces slot together? \n 这两个部件能插在一起吗? \n, Slot piece A into piece B, taking care to keep the two pieces at right angles. \n 把 A 件插入 B 件，注意使二者保持正确的角度。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukslo/ukslobb018.mp3'),('smack','（尤指作为惩戒孩子的方式）掌掴，打撞；使劲摔（作为惩戒手段的）打巴掌，掴（用握成拳的手）打呯的一声，啪的一声响吻海洛因不偏不倚地，正好径直，猛地；砰然作声地','uk :smæk, us :smæk','[I never smack my children. \n 我从来不打孩子。 \n, I ll smack your bottom if you don t behave yourself. \n 如果你表现不好，我就打你屁股。 \n, I smacked my head on the corner of the shelf. \n 我的头撞在了架子角上。 \n, She smacked her books down on the table and stormed out of the room. \n 她啪地把书摔在桌子上，气冲冲地离开了房间。 \n, You re going to get a smack on the bottom if you don t stop throwing your toys. \n 如果你再乱扔玩具，就该打屁股了。 \n, I gave him a smack on the jaw. \n 我一拳头打在他下巴上。 \n, She slammed her briefcase down on the desk with a smack. \n 她啪的一声把她的皮箱放到桌子上。 \n, a big smack on the lips \n 在嘴唇上的响亮一吻 \n, How long has she been on smack? \n 她吸海洛因多长时间了？ \n, She lives smack in the middle of Shanghai. \n 她住在上海市的正中心。 \n, S \n The kids are smack dab in the middle of the fight between their parents. \n 父母吵架时，孩子们被夹在正中间。 \n, I wasn t looking where I was going and walked smack into a lamppost. \n 我没有看路，直愣愣地撞到了灯柱上。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukslu/ukslutt010.mp3'),('smuggle','走私；（常指非法）偷运','uk :ˈsmʌɡ.əl, us :ˈsmʌɡ.əl','[She was caught trying to smuggle 26 kilos of heroin out of/into the country. \n 她在企图把26千克海洛因走私出境／入境时被抓获。 \n, They managed to smuggle a video of the captive journalists out of the prison. \n 他们设法把被俘记者的录像带偷偷带出了监狱。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksmo/uksmoke026.mp3'),('sneeze','打喷嚏喷嚏','uk :sniːz, us :sniːz','[Cats make him sneeze - I think he s allergic to them. \n 猫会使他打喷嚏——我想他对猫过敏。 \n, He has all the classic symptoms of a cold - the coughs and sneezes and the sore throat. \n 他具备感冒的所有典型症状——咳嗽、打喷嚏和嗓子疼。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksne/uksneak005.mp3'),('soapy','含有肥皂的；像肥皂的','uk :ˈsəʊ.pi, us :ˈsoʊ.pi','[I soaked it in some soapy water and the stains came out. \n 我把它浸泡在肥皂水中，污渍就被洗去了。 \n, I used to think avocados tasted soapy when I was a child. \n 我小时候曾认为鳄梨的味道像肥皂。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksno/uksnows025.mp3'),('sock','短袜，袜子重重的一击（用拳头）打，击（棒球运动中）猛击，狠打（球）','uk :sɒk, us :sɑːk','[a pair of socks \n 一双短袜 \n, nylon/woollen/cotton socks \n 尼龙／羊毛／纯棉短袜 \n, thermal socks \n 保暖袜 \n, ankle/knee socks \n 及脚踝／膝的袜子 \n, Put on your shoes and socks. \n 穿上你的鞋袜。 \n, The little boy was wearing odd socks (= socks of different colours). \n 小男孩穿着两只不配对的袜子。 \n, a sock on the jaw \n 下巴上挨的重重一拳 \n, He socked the policeman on the jaw/in the eye. \n 他冲着警察的下巴／眼睛就是一拳。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksob/uksober023.mp3'),('sophisticated','精于世故的，老练的；见多识广的；很有品位的精密的，复杂的；高级的','uk :səˈfɪs.tɪ.keɪ.tɪd, us :səˈfɪs.tə.keɪ.t̬ɪd','[She was slim, svelte, and sophisticated. \n 她身材苗条，体态娇美，处事练达。 \n, I don t think I have any books that would suit your sophisticated tastes. \n 我认为我没有什么书能满足你那高雅的品位。 \n, He was older than me and from London and I thought him very sophisticated. \n 他比我大，而且来自伦敦，我觉得他为人很老练。 \n, I think a more sophisticated approach is needed to solve this problem. \n 我认为要解决这个问题需要更为高明的方法。 \n, These are among the most sophisticated weapons in the world. \n 这些属于世界上最尖端的武器。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksoo/uksoon_012.mp3'),('sophomore','（美国大学或高中的）二年级学生','uk :ˈsɒf.ə.mɔːr, us :ˈsɑː.fə.mɔːr','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksoo/uksoon_015.mp3'),('sought','搜寻','uk :sɔːt, us :sɑːt',NULL,'2020-02-13',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uks/uksor/uksorel011.mp3'),('sour','酸的，有酸味的不友好的；坏脾气的，没好气的（使）变酸；（使）酸腐（使）令人不快，（使）不友好酸味鸡尾酒','uk :saʊər, us :saʊr','[These plums are a bit sour. \n 这些李子有点酸。 \n, Overnight, it seemed, their relationship had turned sour. \n 他们的关系似乎在一夜之间变糟了。 \n, She gave me a sour look. \n 她没好气地瞪了我一眼。 \n, Hot weather sours milk. \n 热天会让牛奶变酸。 \n, Milk sours in hot weather. \n 牛奶在热天会变酸。 \n, Her whole attitude to life soured as a result of that experience. \n 那次经历过后，她对生活的整个态度变得很消极。 \n, This incident has soured relations between the two countries. \n 这一事件导致两国关系恶化。 \n, a whisky sour \n 威士忌酸味鸡尾酒 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksou/uksound010.mp3'),('souvenir','纪念品；纪念物','uk :ˌsuː.vənˈɪər, us :ˌsuː.vəˈnɪr',NULL,'2020-02-14',5,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksou/uksouth007.mp3'),('spacious','宽敞的，空间大的','uk :ˈspeɪ.ʃəs, us :ˈspeɪ.ʃəs','[a spacious house/living room \n 宽敞的房子／起居室 \n, spacious accommodation \n 宽敞的住宿条件 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksou/uksouth030.mp3'),('spam','（斯帕姆）午餐肉垃圾邮件（通常指广告）给…发垃圾邮件','uk :spæm, us :spæm','[spam fritters \n 油炸午餐肉馅饼 \n, I get so much spam at work. \n 我的工作邮箱收到如此之多的垃圾邮件。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/ukspaci009.mp3'),('spare','额外的，备用的；多余的空闲时间瘦高的，瘦长的简朴的，未装饰的很恼火，很生气饶恕；不伤害；不毁坏使避免，使免遭不遗余力／不惜工本竭尽全力，全力以赴（尤指在自己困难的情况下）抽出，拨出，匀出替（某人）着想剩下，多余备用品（汽车或其他设备的）备件，配件','uk :speər, us :sper','[a spare key/tyre \n 备用钥匙／轮胎 \n, spare sheets and blankets \n 多余的床单和毛毯 \n, Do you have a spare pen? \n 你有多余的笔吗？ \n, We have a spare room if you want to stay overnight with us. \n 要是你想在我们这里过夜的话，我们有一个空房间。 \n, Could I have a word with you when you have a spare moment/minute? \n 如果你有时间，我能否和你谈两句？ \n, K informal \n  Do you want this cake?   Yes, if it s going spare (= if no one else wants it).  \n “你要这块蛋糕吗？”“如果没有别人要，就给我吧。” \n, I like to paint in my spare time. \n 我业余时间喜欢画画。 \n, He had the spare build of a runner. \n 他有着赛跑运动员的瘦长体型。 \n, The interior is spare, almost minimalist. \n 内部是简朴的，几乎是最简单的。 \n, She goes spare if I m so much as five minutes late. \n 如果我迟到5分钟，她就会很生气。 \n, They asked him to spare the women and children. \n 他们要他放过妇女和儿童。 \n, Luckily, I was spared the embarrassment of having to sing in front of everyone. \n 幸运的是，我躲过了在大家面前唱歌的尴尬。 \n, It was a nasty accident - but I ll spare you (= I won t tell you) the gruesome details. \n 那是一起严重的事故——我就不跟你讲那些令人毛骨悚然的细节了。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We will spare no effort to find out who did this. \n 我们会不遗余力，一定查出是谁做了这件事。 \n, She never spared herself in the pursuit of excellence. \n 她竭尽全力追求卓越。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n Could you spare me £20? \n 你能匀给我20英镑吗？ \n, I d love to come, but I can t spare the time. \n 我很想来，但恐怕没时间。 \n, Spare a thought for me tomorrow, when you re lying on a beach, because I ll still be here in the office! \n 明天你躺在海滩上的时候，就想想我吧，因为我还在办公室里！ \n, If you have any woolyarn to spare when you ve finished the sweater, can you make me some gloves? \n 如果你织完毛衣还剩下毛线的话，可以给我织副手套吗？ \n, I caught the plane with only two minutes to spare. \n 我赶上飞机时距离起飞只剩两分钟了。 \n, There s no time/We have no time to spare if we want to get the article written by tomorrow. \n 如果我们想明天就把这篇文章写完，那么就没剩多少时间了。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/ukspaci022.mp3'),('spawn','（鱼、青蛙等的）卵小动物；小孩（使）产生，（使）突然增长产卵','uk :spɔːn, us :spɑːn','[isapproving \n He looked at me as if I was a spawn of Satan because I was smoking a cigarette. \n 他看着我的样子，仿佛是看到了恶魔一般，就因为我抽烟。 \n, The new economic freedom has spawned hundreds of new small businesses. \n 新的经济自由催生了上百家新的小企业。 \n, Her death spawned countless films and books. \n 她的去世催生了无数电影和书籍。 \n, The frogs haven t spawned yet. \n 青蛙还未产卵。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/uksparr017.mp3'),('speakeasy','（美国20世纪20至30年代）非法销售饮用酒精饮料的地方','uk :ˈspiːkˌiː.zi, us :ˈspiːkˌiː.zi','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/uksparr020.mp3'),('species','（动植物的）种，物种','uk :ˈspiː.ʃiːz, us :ˈspiː.ʃiːz','[Mountain gorillas are an endangered species. \n 山地大猩猩属于濒危物种。 \n, Over a hundred species of insect are found in this area. \n 这一地区有上百种昆虫。 \n, igurative humorous \n Women film directors in Hollywood are a rare species. \n 女性电影导演在好莱坞属于稀有物种。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspe/ukspeci007.mp3'),('speculate','猜测；推测，推断投机，做投机买卖','uk :ˈspek.jə.leɪt, us :ˈspek.jə.leɪt','[I don t know why she did it - I m just speculating. \n 我不知道她为什么那么做——我只是猜测。 \n, A spokesperson declined to speculate on the cause of the train crash. \n 一位发言人拒绝就火车相撞事件的原因作出推测。 \n, Journalists are speculating about whether interest rates will be cut. \n 记者们在猜测是否会降息。 \n, [ + that ] \n The newspapers have speculated that they will get married next year. \n 报纸猜测他们明年会结婚。 \n, He made his money speculating on the London gold and silver markets. \n 他在伦敦黄金市场和白银市场上做投机生意赚了钱。 \n, The company has been speculating in property for years. \n 这家公司做房地产投机生意已经有好几年了。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspe/ukspect003.mp3'),('speculator','投机商，投机者','uk :ˈspek.jə.leɪ.tər, us :ˈspek.jə.leɪ.t̬ɚ','[]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspe/ukspect007.mp3'),('splintered','（木头、玻璃、塑料等的）尖细条，尖碎片裂成碎片','uk :ˈsplɪn.tər, us :ˈsplɪn.tɚ','[The girl had a splinter (of wood) in her toe. \n 女孩脚趾上扎进了一块（木头）碎片。 \n, The edges of the plastic cover had cracked and splintered. \n 塑料罩子的边缘裂成了碎片。 \n, igurative \n The danger is that the Conservative Party may splinter into several smaller political parties. \n 危险在于保守党可能会分裂成几个小的政党。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee010.mp3'),('spoiler','（汽车的）气流偏导器；（机翼的）扰流器（某报刊或电视台抢先或同期推出的）试图抢风头的文章（或节目）,剧透·','uk :ˈspɔɪ.lər, us :ˈspɔɪ.lɚ','[]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee021.mp3'),('spondulix','（幽默的说法）货币；钱，金钱；财产','uk :spɒnˈduː.lɪks, us :spɑːnˈduː.lɪks','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee028.mp3'),('sponge','（擦洗物品用的）海绵（用海绵或布）擦拭，擦洗海绵蛋糕白吃，白要；（尤指）吃白饭用湿海绵（或湿布）擦，擦洗','uk :spʌndʒ, us :spʌndʒ','[Give it a sponge with a damp cloth - that will remove the blood stains. \n 用湿布擦一下——能把血迹擦掉。 \n, sponging off the state \n 靠国家来养活 \n, Most food stains will come off if you sponge the material with a little detergent. \n 用一点去污剂能去除布料上的大部分食物污渍。 \n, The doctor told me to sponge Erik down with cold water in order to lower his temperature. \n 医生告诉我用冷水给埃里克擦身，以帮他降低体温。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee029.mp3'),('spreadsheet','（尤用于商务的）电子表格程序','uk :ˈspred.ʃiːt, us :ˈspred.ʃiːt','[]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspo/ukspotl019.mp3'),('square','正方形，四方形正方形物，四方形物（城镇中的）广场（常包括周围的建筑）（游戏中棋盘的）格直角尺，丁字尺古板的人；老古董使成平方；使成二次幂正方形的，四方形的（与长度单位连用）平方的（紧接长度单位后）…见方正的；相等的；水平的两清的，互不欠账的平局的直线的，笔直的乏味的；古板守旧的使成平方；使成二次幂（表示决心已定）挺起胸膛，挺直身子','uk :skweər, us :skwer',NULL,'2020-01-07',0,3,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksqu/uksquab010.mp3'),('squishy','软弱','uk :ˈskwɪʃ.i, us :ˈskwɪʃ.i','[ squishy banana\n, he whole idea of what constitutes a disability is squishy. \n, he definition of spam is squishy - a message that you delete I may think is a worthwhile offer.\n, hey feel he is too squishy on issues such as the rights of suspected terrorists.\n, he toy shop has a range of squishies for kids who love to squeeze, squish, and squash. \n, quishy white bread\n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uks/uksqu/uksquee019.mp3'),('staircase','（建筑物内通常带有扶手的）楼梯','uk :ˈsteə.keɪs, us :ˈster.keɪs','[She descended the sweeping (= long and wide) staircase into the crowd of photographers and journalists. \n 她走下又长又宽的楼梯，来到摄影师和记者中间。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksta/ukstabl030.mp3'),('statistical','统计的；统计学的','uk :stəˈtɪs.tɪ.kəl, us :stəˈtɪs.tɪ.kəl','[statistical errors/evidence \n 统计错误／证据 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksta/ukstate017.mp3'),('sterile','（生物）不育的；（土地）贫瘠的，不长作物的缺乏想象力的；缺乏新意的；无生气的消过毒的，无菌的','uk :ˈster.aɪl, us :ˈster.əl','[Mules are usually sterile. \n 骡子通常无法生育。 \n, One of the side effects of the drug could be to make men sterile. \n 这种药物的副作用之一是可能会导致男性不育。 \n, a sterile argument \n 毫无新意的论点 \n, The operation must be carried out under sterile conditions. \n 手术必须在无菌条件下进行。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukste/ukstere007.mp3'),('stiff','硬的，挺的，坚实的不易弯曲的；不易活动的（人或身体部位）僵硬的，强直的拘谨的，局促的，生硬的严厉的，严格的；艰难的强风烈性酒／白兰地／杜松子酒（等等）（价格）高昂的，过高的十分，非常…的人死尸不付…欠下的钱','uk :stɪf, us :stɪf','[stiff cardboard \n 硬纸板 \n, a stiff collar \n 硬领 \n, His clothes were stiff with dried mud. \n 他的衣服上的泥干了，硬邦邦的。 \n, This hair spray has made my hair stiff. \n 这种发胶使我的头发变硬了。 \n, Mix the powder and water into a stiff paste. \n 把粉末和水混合成稠糊。 \n, The handle on this door is rather stiff. \n 这扇门的把手相当紧。 \n, The man s body was (as) stiff as a board when it was found in the snow. \n 在雪地里找到这名男子时，他的身体已经僵硬了。 \n, Sitting still at a computer terminal all day can give you a stiff neck. \n 在电脑前一动不动地坐上一整天会令人颈部发僵。 \n, The general is a tall man with steel spectacles and a stiff, pompous manner. \n 将军是个戴着金属框眼镜的高个男子，态度生硬，相当傲慢。 \n, The athlete was given a stiff punishment for using drugs. \n 这名运动员因服用违禁药物受到了严厉的惩罚。 \n, They are campaigning for stiffer penalties for people who drink and drive. \n 他们正在进行游说活动，要求对酒后驾车者处以更严厉的惩罚。 \n, There has been stiff opposition/resistance to the proposed tax increases. \n 增加税收的提案遭到了强烈的反对／抵制。 \n, It s a stiff climb to the top of the hill. \n 要爬上山顶很费劲。 \n, Some colleges have stiffer entry requirements than others. \n 有些大学比其他大学有更严格的入学资格要求。 \n, Both companies are worried about losing business in the face of stiff competition. \n 两家公司都担心在激烈的竞争中损失业务。 \n, A stiff whisky - that s what I need. \n 一杯烈性威士忌——这是我真正需要的。 \n, We had to pay a stiff membership fee to join the health club. \n 我们支付了一笔高昂的会费后才得以加入这家健康俱乐部。 \n, I got frozen stiff (= very cold) waiting at the bus stop. \n 我在公交车站等车时差点儿冻僵了。 \n, I was scared stiff when I heard someone moving around upstairs. \n 我听到楼上有人走来走去时吓坏了。 \n, a working stiff \n 工作狂 \n, you lucky stiff \n 你这个幸运的家伙 \n, They found a stiff in the river. \n 他们在河里发现了一具尸体。 \n, She stiffed the cab driver. \n 她没有付给出租车司机钱。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksti/ukstick006.mp3'),('stimulating','（物）有启发性的（人）能激发热情的，激发灵感的（活动）增强活力的，促进身体机能的','uk :ˈstɪm.jə.leɪ.tɪŋ, us :ˈstɪm.jə.leɪ.t̬ɪŋ','[a stimulating discussion \n 具有启发性的讨论 \n, The classes look attractive and stimulating. \n 这些课程看起来既有吸引力又有启发性。 \n, a really stimulating teacher \n 真正循循善诱的老师 \n, Aerobics is one of the most stimulating forms of exercise. \n 有氧健身操是最能增强身体活力的锻炼之一。 \n]\n','2020-02-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksti/ukstick029.mp3'),('stoic','克制感情的；（尤指面对逆境）坚忍的，隐忍的恬淡寡欲者；克制感情的人','uk :ˈstəʊ.ɪk, us :ˈstoʊ.ɪk','[We knew she must be in pain, despite her stoic attitude. \n 尽管她非常坚忍，但我们知道她一定很痛苦。 \n, He showed a stoic resignation towards his fate. \n 他在命运面前表现得听天由命，隐忍顺从。 \n, Local people were stoical about the damage caused by the hurricane. \n 当地居民默默承受了飓风造成的破坏。 \n, My father is a stoic by nature and found it hard to express his grief when my mother died. \n 我父亲天生隐忍克制，我母亲去世时他很难表露自己的悲伤之情。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksto/ukstock022.mp3'),('stomp','迈着重重的步子走；（尤指）怒气冲冲地走（常指为表示生气）跺（脚）；重踏，重踩','uk :stɒmp, us :stɑːmp','[She stomped up the stairs and slammed her bedroom door. \n 她噔噔噔地上了楼，重重地关上了卧室的门。 \n, He woke up in a bad mood and stomped off to the bathroom. \n 他一觉醒来心情不佳，噔噔地踩着重步走向浴室。 \n, The little boy was stomping his foot and refusing to take his medicine. \n 那个小男孩跺着脚不肯吃药。 \n, She stood by the road, stomping her feet to stay warm. \n 她站在路边，跺着脚让自己暖和些。 \n, I wish those people upstairs would stop stomping around. \n 我希望楼上那些人别再乱跺脚了。 \n, Why did you stomp on that insect? \n 你为什么要踩那只虫子？ \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksto/ukstoma003.mp3'),('strategies','战略；策略；计谋；行动计划；策划，部署','uk :ˈstræt.ə.dʒi, us :ˈstræt̬.ə.dʒi','[The president held an emergency meeting to discuss military strategy with the Pentagon yesterday. \n 总统昨天召开紧急会议，跟五角大楼商讨军事战略。 \n, Their marketing strategy for the product involves obtaining as much free publicity as possible. \n 他们对这一产品采取的市场策略包括尽可能去争取免费宣传的机会。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We re working on new strategies to improve our share of the market. \n 我们正在制订新策略来增加我们的市场份额。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstr/ukstrat003.mp3'),('strategy','战略；策略；计谋；行动计划；策划，部署','uk :ˈstræt.ə.dʒi, us :ˈstræt̬.ə.dʒi','[The president held an emergency meeting to discuss military strategy with the Pentagon yesterday. \n 总统昨天召开紧急会议，跟五角大楼商讨军事战略。 \n, Their marketing strategy for the product involves obtaining as much free publicity as possible. \n 他们对这一产品采取的市场策略包括尽可能去争取免费宣传的机会。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We\'re working on new strategies to improve our share of the market. \n 我们正在制订新策略来增加我们的市场份额。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstr/ukstrat003.mp3'),('stuffy','（房间或建筑物）闷的，通风不畅的古板的，保守的，一本正经的','uk :ˈstʌf.i, us :ˈstʌf.i','[a stuffy office \n 空气污浊的办公室 \n, It s really hot and stuffy in here - let s open the window. \n 这里又热又闷——我们把窗户打开吧。 \n, The bedroom gets a little stuffy in the summer. \n 这个房间在夏天有点闷。 \n, Sir William had the ability to conduct proceedings in a dignified manner without ever becoming stuffy. \n 威廉爵士能够以庄重但毫不刻板的方式主持会议。 \n, She is trying to promote a less stuffy image of librarians. \n 他在努力提升图书管理员的形象，想使之显得不那么古板。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstu/ukstubb024.mp3'),('sturdy','结实的，牢固的；强壮的坚决的，坚定的','uk :ˈstɜː.di, us :ˈstɝː.di','[sturdy walking boots \n 结实的徒步靴 \n, a sturdy table \n 结实的桌子 \n, sturdy little legs \n 结实的小腿 \n, They put up a sturdy defence of their proposal. \n 他们坚定地为自己的提议辩护。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstu/ukstun_020.mp3'),('submission','提交；呈递顺从，屈服；不得以接受','uk :səbˈmɪʃ.ən, us :səbˈmɪʃ.ən','[No date has yet been set for the submission of applications. \n 申请的提交日期还未确定。 \n, The final deadline for submissions is 21 February. \n 提交的最后期限是2月21日。 \n, [ + that ] \n formal \n The judge will hear the defence s submission (= suggestion) that the case be dismissed. \n 法官将听取被告方撤销该案的意见。 \n, They thought the country could be bombed into submission. \n 他们认为轰炸可以使该国屈服。 \n, The teachers agreed to a special meeting, in submission to parents  demands. \n 在家长的要求下，老师们只得同意召开特别会议。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksub/uksubhe027.mp3'),('succor','帮助；（尤指）救助，救援帮助；（尤指）救助，救援','uk :ˈsʌk.ər, us :ˈsʌk.ɚ','[Her organization gave succour and strength to those who had been emotionally damaged. \n 她的机构向那些情感上受到过伤害的人提供帮助和支持。 \n, to succour the poor, help the helpless, support the weak \n 救助贫困者，帮助无助者，支持弱者 \n, Students should be encouraged, supported and succoured. \n 学生们应该受到鼓励、支持和帮助。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksub/uksubur021.mp3'),('succumb','屈从，屈服；放弃抵抗；承认失败病死；生病；受病痛折磨','uk :səˈkʌm, us :səˈkʌm','[The town finally succumbed last week after being pounded with heavy artillery for more than two months. \n 在遭受了两个多月的猛烈炮火轰击后，小镇最终在上星期放弃了抵抗。 \n, I m afraid I succumbed to temptation and had a piece of cheesecake. \n 我还是没顶住诱惑，吃了一块奶酪蛋糕。 \n, I felt sure it would only be a matter of time before he succumbed to my charms. \n 我确信他为我的魅力所倾倒只不过是个时间问题。 \n, Thousands of cows have succumbed to the disease in the past few months. \n 过去几个月里，几千头奶牛都得了这种病。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksub/uksubur024.mp3'),('summit','峰会，首脑会议，最高级会议山顶，顶峰顶峰，极点，巅峰','uk :ˈsʌm.ɪt, us :ˈsʌm.ɪt','[a summit meeting \n 首脑会议 \n, World leaders will meet next week for their annual economic summit. \n 世界各国领导人将在下周齐聚一堂，参加一年一度的经济峰会。 \n, On this day in 1784, Dr Michel Paccard and Jacques Balmat reached the summit of Mont Blanc. \n 1784年的今天，迈克尔‧帕卡德医生和雅克‧巴尔马特登上了勃朗峰的顶峰。 \n, I certainly haven\'t reached the summit of my career. \n 当然，我还没有达到事业的巅峰。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksul/uksulta014.mp3'),('superior','好于平均的，好过其他的，优越的（人）高傲的，傲慢的，有优越感的上司（的），上级（的）更靠近头，更远离脚的上司，上级','uk :suːˈpɪə.ri.ər, us :səˈpɪr.i.ɚ','[This is clearly the work of a superior artist. \n 这显然是一位优秀艺术家的作品。 \n, She was chosen for the job because she was the superior candidate. \n 因为她比其他应聘者更出色，所以她被选中做这份工作。 \n, For babies, breastfeeding is superior to bottle-feeding. \n 对婴儿来说，母乳喂养比奶瓶喂养好得多。 \n, The government troops were superior in numbers (= there were more of them). \n 政府军在人数上占优势。 \n, a superior manner/smile \n 傲慢的态度／微笑 \n, I can t stand Amanda - she s so superior. \n 我受不了阿曼达——她太高傲了。 \n, The soldier was reported to his superior officer for failing in his duties. \n 这个士兵失职之事被报告到了他的上级那里。 \n, The head is superior to the shoulder. \n 头比肩离脚更远。 \n, I will pass your complaint on to my superiors. \n 我会把您的投诉转达给我的上司。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksup/uksuper004.mp3'),('supervised','监督，管理，指导','uk :ˈsuː.pə.vaɪz, us :ˈsuː.pɚ.vaɪz','[The UN is supervising the distribution of aid by local agencies in the disaster area. \n 联合国正在监督灾区的地方机构发放救援物资。 \n, The children play while two teachers supervise (= make certain that they behave correctly and are safe). \n 孩子们在两位教师的监管下玩耍。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksup/uksuper030.mp3'),('surly','脾气坏的；不友好的，粗鲁无礼的','uk :ˈsɜː.li, us :ˈsɝː.li','[We were served by a very surly waiter. \n 为我们服务的侍者态度很差。 \n, He gave me a surly look. \n 他很不友好地看了我一眼。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksur/uksurge008.mp3'),('suspend','停止，暂停，中止（因犯错而）暂令停职；暂令停学；暂令停止参加活动悬挂悬浮，漂浮','uk :səˈspend, us :səˈspend','[The ferry service has been suspended for the day because of bad weather. \n 因为天气恶劣，渡船已经停开了。 \n, The country\'s president has suspended the constitution and assumed total power. \n 总统废除了宪法，独揽大权。 \n, When you go to the theatre, you have to be willing to suspend disbelief (= to act as if you believe that what you are seeing is real or true, although you know that it is not). \n 去戏院看戏时你得对剧情深信不疑。 \n, I\'m suspending judgment (= not forming an opinion) on the book I\'m reading until I\'ve finished it. \n 把书读完之前我不会作任何评价。 \n, Mr Young was given a six-month jail sentence, suspended for two years (= if he commits another crime within two years, he will have to go to prison for six months for his original crime). \n 杨先生被判监禁6个月，缓期2年执行。 \n, She was suspended from school for fighting. \n 她因为打架而被勒令停学。 \n, He was suspended for four games after arguing with the referee. \n 跟裁判发生争执之后，他被停赛4场。 \n, The builders worked on wooden platforms, suspended by ropes from the roof of the building. \n 建筑工人站在用绳子从房顶上吊下来的木制平台上作业。 \n, It was very uncomfortable lying on the hospital bed with my legs suspended in the air. \n 我躺在医院的病床上，腿悬吊在半空，难受极了。 \n, The drug is suspended in a saline solution. \n 这种药悬浮在生理盐水中。 \n, A cloud of smoke was suspended in the air. \n 空中飘浮着一团烟雾。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksur/uksurro024.mp3'),('sustain','保持，维持，使持续，使继续维持…的生命，供养经历，遭受（尤指破坏或损失）（情感上）支持','uk :səˈsteɪn, us :səˈsteɪn','[The economy looks set to sustain its growth into next year. \n 看来经济的增长会持续到明年。 \n, He seems to find it difficult to sustain relationships with women. \n 他似乎觉得和女人维持关系并不容易。 \n, S \n The judge sustained (= accepted) the lawyer s objection. \n 法官接受了律师的反对意见。 \n, The soil in this part of the world is not rich enough to sustain a large population. \n 这里的土地不够肥沃，无法供养大量的人口。 \n, She sustained multiple injuries in the accident. \n 她在这次事故中多处受伤。 \n, Most buildings sustained only minimal damage in the earthquake. \n 在这次地震中，大多数建筑物受到的破坏都很小。 \n, The company has sustained heavy losses this year. \n 公司今年遭受了严重的亏损。 \n, She was sustained by the strength of her religious faith. \n 宗教信仰的力量支撑着她。 \n, The love of my family and friends sustained me through my ordeal. \n 家人和朋友的爱支撑着我渡过了难关。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksus/uksuspi003.mp3'),('swath','长条区域，大块区域；（尤指）长条田地，大块田地部分；范围绷带，布条，带子（用布）裹，绑，包，缠','uk :sweɪð, us :sweɪð','[Huge swathes of rainforest are being cleared for farming and mining. \n 为了耕种和采矿，大片大片的雨林被砍伐。 \n, These people represent a broad/wide swathe of public opinion. \n 这些人代表了广大人民的意见。 \n, His head was wrapped in swathes of bandages. \n 他的头上缠着绷带。 \n, He came out of the hospital swathed in bandages. \n 他从医院出来时身上缠满了绷带。 \n, I love to swathe (= dress) myself in silk. \n 我喜欢穿丝绸做的衣服。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswa/ukswast004.mp3'),('swathe','长条区域，大块区域；（尤指）长条田地，大块田地部分；范围绷带，布条，带子（用布）裹，绑，包，缠','uk :sweɪð, us :sweɪð','[Huge swathes of rainforest are being cleared for farming and mining. \n 为了耕种和采矿，大片大片的雨林被砍伐。 \n, These people represent a broad/wide swathe of public opinion. \n 这些人代表了广大人民的意见。 \n, His head was wrapped in swathes of bandages. \n 他的头上缠着绷带。 \n, He came out of the hospital swathed in bandages. \n 他从医院出来时身上缠满了绷带。 \n, I love to swathe (= dress) myself in silk. \n 我喜欢穿丝绸做的衣服。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswa/ukswast004.mp3'),('swell','肿胀，肿，膨胀（音乐声等）变大，增大，变响亮（缓慢的）波涛起伏（乐器）音量的变大极好的极好地','uk :swel, us :swel','[It was obvious she had broken her toe, because it immediately started to swell (up). \n 她的脚趾显然已经骨折，因为立刻肿起来了。 \n, The group recruited more members, swelling its ranks (= increasing its size) to more than 1.3 million. \n 这个团体招募了更多会员，总人数已超过130万人。 \n, iterary \n His heart/breast swelled with pride (= he felt very proud) as he stood watching his son graduate. \n 当他站在那里观看儿子的毕业典礼时，心中充满自豪。 \n, That s a swell idea! \n 那个主意好极了！ \n, Everything s going swell. \n 一切都很顺利。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet002.mp3'),('swells','肿胀，肿，膨胀（音乐声等）变大，增大，变响亮（缓慢的）波涛起伏（乐器）音量的变大极好的极好地','uk :swel, us :swel','[It was obvious she had broken her toe, because it immediately started to swell (up). \n 她的脚趾显然已经骨折，因为立刻肿起来了。 \n, The group recruited more members, swelling its ranks (= increasing its size) to more than 1.3 million. \n 这个团体招募了更多会员，总人数已超过130万人。 \n, iterary \n His heart/breast swelled with pride (= he felt very proud) as he stood watching his son graduate. \n 当他站在那里观看儿子的毕业典礼时，心中充满自豪。 \n, That s a swell idea! \n 那个主意好极了！ \n, Everything s going swell. \n 一切都很顺利。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet002.mp3'),('swift','迅速的，敏捷的，快的雨燕','uk :swɪft, us :swɪft','[The police took swift action against the rioters. \n 警方对暴动人员迅速采取了行动。 \n, Thank you for your swift reply. \n 感谢您的即时回复。 \n, The gazelle is one of the swiftest and most graceful of animals. \n 瞪羚是最敏捷、最优雅的动物之一。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet010.mp3'),('swinging','令人兴奋的；时尚的','uk :ˈswɪŋ.ɪŋ, us :ˈswɪŋ.ɪŋ','[It s a nostalgia trip back into the youth culture of the swinging 60s. \n 这是一次感受风靡一时的60年代青年文化的怀旧之旅。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet029.mp3'),('swivel','（使）转动，（使）旋转转动的，旋转的','uk :ˈswɪv.əl, us :ˈswɪv.əl','[She swivelled round to look out of the window. \n 她转过身看着窗外。 \n, The ostrich swivelled its head in our direction. \n 鸵鸟把头转向我们。 \n, a swivel chair \n 转椅 \n, a swivel lamp \n 旋转灯 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswi/ukswipe013.mp3'),('sympathy','同情（心），理解慰问，吊唁，吊慰支持，赞同支持参加罢工以支持（某人）','uk :ˈsɪm.pə.θi, us :ˈsɪm.pə.θi','[The president has sent a message of sympathy to the relatives of the dead soldiers. \n 总统已经向阵亡士兵的家属发去了唁电。 \n, I don t have much sympathy for her - I think she s brought her troubles on herself. \n 我不太同情她——我觉得她是在自找麻烦。 \n, I went along to the funeral in order to offer my sympathies. \n 我去参加了葬礼以表吊慰。 \n, I must confess I have some sympathy with his views. \n 我必须承认我比较赞同他的观点。 \n, Of those people questioned, 93 percent said their sympathies were with the teachers. \n 接受调查的人当中有93%表示支持教师。 \n, He is known to have right-wing sympathies. \n 大家都知道他支持右翼。 \n, The railway workers came out in sympathy with the miners. \n 铁路工人加入了罢工，声援煤矿工人。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksym/uksympa002.mp3'),('symptom','（疾病的）症状征兆，征候','uk :ˈsɪmp.təm, us :ˈsɪmp.təm','[He s complaining of all the usual flu symptoms - a high temperature, headache, and so on. \n 他说他出现了所有常见的感冒症状——高烧、头痛等。 \n, He s been HIV-positive for six years, but just recently he s started to develop the symptoms of AIDS. \n 他 HIV 病毒检测呈阳性已有6年时间，但直到最近才开始出现艾滋病的症状。 \n, It s her feeling that the recent outbreaks of violence are a symptom of the dissatisfaction that is currently affecting our society. \n 她觉得最近爆发的暴力事件表明目前不满情绪正在影响我们的社会。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksym/uksympa008.mp3'),('syndrome','综合征，征群，综合症状（用于多种病名中）综合征（特定情形下人的）典型负面特征，典型负面表现','uk :ˈsɪn.drəʊm, us :ˈsɪn.droʊm','[irritable bowel syndrome \n 肠易激综合征 \n, It s a classic case of the bored-housewife syndrome - she has nothing to do all day except eat and go shopping. \n 这是百无聊赖的家庭主妇的典型特征——她成天除了喝酒、购物，就没有什么事情可干了。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksym/uksympa022.mp3'),('synonym','同义词，近义词','uk :ˈsɪn.ə.nɪm, us :ˈsɪn.ə.nɪm',NULL,'2020-02-13',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksym/uksympa026.mp3'),('tactics','策略，手法战术','uk :ˈtæk.tɪk, us :ˈtæk.tɪk','[These bomb attacks represent a change of tactics by the terrorists. \n 这些炸弹袭击事件表明恐怖分子改变了策略。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktab/uktable029.mp3'),('talkative','爱说话的，健谈的；多嘴的','uk :ˈtɔː.kə.tɪv, us :ˈtɑː.kə.t̬ɪv','[She s a lively, talkative person. \n 她是个活泼健谈的人。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktaj/uktajik018.mp3'),('tango','探戈舞；探戈舞曲','uk :ˈtæŋ.ɡəʊ, us :ˈtæŋ.ɡoʊ','[]\n','2019-12-20',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktal/uktalmu025.mp3'),('tariff','关税；关税表','uk :ˈtær.ɪf, us :ˈter.ɪf','[]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktar/uktarge002.mp3'),('teaser','有趣的难题；智力测验题','uk :ˈtiː.zər, us :ˈtiː.zɚ','[]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktea/ukteams012.mp3'),('temerity','鲁莽；冒失','uk :təˈmer.ə.ti, us :təˈmer.ə.t̬i',NULL,'2020-02-14',10,11,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktel/uktelex008.mp3'),('tenfold','十倍的有十个部分的（以）十倍（地)','uk :ˈten.fəʊld, us :ˈten.foʊld','[a tenfold increase \n 十倍的增长 \n, a tenfold classification \n 十部分的分类 \n, Membership grew more than tenfold this year.  \n 今年会员人数增长了十倍。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.ca