他的生意很兴隆。 \n, She seems to thrive on stress. \n 她似乎很擅长在压力下工作。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktho/ukthoug026.mp3'),('thwart','反对；阻挠；挫败','uk :θwɔːt, us :θwɔːrt',NULL,'2020-02-13',5,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthu/ukthund012.mp3'),('tobacco-stained','烟草染色','Yāncǎo rǎnsè','\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=tobacco-stained&tl=ja&tk=734078.853770&client=webapp&prev=input'),('toggle','套索扣，栓扣钉切换键（点击同一按键来）切换','uk :ˈtɒɡ.əl, us :ˈtɑː.ɡəl','[Select the function you require by pointing to the toggle (= image of a button on the screen) with the mouse and then clicking. \n 将鼠标移向切换图标并点击，选择你所需要的功能。 \n, Use this key to toggle between the two typefaces. \n 用这个键在这两种字体间切换。 \n, By toggling this key, you can switch the italics on and off. \n 用这个键来切换，你能够打开和关闭斜体字。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktob/uktobyj018.mp3'),('tolerance','宽容；忍受；容忍忍耐力；忍受力（动植物对药物或毒药的）耐受性公差；容许偏差','uk :ˈtɒl.ər.əns, us :ˈtɑː.lɚ.əns',NULL,'2020-02-14',3,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktol/uktold_004.mp3'),('tolerate','宽容；容忍忍耐；忍受','uk :ˈtɒl.ər.eɪt, us :ˈtɑː.lə.reɪt','[I will not tolerate that kind of behaviour in my class. \n 在我的课堂上我不会容许那种行为。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n I won t tolerate lying. \n 我不会容忍说谎。 \n, These ants can tolerate temperatures that would kill other species. \n 这些蚂蚁能够忍受可以导致其他物种死亡的高温。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktol/uktold_007.mp3'),('toll','（道路、桥梁等的）通行费长途电话费伤亡；损失；破坏（使）缓慢而反复地鸣响','uk :təʊl, us :toʊl','[Tolls are now collected electronically on most motorways. \n 现在绝大部分高速公路采用电子收费。 \n, Is Bayonne a toll call (= a more expensive phone call) from New York? \n 从纽约打电话到贝约纳是长途吗？ \n, Independent sources say that the death toll from the earthquake runs into thousands. \n 独立消息人士称地震中的伤亡人数达到数千人。 \n, In the distance, a church bell tolled the hour (= showed the time by ringing). \n 远处传来教堂报时的钟声。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktol/uktold_009.mp3'),('torture','拷打；拷问；折磨；虐待折磨，煎熬拷打；拷问；折磨；虐待使精神上受到折磨；使痛苦；使苦恼','uk :ˈtɔː.tʃər, us :ˈtɔːr.tʃɚ','[Half of the prisoners died after torture and starvation. \n 半数的囚犯死于拷打和饥饿。 \n, He revealed the secret under torture. \n 在严刑拷打之下他吐露了秘密。 \n, The rush-hour traffic was sheer torture as usual. \n 交通高峰期像往常一样简直就是一种煎熬。 \n, It is claimed that the officers tortured a man to death in a city police station. \n 据称在一所市警察局里警察将一名男子拷打致死。 \n, He tortured himself for years with the thought that he could have stopped the boy from running into the road. \n 他本可以阻止那个男孩跑到马路上去的想法多年来一直折磨着他。 \n]\n','2019-11-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktor/uktorme030.mp3'),('tract','（尤指有关宗教或政治主题的）短文，传单大片土地（用于建房、采油等特定目的）丈量过的土地（人或动物体内的）管，道，束','uk :trækt, us :trækt','[a moral/religious/socialist tract \n 关于道德说教／宗教／社会主义者的短文 \n, Have you read John Milton s tracts on divorce? \n 你读过约翰‧弥尔顿论离婚的小册子吗？ \n, The house is surrounded by vast tracts of woodland. \n 这幢房子周围是大片的林地。 \n, a 132-acre tract in Irving \n 位于埃尔温的一块132英亩的土地 \n, the urinary/respiratory/digestive tract \n 尿道／呼吸道／消化道 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktow/uktowni026.mp3'),('trailer','拖车；挂车（大卡车的）挂车旅行拖车（影视节目、广播的）预告片','uk :ˈtreɪ.lər, us :ˈtreɪ.lɚ','[The car was pulling a trailer with a motorcycle on it. \n 这辆汽车拖着一辆挂车，挂车上面载着一辆摩托车。 \n, I saw a trailer for the new series of  Game of Thrones  last night. \n 我昨晚看了新一季《权力的游戏》的预告片。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktract026.mp3'),('transaction','交易','uk :trænˈzæk.ʃən, us :trænˈzæk.ʃən','[a business transaction \n 生意 \n, Each transaction at the foreign exchange counter seems to take forever. \n 外币兑换柜台的每笔交易似乎都要花很长时间。 \n, We need to monitor the transaction of smaller deals. \n 我们需要监控规模较小的交易。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrain021.mp3'),('transatlantic','横越大西洋的；大西洋两岸国家的','uk :ˌtræn.zətˈlæn.tɪk, us :ˌtræn.zætˈlæn.t̬ɪk','[transatlantic flights \n 横越大西洋的飞行 \n, a transatlantic phone call \n 来自大西洋彼岸的电话 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrain022.mp3'),('transmit','播送，发射，传送（信号）传递；传播','uk :trænzˈmɪt, us :trænsˈmɪt','[Radio Seven transmits on 201 medium wave (= uses those particular radio waves to broadcast on). \n 广播七台通过中波201千赫广播。 \n, The information is transmitted electronically to the central computer. \n 这些信息以电子化的方式传送到中央计算机。 \n, a sexually transmitted disease \n 性传播疾病 \n, Cholera is transmitted through contaminated water. \n 霍乱是通过受污染的水传播的。 \n, Some diseases are transmitted from one generation to the next. \n 有些疾病是世代遗传的。 \n, Somehow your panic and fear transmits itself to the horse that you re riding. \n 不知怎么的，你的恐惧会传染给你骑的马。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrans105.mp3'),('transparency','透明性，透明幻灯片；透明正片（公开处理，非秘密进行的）透明度','uk :trænˈspær.ən.si, us :trænˈsper.ən.si','[The old-fashioned type of plastic lacked transparency. \n 老式塑料透明性不好。 \n, We want more transparency in government. \n 我们想要政府更透明。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrans112.mp3'),('treaty','条约；协定','uk :ˈtriː.ti, us :ˈtriː.t̬i','[a peace treaty \n 和平条约 \n, the treaty on European union \n 欧盟条约 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We\'ve signed/concluded a treaty with neighbouring states to limit emissions of harmful gases. \n 我们和几个邻国签署／缔结了限制有害气体排放的条约。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktre/uktreac018.mp3'),('trend','趋势，趋向；倾向，动向时尚；新款式时尚的（某一时刻在社交媒体或网站上）被提及最多的词语（主题或名字）','uk :trend, us :','[Surveys show a trend away from home-ownership and toward rented accommodation. \n 调查表明，出现了一种从私人拥有住房转向租赁住房的趋势。 \n, There s been a downward/upward trend in sales in the last few years. \n 过去几年中销售额一直呈下降／上升趋势。 \n, Whatever the latest fashion trend, you can be sure Nicki will be wearing it. \n 不管是什么样的流行款式，尼基肯定会穿。 \n, The trend at the moment is for a more natural and less made-up look. \n 时下的潮流是多一分自然，少一些妆容。 \n, Her long skirt is right on trend this winter. \n 她的长半截裙今年冬季正流行。 \n, Within minutes of the incident her name was trending on Twitter. \n 事件发生几分钟后她的名字就在推特上传开了。 \n, Click here for a list of trending topics. \n 点击这里可以看到热门主题的名单。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktre/uktremu008.mp3'),('trial','审判，审理试验；试用惹麻烦的人；令人伤脑筋的事物；考验预试，模拟考试试验；试用','uk :traɪəl, us :traɪəl','[trial proceedings \n 审判程序 \n, Trial by jury is a fundamental right. \n 由陪审团审判是一项基本权利。 \n, It was a very complicated trial that went on for months. \n 该审判非常复杂，历时数月。 \n, She s going on/standing trial for fraud. \n 她将因诈骗而受审。 \n, They re doing clinical trials on a new drug. \n 他们正在对一种新药进行临床试验。 \n, They ve employed her for a six-month trial (period). \n 他们录用了她，试用期为6个月。 \n, You can have the equipment on a trial basis (UK also on trial), and if you don t like it you can give it back. \n 你可以采用试用方式购买设备，如果不喜欢可以退货。 \n, She was a real trial to her parents when she was younger. \n 她年轻时真令父母头疼。 \n, The book is all about the trials of growing up. \n 这本书讲的全是成长过程中经历的种种烦恼。 \n, Trials take place in July. \n 预试在七月举行。 \n, We will trial the new drug in several hospitals. \n 我们将在几家医院试用这种新药。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktre/uktremu018.mp3'),('tricky','难办的；难对付的欺骗性的；狡猾的；诡计多端的','uk :ˈtrɪk.i, us :ˈtrɪk.i',NULL,'2020-01-07',0,3,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktri/uktribu010.mp3'),('trivialize','使显得不重要','uk :ˈtrɪv.i.ə.laɪz, us :ˈtrɪv.i.ə.laɪz','[I don t want to trivialize the problem, but I do think there are more important matters to discuss. \n 我并不是要贬低这个问题的重要性，我确实认为有更重要的事情需要讨论。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktri/uktrium008.mp3'),('trumpet','小号；喇叭（尤指象等大型动物的）吼声吹嘘；鼓吹','uk :ˈtrʌm.pɪt, us :ˈtrʌm.pət','[We could hear the elephants trumpeting in the distance. \n 我们可以听见远处大象的吼声。 \n, The museum has been loudly trumpeting its reputation as one of the finest. \n 该博物馆一直在大肆吹嘘自己是世界上最好的博物馆之一。 \n, Their much-trumpeted  low low prices  affect only five percent of the goods that they sell. \n 他们极力吹嘘的“一降再降”活动只包括他们所卖商品的5%。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktru/uktruam018.mp3'),('tub-thumping','暴言','Zhòng jī','\n','2020-02-14',5,4,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=tub-thumping&tl=ja&tk=143096.268940&client=webapp&prev=input'),('tumble','跌倒；滚下，坠落；倒塌（价值）暴跌，骤降跌跌撞撞地走摔倒，跌跤；跌落','uk :ˈtʌm.bəl, us :ˈtʌm.bəl','[I lost my footing and tumbled down the stairs. \n 我一失足从楼梯上滚了下来。 \n, At any moment the whole building could tumble down. \n 整幢建筑随时有可能坍塌。 \n, He lost his balance and tumbled over. \n 他失去平衡摔倒了。 \n, Share prices tumbled yesterday. \n 昨天股票大跌。 \n, An excited group of children tumbled out of school/the bus. \n 一群激动不已的孩子一窝蜂地跑出了学校／跑下了公共汽车。 \n, She took a nasty tumble on her way to work and grazed her arm. \n 她上班途中重重摔了一跤，擦伤了胳膊。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktub/uktube_023.mp3'),('tumbler','（无柄无脚的）杯子','uk :ˈtʌm.blər, us :-blɚ','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktub/uktube_025.mp3'),('tweak','扭，拧稍稍改进','uk :twiːk, us :twiːk','[Standing in front of the mirror she tweaked a strand of hair into place. \n 她站在镜子前，把一缕头发捋好。 \n, The software is pretty much there - it just needs a little tweaking. \n 软件差不多好了——只需要一点点改进。 \n, You just need to tweak the last paragraph and then it\'s done. \n 你只需要把最后一段稍作修改就可以了。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktux/uktuxed007.mp3'),('tweed','（杂色的）粗花呢粗花呢服装；（尤指）粗花呢套装','uk :twiːd, us :twiːd','[a tweed jacket \n 花呢短上装 \n, a tweed skirt and sensible shoes \n 花呢裙子及舒适实用的鞋子 \n, He wore tweeds and smoked a pipe. \n 他身上穿着花呢衣服，嘴里叼着烟斗。 \n]\n','2020-01-07',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktux/uktuxed009.mp3'),('twerp','傻瓜，笨蛋','uk :twɜːp, us :twɝːp','[]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktux/uktuxed020.mp3'),('twitchiness','焦虑','null','null\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'null'),('tyranny','暴政，专制统治暴虐，专横','uk :ˈtɪr.ən.i, us :ˈtɪr.ən.i',NULL,'2020-01-07',0,3,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktyp/uktypho016.mp3'),('unanimous','（团体）意见一致的；（决定或裁决）一致通过的，获得全体支持的','uk :juːˈnæn.ɪ.məs, us :juːˈnæn.ə.məs',NULL,'2020-02-14',4,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uku/ukump/ukumpir026.mp3'),('unanimously','満場一致','uk :juːˈnæn.ɪ.məs.li, us :juːˈnæn.ə.məs.li',NULL,'2020-02-14',3,4,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uku/ukump/ukumpir027.mp3'),('unceremoniously','毫不客气地','uk :ʌnˌser.ɪˈməʊ.ni.əs.li, us :ʌnˌser.ɪˈmoʊ.ni.əs.li','[e was unceremoniously removed from the list of members, for gross misconduct.\n, She was unceremoniously dropped from the team.\n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uku/ukunb/ukunben022.mp3'),('unconvincing','（解释或说法）似乎不真实的，不令人信服的','uk :ˌʌn.kənˈvɪn.sɪŋ, us :ˌʌn.kənˈvɪn.sɪŋ','[They gave some unconvincing explanations for the system failure. \n 关于这个系统的失灵，他们给出了一些令人难以信服的理由。 \n, The dialogue was unconvincing, partly because it was American actors trying to speak London English. \n 对白听起来不真实，部分原因在于明明是美国演员，却非要说一口伦敦腔。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uku/ukunc/ukuncon011.mp3'),('undertaking','工作；任务；企业；事业正式承诺','uk :ˌʌn.dəˈteɪ.kɪŋ, us :ˈʌn.dɚˌteɪ.kɪŋ','[The construction of the tunnel is a large and complex undertaking. \n 该隧道的修建是项复杂的大工程。 \n, [ + that ] \n formal \n The manager gave a written undertaking that no one would lose their job. \n 经理写下了书面保证，不会让任何人丢掉工作。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uku/ukund/ukunder124.mp3'),('undertone','（文章或講話的）含意，弦外之音；（事件或情況的）蘊含意義','null','null\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'null'),('unilateral','单边的；单方的','uk :ˌjuː.nɪˈlæt.ər.əl, us :ˌjuː.nəˈlæt̬.ɚ.əl','[The party leader has actually declared her support for unilateral nuclear disarmament (= giving up her country\'s nuclear weapons without first waiting for other countries to do the same). \n 该党领导人实际上已经宣布了她支持单方面核裁军的决定。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uku/ukunh/ukunhea017.mp3'),('unraveled','（把布、结或线团）解开；拆散揭开，弄清，阐明（谜团或复杂问题）；被澄清；被解决破坏（成就等）','uk :ʌnˈræv.əl, us :ʌnˈræv.əl','[You d better mend that hole before the whole sweater starts to unravel. \n 你最好把那个洞补上，免得整件毛衣脱线。 \n, I had to unravel one of the sleeves because I realized I d knitted it too small. \n 我不得不拆掉一只袖子，因为我发现它织得太小了。 \n, We have a long way to go before we unravel the secrets of genetics. \n 在揭开遗传学之谜前，我们还有很长的路要走。 \n, As talks between the leaders broke down, several months of careful diplomacy were unravelled. \n 由于领导人之间的会谈破裂，几个月精心策划的外交努力付诸东流。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uku/ukunp/ukunpre024.mp3'),('unrest','动乱，动荡；骚乱','uk :ʌnˈrest, us :ʌnˈrest',NULL,'2020-02-14',4,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uku/ukunr/ukunrec017.mp3'),('urgent','紧急的，急迫的（尤指某人的行动）执着的，坚定的','uk :ˈɜː.dʒənt, us :ˈɝː.dʒənt','[He s got to sign that paper - will you tell him it s urgent? \n 他务必要签署那份文件——请你告诉他这很紧急，好吗? \n, The most urgent thing in a fire is to make sure everyone is out of the building. \n 失火时最紧要的事是确保所有人都撤离大楼。 \n, Many people are in urgent need of food and water. \n 很多人亟需食物和水。 \n, His urgent pleas of innocence made no difference to the judge s decision. \n 他一再申辩自己无罪，却无法改变法官的判决。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uku/ukups/ukupstr028.mp3'),('utter','>说；讲；出声>完全的；十足的；极度的','uk :>ˈʌt.ə, us :>ˈʌ.t̬ɚ',NULL,'2020-02-13',4,11,1,NULL),('vaccine','疫苗','uk :ˈvæk.siːn, us :ˈvæk.siːn','[This vaccine protects against some kinds of the bacteria. \n 这种疫苗能抵抗这些细菌中的某几种。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uku/ukutt/ukutter017.mp3'),('vagabond','流浪者；（通常指）无业游民','uk :ˈvæɡ.ə.bɒnd, us :ˈvæɡ.ə.bɑːnd','[They live a vagabond life/existence, travelling around in a caravan. \n 他们开着大篷车四处漂泊过活。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uku/ukutt/ukutter025.mp3'),('vast','巨大的；广大的','uk :vɑːst, us :væst','[A vast audience watched the broadcast. \n 大量的观众观看了转播。 \n, The amount of detail the book contains is vast. \n 该书所包含的细节内容非常丰富。 \n, The people who have taken our advice have saved themselves vast amounts/sums of money. \n 那些听从了我们建议的人省了一大笔钱。 \n, The vast majority of children attend state schools. \n 绝大部分学生就读于政府学校。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvar/ukvario011.mp3'),('vehicle','（陆上）交通工具；车辆；机动车（实现、产生或表达…的）方法，手段，媒介（为某个表演者或艺术家）特意制作的电影（或演出节目、展览等）','uk :ˈvɪə.kəl, us :ˈviː.ə.kəl','[A truck driver died last night when his vehicle overturned. \n 昨晚一辆卡车翻了车，司机死亡。 \n, Road vehicles include cars, buses, and trucks. \n 道路交通工具包括汽车、公共汽车和卡车。 \n, Tractors are farm vehicles. \n 拖拉机是农用车辆。 \n, The number of thefts of motor vehicles rose by a third last year. \n 去年机动车失窃案数量上升了1/3。 \n, The conference was seen as an ideal vehicle for increased cooperation between the member states. \n 那次会议被视为增进成员国之间合作的理想途径。 \n, The play seems to be little more than a vehicle for its director and star. \n 那部戏看起来不过是为其导演兼主演量身打造的而已。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvec/ukvecto021.mp3'),('vent','通风口；排气口（衣物的）开衩，衩口（常指不公地）发泄（负面情绪）发泄，表达（负面的情绪）','uk :vent, us :vent','[If you have a gas fire in a room, you should have some kind of outside vent. \n 如果你的屋里有煤气炉，那你就应该有个通向外面的排气口。 \n, The skirt is long and straight with two side vents. \n 这条裙子是很长的直筒裙，两侧开衩。 \n, The meeting will be an opportunity for everyone to give vent to their feelings. \n 这次会议将给每个人一吐为快的机会。 \n, Please don t shout - there s no need to vent your frustration/anger/rage/spleen on me. \n 请不要大吵大闹——没有必要把气撒在我身上。 \n, I didn t mean to upset anyone, I just needed to vent. \n 我没想要针对任何人，我只是想发泄一下。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvel/ukvelve027.mp3'),('versus','以…为对手；对（诉讼案中）诉（尤指进行选择时）与…相比','uk :ˈvɜː.səs, us :ˈvɝː.səs',NULL,'2020-02-13',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukver/ukverit019.mp3'),('vest-pocket','背心口袋','Bèixīn kǒudài','\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=vest-pocket&tl=ja&tk=772793.917197&client=webapp&prev=input'),('veto','否决；禁止否决；禁止','uk :ˈviː.təʊ, us :ˈviː.t̬oʊ','[The president has the power of veto over any bill that comes across his desk. \n 总统可以利用否决权来阻止任何议案的通过。 \n, In theory the British government could use its veto to block this proposal. \n 理论上英国政府可以利用否决权来阻止这项议案通过。 \n, The Senate voted to override the president\'s veto of the proposed measures. \n 参议院投票推翻了总统对拟议中的措施的否决。 \n, ainly UK \n My parents put a veto on our watching television for more than two hours each evening. \n 妈妈禁止我们每天晚上看电视超过两个小时。 \n, In 1961, President De Gaulle vetoed Britain\'s entry into the Common Market. \n 1961年，戴高乐总统行使否决权，反对英国加入西欧共同市场。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n My boss vetoed my taking any more time off this year. \n 我的老板不允许我今年再请假。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukver/ukverve015.mp3'),('vicious','邪恶的；恶毒的；凶暴的严重的；剧烈的，恶毒的','uk :ˈvɪʃ.əs, us :ˈvɪʃ.əs','[a vicious thug \n 凶残的暴徒 \n, a vicious dog \n 恶狗 \n, The police said that this was one of the most vicious attacks they d ever seen. \n 警方说这是他们所见过的最为残暴的袭击之一。 \n, He gave her a vicious look. \n 他恶狠狠地瞪了她一眼。 \n, a large collection of vicious medieval torture instruments \n 收藏的大量中世纪的酷刑刑具 \n, a vicious lie/accusation/rumour \n 恶意的谎言／指控／谣言 \n, I have a vicious headache. \n 我头疼得厉害。 \n]\n','2019-11-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvia/ukvia__029.mp3'),('viper','蝰蛇（一种小毒蛇）阴险的人','uk :ˈvaɪ.pər, us :ˈvaɪ.pɚ','[When I started my new job, I didn\'t realize that I was walking into a nest of vipers. \n 当我开始新的工作时，我没有意识到自己已经进了一个蛇蝎之窝。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvin/ukvineg021.mp3'),('viral','病毒病，病毒性疾病；病毒感染（通过网络在个体之间迅速）病毒式的（传播）','uk :ˈvaɪə.rəl, us :ˈvaɪ.rəl','[viral infections \n 病毒感染 \n, Here s a list of the top ten viral videos this week. \n 以下是本周十大病毒式传播的视频。 \n, Within days the film clip went viral. \n 几天内这段电影视频便病毒式地传开了。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvin/ukvineg025.mp3'),('virtue','美德；高尚品德优点；好处因为；由于；凭借','uk :ˈvɜː.tʃuː, us :ˈvɝː.tʃuː',NULL,'2020-02-14',4,3,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvir/ukvirgi010.mp3'),('vocal','嗓音的；发声的喜欢畅所欲言的；直言不讳的（流行音乐中的）演唱部分','uk :ˈvəʊ.kəl, us :ˈvoʊ.kəl',NULL,'2020-02-14',4,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukviv/ukviva_017.mp3'),('vocalist','歌手；（尤指）流行乐队的主唱','uk :ˈvəʊ.kəl.ɪst, us :ˈvoʊ.kəl.ɪst','[She won the Grammy Award for Best Female Vocalist. \n 她赢得了格莱美最佳女歌手奖。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukviv/ukviva_018.mp3'),('volatility','波动性','uk :ˌvɒl.əˈtɪl.ə.ti, us :ˌvɑː.ləˈtɪl.ə.t̬i','[he volatility of the political situation\n, worries about volatility in the economy\n, market/price/currency volatility\n, here are many stories about his volatility and volcanic temper.\n, he higher the vapour pressure of a liquid at a given temperature, the higher the volatility.\n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvoi/ukvoila004.mp3'),('volume','容积；体积；容量总数；总量；总额音量；音量调节钮卷；册书','uk :ˈvɒl.juːm, us :ˈvɑːl.juːm','[Which of these bottles do you think has the greater volume? \n 你认为这些瓶子中哪个容积最大？ \n, It s the sheer volume of traffic in the city that is causing the problems. \n 造成这些问题的就是城里的交通流量。 \n, Could you turn the volume down, please, I m trying to sleep. \n 你能把音量调低些吗？我要睡觉。 \n, I ll turn it up if you tell me which one is the volume (= switch). \n 如果你告诉我哪个是音量钮的话，我会把声音开大些。 \n, The second volume of his memoirs will be published later this year. \n 他回忆录的第二卷将于今年晚些时候面世。 \n, She took a slim volume down from the shelf. \n 她从书架上取下一本很薄的书。 \n, a volume of poetry \n 一本诗集 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvoi/ukvoila018.mp3'),('wailing','恸哭；号啕大哭高声抱怨；大发牢骚恸哭；号啕大哭','uk :weɪl, us :weɪl','[The women gathered around the coffin and began to wail, as was the custom in the region. \n 女人们都围到了棺材旁，开始号啕大哭，当地的风俗就是这样。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  My finger hurts,  wailed the child. \n “我的手指头很疼，”那个孩子大哭道。 \n, [ + that ] \n Business people wailed that their trade would be ruined. \n 生意人都强烈抱怨说他们的买卖会被毁掉的。 \n, a wail of anguish \n 痛苦的哀号 \n, the wail of the police sirens \n 警笛的尖啸声 \n]\n','2019-12-26',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukv/ukvul/ukvulva028.mp3'),('walkdowntheaisle','结婚','null','null\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'null'),('ware','（常用于商店中表示用于烹饪或餐饮的）…制品，…用具','uk : -weər, us : -wer','[tableware \n 餐具 \n, the kitchenware department \n 厨房用品部 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd30/epd30026.mp3'),('wary','谨慎的；小心翼翼的','uk :ˈweə.ri, us :ˈwer.i','[I m a little wary of/about giving people my address when I don t know them very well. \n 如果不是太熟的话，我不会轻易告诉别人我的地址。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwar/ukwarp_015.mp3'),('watertight','防水的，水密的；不透水的（理论、计划或协议）严密的，无懈可击的，毫无破绽的（足球队防守）滴水不漏','uk :ˈwɔː.tə.taɪt, us :ˈwɑː.t̬ɚ.taɪt','[They\'re doing some repairs to make the roof more watertight. \n 他们在进行一些修理，以加强屋顶的防水性。 \n, This book is designed to be provocative rather than a watertight piece of economic analysis. \n 这本书旨在引发大家辩论，而不是要对经济进行缜密的分析。 \n, Rovers\' defence will need to be watertight in their Carling Cup clash with Watford. \n 巡游者队在卡林杯赛上遭遇沃特福德队时防守必须滴水不漏。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwat/ukwater018.mp3'),('wheeze','（因呼吸困难而）发出粗重的呼吸声，喘息，发出呼哧呼哧声（因呼吸困难而）发出粗重的呼吸声，喘息，发出呼哧呼哧声（尤指为获利而想出的）巧计，计谋','uk :wiːz, us :wiːz','[I could hear the old man behind me wheezing. \n 我能听到身后的老人呼哧呼哧的喘气声。 \n, I know when I\'ve been smoking too much because I start to wheeze when I run for a train. \n 我知道自己烟抽得太多了，因为我在跑着赶火车时开始呼哧呼哧地喘。 \n, The cough, wheeze, and shortness of breath are things that go with smoking, not with age. \n 咳嗽、气喘和气短不是因为上了年纪，而是因为吸烟引起的。 \n, As a part of their latest marketing wheeze they\'re giving away tickets for the concert. \n 作为最新营销策略的一部分，他们在免费赠送音乐会的票。 \n, So the public actually pay to feed the animals in the zoo? That seems like a good wheeze. \n 那么人们实际上是花钱来喂动物园里的动物？这听起来像个好主意。 \n, I\'ve had a wheeze - why don\'t we put both kids in the small room and that will leave the back room free. \n 我有个主意——为什么不把两个孩子放在那间小一点的屋子里，这样后边的屋子就可以空出来了。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwhe/ukwheel008.mp3'),('wield','挥舞，握，抓着（武器或工具）施加影响／运用权力（等等）','uk :wiːld, us :wiːld','[She was confronted by a man wielding a knife. \n 她受到一名持刀男子的威胁。 \n, He still wields enormous influence in politics. \n 他在政坛仍然很有影响。 \n]\n','2019-10-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwi_/ukwi___016.mp3'),('winding','风；气流呼吸；呼吸能力空谈，废话肠气，胃气，肠胃气胀（管弦乐队中的）木管乐器组（击打腹部而）使气急，使呼吸困难（用抚拍的方法）使（婴儿）打嗝通气绕；使卷绕给（钟表）上弦，给…上发条（道路或河流等）曲折前进，蜿蜒包，裹；使缠绕成团弯弯的','uk :wɪnd, us :wɪnd','[There isn t enough wind to fly a kite. \n 风不够大，风筝飞不起来。 \n, The forecast warned of winds of up to 60 miles an hour today. \n 天气预报警告说，今天有时速高达60英里的强风。 \n, There was a light wind blowing. \n 微风轻拂。 \n, Strong/High winds made the crossing very choppy. \n 强风使横渡变得非常不舒服。 \n, The sails flapped in the wind. \n 风帆在风中啪啪地拍打着。 \n, iterary \n There wasn t a breath of (= even a slight amount of) wind. \n 没有一丝风。 \n, A gust of wind suddenly caught her skirt. \n 突然一阵风吹动了她的裙子。 \n, The wind is beginning to pick up (= get stronger). \n 风开始越刮越猛。 \n, She ran like the wind (= very fast) to catch up. \n 她像一阵风似的赶了上去。 \n, The blow to my stomach knocked the wind out of me. \n 打在腹部的一记重拳让我喘不过气来。 \n, I rarely bother to listen to politicians  speeches - it s all just wind. \n 几乎从不费神去听政治家的演讲——都是废话。 \n, I like garlic but it gives me terrible wind. \n 我爱吃大蒜，但吃了肚子胀气很厉害。 \n, She wound the handle but nothing happened. \n 她转动把手，但是没起什么作用。 \n, Once she was in the car, she wound the window down/up (= caused it to open/close by turning a handle). \n 她一进到车里，就把车窗玻璃摇了下来／上去。 \n, That noise you can hear is the tape winding back. \n 你能听到的噪音是倒磁带的声音。 \n, The river winds through the valley. \n 河流弯弯曲曲地穿过山谷。 \n, She wound a scarf around her neck. \n 她在脖子上围了一条围巾。 \n, He wound the string into a ball. \n 他将绳子缠成一团。 \n, He wound a small bandage round her finger. \n 他在她的手指上缠了一小条绷带。 \n, There s a very long, winding path leading up to the house. \n 一条很长的弯弯小路通向这所房子。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwil/ukwildl027.mp3'),('winging','（鸟类等的）翅膀；（飞机的）机翼飞走突然发展；自由飞扬（鸟儿）正在飞翔（政党中的）派别，宗派（常指后来增建的）建筑翼部，厢房，侧厅（汽车的）挡泥板，翼子板（足球、曲棍球等集体项目的）侧翼位置，侧翼队员，边锋队员（舞台的）侧面即兴做；即兴发言','uk :wɪŋ, us :wɪŋ','[the delicacy of a butterfly s wings \n 蝴蝶翅膀的精致 \n, I don t like chicken wings - there s not much meat on them. \n 我不喜欢吃鸡翅——上面没有多少肉。 \n, I could see the plane s wing out of my window. \n 我透过身边的窗户能看到飞机的机翼。 \n, She walked in the hills, letting her thoughts take wing. \n 她走在山间，任思绪自由飞扬。 \n, The president is on the left wing of the Democratic party. \n 总统属于民主党左翼。 \n, The extreme right wing of the party has dominated the discussion. \n 该党派中的极端右翼主导了讨论。 \n, The maternity department will be in the new wing of the hospital. \n 产科病房将设在医院新建的一侧。 \n, The west wing of the house is still lived in by Lord and Lady Carlton, while the rest of the house is open to the public. \n 房子的西翼仍由卡尔顿勋爵及夫人居住，而其余部分则向公众开放。 \n, There s a dent in the left wing. \n 左挡泥板上有个凹痕。 \n, Look in your wing mirror. \n 看你侧面的反光镜。 \n, Zinoli passes the ball to Pereira out there on the wing. \n 齐诺利将球传给处在边锋位置的佩雷拉。 \n, He played left/right wing for Manchester United. \n 他在曼联队踢左／右边锋。 \n, I was in the wings waiting for my cue to come on stage. \n 我站在舞台的侧面，等待着上台的提示。 \n, I didn t have time to prepare for the talk, so I just had to wing it. \n 我没时间准备发言，所以只好即兴发挥了。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwin/ukwinde023.mp3'),('wipe','擦，拭，抹（湿）抹布；（湿）纸巾；（湿）手巾擦，拭，抹','uk :waɪp, us :waɪp','[Do you have some paper towels that I can wipe the floor with? \n 你有没有我可以用来擦地板的纸巾？ \n, I ll just get a sponge and wipe the crumbs off the table. \n 我这就去找块海绵把桌子上的碎屑擦掉。 \n, Don t wipe your nose on your sleeve! \n 别用袖子擦鼻子！ \n, Someone has wiped their dirty hands on my nice clean towel! \n 有人在我干净漂亮的毛巾上擦过脏手！ \n, baby wipes \n 婴儿纸巾 \n, I d better give the floor a quick wipe before someone slips on it. \n 我最好赶快擦一下地板，省得有人滑倒。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwin/ukwinni012.mp3'),('wire','金属丝；金属线电线；导线（尤指藏在衣服内的）窃听器（监狱等处的）铁丝网电报用金属丝捆扎为（电子设备）接上电线（或导线）用电报传送；（尤指）电汇（过去）给…发电报','uk :waɪər, us :waɪr','[a wire fence \n 金属线栅栏 \n, Someone had cut the phone wires. \n 有人切断了电话线。 \n, Don t touch those wires whatever you do. \n 无论如何都别碰那些导线。 \n, The undercover police officer was wearing a wire during the meeting. \n 卧底警官身上藏着窃听器参加了会面。 \n, During the war he spent three years behind the wire (= in prison). \n 战争期间他蹲了3年监狱。 \n, She had her jaws wired together so that she wouldn t be able to eat. \n 她把上下颌用金属丝捆在一起，这样就不能吃东西了。 \n, The stereo wasn t working because it hadn t been wired up correctly. \n 立体声音响不响了，因为电线没有接好。 \n, Nearly one home in ten across the country is wired up to receive TV via cable. \n 该国有近十分之一的家庭通过电缆接收电视信号。 \n, The insurance company wired millions of dollars to its accounts to cover the payments. \n 保险公司向其账户里电汇了几百万美元以支付该款项。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n Luckily my father wired me two hundred bucks. \n 幸运的是，爸爸电汇给我200美元。 \n, Janet wired me to say she d be here a day later than planned. \n 珍妮特发电报给我，说她要比计划晚一天到这里。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwin/ukwinni014.mp3'),('wither','（使）枯萎，（使）干枯萎缩；逐渐消失','uk :ˈwɪð.ər, us :ˈwɪð.ɚ','[Grass had withered in the fields. \n 田里的草都枯萎了。 \n, This country is in danger of allowing its industrial base to wither away. \n 这个国家正面临着工业基础萎缩的危险。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwis/ukwispy017.mp3'),('witnessing','（尤指犯罪或事故的）目击者看到；目睹见证人；连署人（法庭上的）证人专家证人目击，看到（尤指事故或犯罪）为…签名作证；连署是发生…的地点（或时间）证明；表明','uk :ˈwɪt.nəs, us :ˈwɪt.nəs','[Police are appealing for witnesses to the accident to come forward. \n 警方呼吁那场事故的目击者站出来。 \n, According to (eye) witnesses, the robbery was carried out by two teenage boys. \n 据目击者说，抢劫案是两个十几岁的少年干的。 \n, She was witness to the tragic event. \n 她目睹了这一悲剧。 \n, He signed the treaty in the presence of two witnesses. \n 他在两位见证人面前签署了条约。 \n, They were married a year after they first met, with two friends acting as witnesses. \n 初次见面一年之后，他们在两位朋友的见证之下结婚了。 \n, Ten witnesses are expected to testify at the trial today. \n 在今天的审判中，将有两名证人出庭作证。 \n, The key witness for the prosecution was offered police protection after she received death threats. \n 原告的关键证人在受到死亡恐吓后得到了警方的保护。 \n, A psychiatrist was called as an expert witness for the defence. \n 一位精神病医生作为被告的专家证人被传作证。 \n, Did anyone witness the attack? \n 有人看到那次袭击了吗？ \n, They were staying in the capital at the time of the riots and witnessed several street battles. \n 暴乱期间他们在首都，目击了好几起巷战。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n He arrived home just in time to witness his brother being taken away by the police. \n 他到家时正好看到他兄弟被警察带走。 \n, Her will was witnessed by two colleagues. \n 她的遗嘱由两名同事签名作证。 \n, This university has witnessed quite a few changes over the years. \n 这所大学多年来经历过很多变革。 \n, Those years witnessed momentous changes throughout Europe. \n 那些年间整个欧洲都发生了重大的变化。 \n, This year s charity ball was the most successful one ever, as witnessed by the number of tickets sold. \n 今年的慈善舞会是最为成功的一次，这可以从售出门票的数量上看出来。 \n, The programme aroused strong feelings - witness the number of letters received. \n 这个节目激起了强烈的反响——来信的数量便是明证。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwis/ukwispy029.mp3'),('wobble','（使）摇晃，（使）摇摆拿不定主意；动摇；（在两种观点间）变来变去摇晃，摇摆拿不定主意；动摇；（在两种观点间）变来变去','uk :ˈwɒb.əl, us :ˈwɑː.bəl','[That bookcase wobbles whenever you put anything on it. \n 那个书架你一放东西就摇摇晃晃的。 \n, Don t wobble the table, please, Dan. \n 丹，别晃桌子好吗？ \n, igurative \n The company s shares wobbled with the news of a foreign takeover bid. \n 这家公司的股票由于外国公司收购的消息而波动。 \n, The government can t afford to wobble on this issue. \n 如果政府在这个问题上不作出果断决策就会付出巨大代价。 \n, I gave the poles a slight wobble and the whole tent collapsed. \n 我轻轻晃了晃几根柱子，整个帐篷就倒了。 \n, igurative \n The closure of the company s German subsidiary caused a sharp wobble in its profits. \n 这家公司德国分部的关闭导致其利润急剧下降。 \n, She s having a bit of a wobble about the move to New York. \n 她对是否搬到纽约还有点犹豫不定。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwit/ukwitte011.mp3'),('worthwhile','值得的；值得花钱（或时间、精力）的','uk :ˌwɜːθˈwaɪl, us :ˌwɝːθˈwaɪl','[She considers teaching a worthwhile career. \n 她把教书看成是一项值得从事的事业。 \n, The time and expense involved in keeping up to date with all the changes has been worthwhile. \n 为跟上所有这些变动而花费的时间和费用是值得的。 \n, If you need him on this project, you ve got to make it financially worthwhile for him (= you will have to pay him a suitable amount of money for the amount of work involved). \n 如果你需要他参与这个项目，你就得适当付给他钱，让他觉得值得一做。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwor/ukworth006.mp3'),('wristwatch','手表，腕表','uk :ˈrɪst.wɒtʃ, us :ˈrɪst.wɑːtʃ','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukw/ukwre/ukwreat024.mp3'),('yard','码（相当于3英尺，约91.4厘米）（进行某种工作的）场地，场所；（常指出售货物的）场地院子；天井；庭院（房屋旁的）园圃，花园','uk :jɑːd, us :jɑːrd','[a lumber yard \n 堆木场 \n, a scrap yard \n 废料场 \n, The house has a small yard at the back. \n 这所房子后面有个小院。 \n, The children played in the school yard. \n 孩子们在学校的院落里玩耍。 \n, a prison yard \n 监狱里的院子 \n, The kids were playing in the yard. \n 孩子们在房子旁边的花园里玩。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukx/ukxra/ukxray_024.mp3'),('yawnfest','无聊','null','null\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'null'),('yon','（在）那边','uk :ˈjɒn.dər, us :ˈjɑːn.dɚ','[]\n','2019-